56 /// Return a `memref.dim` or `tensor.dim` for the shape of `v` at `dim`.
57 static OpFoldResult getDimValue(OpBuilder &builder, Location loc, Value v,
58  int64_t dim) {
59  auto type = cast<ShapedType>(v.getType());
60  if (!type.isDynamicDim(dim))
61  return builder.getIndexAttr(type.getDimSize(dim));
62 
63  return getAsOpFoldResult(
64  TypeSwitch<Type, Value>(v.getType())
65  .Case<RankedTensorType>([&](RankedTensorType t) -> Value {
66  return tensor::DimOp::create(builder, loc, v, dim);
67  })
68  .Case<MemRefType>([&](MemRefType t) -> Value {
69  return memref::DimOp::create(builder, loc, v, dim);
70  }));
71 }
72 
73 /// Returns a memref.subview or a tensor.extract_slice based on the type of the
74 /// `source`.
75 static Operation *getSlice(OpBuilder &b, Location loc, Value source,
76  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> offsets,
77  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> sizes,
78  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> strides) {
79  return TypeSwitch<Type, Operation *>(source.getType())
80  .Case<RankedTensorType>([&](RankedTensorType t) -> Operation * {
81  return tensor::ExtractSliceOp::create(b, loc, source, offsets, sizes,
82  strides);
83  })
84  .Case<MemRefType>([&](MemRefType type) -> Operation * {
85  return memref::SubViewOp::create(b, loc, source, offsets, sizes,
86  strides);
87  })
88  .Default([&](Type t) -> Operation * { return nullptr; });
89 }

95 Value linalg::createOrFoldDimOp(OpBuilder &b, Location loc, Value source,
96  int64_t dim) {
97  if (llvm::isa<UnrankedMemRefType, MemRefType>(source.getType()))
98  return b.createOrFold<memref::DimOp>(loc, source, dim);
99  if (llvm::isa<UnrankedTensorType, RankedTensorType>(source.getType()))
100  return b.createOrFold<tensor::DimOp>(loc, source, dim);
101  llvm_unreachable("Expected MemRefType or TensorType");
102 }
103 
104 OpFoldResult linalg::createFoldedDimOp(OpBuilder &b, Location loc, Value source,
105  int64_t dim) {
106  auto shapedType = llvm::cast<ShapedType>(source.getType());
107  if (!shapedType.hasRank() || shapedType.isDynamicDim(dim))
108  return createOrFoldDimOp(b, loc, source, dim);
109  return b.getIndexAttr(shapedType.getDimSize(dim));
110 }

116 using RegionBuilderFn = llvm::function_ref<void(
117  ImplicitLocOpBuilder &, Block &, ArrayRef<NamedAttribute>,
118  function_ref<InFlightDiagnostic()>)>;
119 
120 /// Fills the region of a structured operation using the provided
121 /// `regionBuilder`. The method is used by both named structured ops created by
122 /// ods-gen and by manually defined C++ ops. It is called by both builders and
123 /// parsers and creates a block with arguments corresponding to the elemental
124 /// types of `inputTypes` and `outputTypes`.
125 static void fillStructuredOpRegion(OpBuilder &opBuilder, Region &region,
126  TypeRange inputTypes, TypeRange outputTypes,
127  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attrs,
128  function_ref<InFlightDiagnostic()> emitError,
129  RegionBuilderFn regionBuilder) {
130  SmallVector<Type, 8> argTypes;
131  SmallVector<Location, 8> argLocs;
132  for (auto containers : {inputTypes, outputTypes}) {
133  for (auto t : containers) {
134  argTypes.push_back(
135  isa<MemRefType, RankedTensorType>(t) ? getElementTypeOrSelf(t) : t);
136 
137  // TODO: Pass in a proper location here.
138  argLocs.push_back(opBuilder.getUnknownLoc());
139  }
140  }
141 
142  // RAII.
143  OpBuilder::InsertionGuard guard(opBuilder);
144  Block *body =
145  opBuilder.createBlock(&region, /*insertPt=*/{}, argTypes, argLocs);
146 
147  opBuilder.setInsertionPointToStart(body);
148  ImplicitLocOpBuilder b(opBuilder.getUnknownLoc(), opBuilder);
149  regionBuilder(b, *body, attrs, emitError);
150 
151  // indexing_maps is an auto-generated method.
152 
153  // iterator_types is an auto-generated method.
154 }
155 
156 /// Creates a structured operation given `inputs`, `outputs`, and `attributes`.
157 /// The result types are derived automatically if `resultTensorTypes` is none.
158 /// The body of the operation is filled using `regionBuilder`. All ods-gen
159 /// created structured operations use the method to implement their builders.
160 static void buildStructuredOp(OpBuilder &b, OperationState &state,
161  std::optional<TypeRange> resultTensorTypes,
162  ValueRange inputs, ValueRange outputs,
163  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attributes,
164  RegionBuilderFn regionBuilder) {
165  // Derive the result types if needed.
166  SmallVector<Type> derivedResultTypes =
167  resultTensorTypes.value_or(TypeRange());
168  if (!resultTensorTypes)
169  copy_if(outputs.getTypes(), std::back_inserter(derivedResultTypes),
170  llvm::IsaPred<RankedTensorType>);
171 
172  state.addOperands(inputs);
173  state.addOperands(outputs);
174  state.addTypes(derivedResultTypes);
175 
176  state.addAttributes(attributes);
177  state.addAttribute(
178  "operandSegmentSizes",
179  b.getDenseI32ArrayAttr({static_cast<int32_t>(inputs.size()),
180  static_cast<int32_t>(outputs.size())}));
181 
182  // Create and fill the region of the structured operation.
183  Region &region = *state.addRegion();
184  fillStructuredOpRegion(b, region, TypeRange(inputs), TypeRange(outputs),
185  state.attributes.getAttrs(), /*emitError=*/{},
186  regionBuilder);
187 }
188 
189 static void buildMatmulOp(OpBuilder &b, OperationState &state,
190  std::optional<TypeRange> resultTensorTypes,
191  ValueRange inputs, ValueRange outputs,
192  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attributes,
193  RegionBuilderFn regionBuilder,
194  ArrayRef<AffineMap> indexingMaps) {
195  // Initialize indexingMaps attribute, for MatmulOp.
196  SmallVector<Attribute, 3> indexingMapsAttrVal;
197  indexingMapsAttrVal = llvm::map_to_vector(
198  MatmulOp::getDefaultIndexingMaps(b.getContext()),
199  [](AffineMap map) -> Attribute { return AffineMapAttr::get(map); });
200  state.addAttribute("indexing_maps", b.getArrayAttr(indexingMapsAttrVal));
201  return buildStructuredOp(b, state, resultTensorTypes, inputs, outputs,
202  attributes, regionBuilder);
203 }
204 
205 static void buildBatchMatmulOp(OpBuilder &b, OperationState &state,
206  std::optional<TypeRange> resultTensorTypes,
207  ValueRange inputs, ValueRange outputs,
208  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attributes,
209  RegionBuilderFn regionBuilder,
210  ArrayRef<AffineMap> indexingMaps) {
211  // Initialize indexingMaps attribute, for BatchMatmulOp.
212  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> indexingMapsAttrVal;
213  indexingMapsAttrVal =
214  llvm::map_to_vector(indexingMaps, [](AffineMap map) -> Attribute {
215  return AffineMapAttr::get(map);
216  });
217  state.addAttribute("indexing_maps", b.getArrayAttr(indexingMapsAttrVal));
218  return buildStructuredOp(b, state, resultTensorTypes, inputs, outputs,
219  attributes, regionBuilder);
220 }

222 static void buildBatchReduceMatmulOp(OpBuilder &b, OperationState &state,
223  std::optional<TypeRange> resultTensorTypes,
224  ValueRange inputs, ValueRange outputs,
225  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attributes,
226  RegionBuilderFn regionBuilder,
227  ArrayRef<AffineMap> indexingMaps) {
228  // Initialize indexingMaps attribute, for BatchReduceMatmulOp.
229  SmallVector<Attribute, 4> indexingMapsAttrVal;
230  indexingMapsAttrVal =
231  llvm::map_to_vector(indexingMaps, [](AffineMap map) -> Attribute {
232  return AffineMapAttr::get(map);
233  });
234  state.addAttribute("indexing_maps", b.getArrayAttr(indexingMapsAttrVal));
235  return buildStructuredOp(b, state, resultTensorTypes, inputs, outputs,
236  attributes, regionBuilder);
237 }

239 /// Common parsing used for both named structured ops created by ods-gen and by
240 /// manually defined C++ ops. Does not handle regions.
241 static ParseResult
242 parseCommonStructuredOpParts(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result,
243  SmallVectorImpl<Type> &inputTypes,
244  SmallVectorImpl<Type> &outputTypes,
245  bool addOperandSegmentSizes = true) {
246  SMLoc attrsLoc, inputsOperandsLoc, outputsOperandsLoc;
247  SmallVector<OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand, 4> inputsOperands,
248  outputsOperands;
249 
250  if (succeeded(parser.parseOptionalLess())) {
251  if (parser.parseAttribute(result.propertiesAttr) || parser.parseGreater())
252  return failure();
253  }
254  attrsLoc = parser.getCurrentLocation();
255  if (parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes))
256  return failure();
257 
258  if (succeeded(parser.parseOptionalKeyword("ins"))) {
259  if (parser.parseLParen())
260  return failure();
261 
262  inputsOperandsLoc = parser.getCurrentLocation();
263  if (parser.parseOperandList(inputsOperands) ||
264  parser.parseColonTypeList(inputTypes) || parser.parseRParen())
265  return failure();
266  }
267 
268  if (succeeded(parser.parseOptionalKeyword("outs"))) {
269  outputsOperandsLoc = parser.getCurrentLocation();
270  if (parser.parseLParen() || parser.parseOperandList(outputsOperands) ||
271  parser.parseColonTypeList(outputTypes) || parser.parseRParen())
272  return failure();
273  }
274 
275  if (parser.resolveOperands(inputsOperands, inputTypes, inputsOperandsLoc,
276  result.operands) ||
277  parser.resolveOperands(outputsOperands, outputTypes, outputsOperandsLoc,
278  result.operands))
279  return failure();
280 
281  if (addOperandSegmentSizes) {
282  // This is a bit complex because we're trying to be backward compatible with
283  // operation syntax that mix the inherent attributes and the discardable
284  // ones in the same dictionary. If the properties are used, we append the
285  // operandSegmentSizes there directly. Otherwise we append it to the
286  // discardable attributes dictionary where it is handled by the generic
287  // Operation::create(...) method.
288  if (result.propertiesAttr) {
289  NamedAttrList attrs = llvm::cast<DictionaryAttr>(result.propertiesAttr);
290  attrs.append("operandSegmentSizes",
291  parser.getBuilder().getDenseI32ArrayAttr(
292  {static_cast<int32_t>(inputsOperands.size()),
293  static_cast<int32_t>(outputsOperands.size())}));
294  result.propertiesAttr = attrs.getDictionary(parser.getContext());
295  } else {
296  result.addAttribute("operandSegmentSizes",
297  parser.getBuilder().getDenseI32ArrayAttr(
298  {static_cast<int32_t>(inputsOperands.size()),
299  static_cast<int32_t>(outputsOperands.size())}));
300  }
301  }
302  if (!result.propertiesAttr) {
303  std::optional<RegisteredOperationName> info =
304  result.name.getRegisteredInfo();
305  if (info) {
306  if (failed(info->verifyInherentAttrs(result.attributes, [&]() {
307  return parser.emitError(attrsLoc)
308  << "'" << result.name.getStringRef() << "' op ";
309  })))
310  return failure();
311  }
312  }
313  return success();
314 }
315 
316 static void printCommonStructuredOpParts(OpAsmPrinter &p, ValueRange inputs,
317  ValueRange outputs) {
318  if (!inputs.empty())
319  p << " ins(" << inputs << " : " << inputs.getTypes() << ")";
320  if (!outputs.empty())
321  p << " outs(" << outputs << " : " << outputs.getTypes() << ")";
322 }
323 
324 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
325 // Specific parsing and printing for named structured ops created by ods-gen.
326 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
327 
328 static ParseResult parseNamedStructuredOpRegion(
329  OpAsmParser &parser, Region &region, unsigned numRegionArgs,
330  TypeRange inputTypes, TypeRange outputTypes, ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attrs,
331  RegionBuilderFn regionBuilder, SMLoc loc) {
332  if (numRegionArgs != inputTypes.size() + outputTypes.size()) {
333  return parser.emitError(
334  parser.getCurrentLocation(),
335  llvm::formatv("[parseNamedStructuredOpRegion] ods-gen generated "
336  "region expects {0} args, got {1}",
337  numRegionArgs, inputTypes.size() + outputTypes.size()));
338  }
339 
340  OpBuilder opBuilder(parser.getContext());
341  ParseResult result = success();
342  fillStructuredOpRegion(
343  opBuilder, region, inputTypes, outputTypes, attrs,
344  [&]() {
345  result = failure();
346  return parser.emitError(loc);
347  },
348  regionBuilder);
349  return result;
350 }
351 
352 static ParseResult
353 parseNamedStructuredOpResults(OpAsmParser &parser,
354  SmallVectorImpl<Type> &resultTypes) {
355  if (parser.parseOptionalArrowTypeList(resultTypes))
356  return failure();
357  return success();
358 }
359 
360 static ParseResult parseNamedStructuredOp(OpAsmParser &parser,
361  OperationState &result,
362  unsigned numRegionArgs,
363  RegionBuilderFn regionBuilder) {
364  // TODO: Enable when ods-gen supports captures.
365  SmallVector<Type, 1> inputTypes, outputTypes;
366  SMLoc loc = parser.getCurrentLocation();
367  if (parseCommonStructuredOpParts(parser, result, inputTypes, outputTypes))
368  return failure();
369 
370  // Parse optional attributes.
371  if (parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes))
372  return failure();
373 
374  // TODO: consider merging results parsing into region parsing.
375  // Need to wait for declarative assembly resolution to decide.
376  SmallVector<Type, 1> outputTensorsTypes;
377  if (parseNamedStructuredOpResults(parser, outputTensorsTypes))
378  return failure();
379  result.addTypes(outputTensorsTypes);
380 
381  std::unique_ptr<Region> region = std::make_unique<Region>();
382  if (parseNamedStructuredOpRegion(parser, *region, numRegionArgs, inputTypes,
383  outputTypes, result.attributes.getAttrs(),
384  regionBuilder, loc))
385  return failure();
386  result.addRegion(std::move(region));
387 
388  return success();
389 }
390 
391 static void printNamedStructuredOpResults(OpAsmPrinter &p,
392  TypeRange resultTypes) {
393  if (resultTypes.empty())
394  return;
395  p.printOptionalArrowTypeList(resultTypes);
396 }
397 
398 static void printNamedStructuredOp(OpAsmPrinter &p, Operation *op,
399  ValueRange inputs, ValueRange outputs,
400  ArrayRef<StringRef> elidedAttrs = {}) {
401  p.printOptionalAttrDict(op->getAttrs(), elidedAttrs);
402 
403  // Printing is shared with generic ops, except for the region and
404  // attributes.
405  printCommonStructuredOpParts(p, inputs, outputs);
406 
407  // Results printing.
408  printNamedStructuredOpResults(p, op->getResultTypes());
409 
410  // Region is elided.
411 }
412 
413 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
414 // Region builder helper.
415 // TODO: Move this to a utility library.
416 // The public methods on this class are referenced directly from generated code.
417 // Helper build the unary, binary, and type conversion functions defined by the
418 // DSL. See LinalgNamedStructuredOps.yamlgen.cpp.inc for the code that uses this
419 // class.
420 //
421 // Implementations of the math functions must be polymorphic over numeric types,
422 // internally performing necessary casts. If the function application makes no
423 // sense, then the only recourse is to assert and return nullptr. This can be
424 // extended later if it becomes possible to fail construction of the region. The
425 // invariant should be enforced at a higher level.
426 //
427 // TODO: These helpers are currently type polymorphic over the class of integer
428 // and floating point types, but they will not internally cast within bit
429 // widths of a class (mixed precision such as i8->i32) or across classes
430 // (i.e. mixed float and integer). Many such combinations are ambiguous or need
431 // to be handled with care and work is being considered to extend the op
432 // language to make such cases explicit. In the mean-time, violating this will
433 // fail verification, which is deemed acceptable.
434 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
435 
436 namespace {
437 
438 class RegionBuilderHelper {
439 public:
440  RegionBuilderHelper(OpBuilder &builder, Block &block)
441  : builder(builder), block(block) {}
442 
443  // Build the unary functions defined by OpDSL.
444  Value buildUnaryFn(UnaryFn unaryFn, Value arg,
445  function_ref<InFlightDiagnostic()> emitError = {}) {
446  if (!isFloatingPoint(arg)) {
447  if (emitError) {
448  emitError() << "unsupported non numeric type";
449  return nullptr;
450  }
451  llvm_unreachable("unsupported non numeric type");
452  }
453  OpBuilder::InsertionGuard g(builder);
454  builder.setInsertionPointToEnd(&block);
455  switch (unaryFn) {
456  case UnaryFn::exp:
457  return math::ExpOp::create(builder, arg.getLoc(), arg);
458  case UnaryFn::log:
459  return math::LogOp::create(builder, arg.getLoc(), arg);
460  case UnaryFn::abs:
461  return math::AbsFOp::create(builder, arg.getLoc(), arg);
462  case UnaryFn::ceil:
463  return math::CeilOp::create(builder, arg.getLoc(), arg);
464  case UnaryFn::floor:
465  return math::FloorOp::create(builder, arg.getLoc(), arg);
466  case UnaryFn::negf:
467  return arith::NegFOp::create(builder, arg.getLoc(), arg);
468  case UnaryFn::reciprocal: {
469  Attribute oneAttr = builder.getOneAttr(arg.getType());
470  auto one = arith::ConstantOp::create(builder, arg.getLoc(),
471  ::cast<TypedAttr>(oneAttr));
472  return arith::DivFOp::create(builder, arg.getLoc(), one, arg);
473  }
474  case UnaryFn::round:
475  return math::RoundOp::create(builder, arg.getLoc(), arg);
476  case UnaryFn::sqrt:
477  return math::SqrtOp::create(builder, arg.getLoc(), arg);
478  case UnaryFn::rsqrt:
479  return math::RsqrtOp::create(builder, arg.getLoc(), arg);
480  case UnaryFn::square:
481  return arith::MulFOp::create(builder, arg.getLoc(), arg, arg);
482  case UnaryFn::tanh:
483  return math::TanhOp::create(builder, arg.getLoc(), arg);
484  case UnaryFn::erf:
485  return math::ErfOp::create(builder, arg.getLoc(), arg);
486  }
487  if (emitError) {
488  emitError() << "unsupported unary function";
489  return nullptr;
490  }
491  llvm_unreachable("unsupported unary function");
492  }
493 
494  // Build the binary functions defined by OpDSL.
495  // If emitError is provided, an error will be emitted if the operation is not
496  // supported and a nullptr will be returned, otherwise an assertion will be
497  // raised.
498  Value buildBinaryFn(BinaryFn binaryFn, Value arg0, Value arg1,
499  function_ref<InFlightDiagnostic()> emitError = {}) {
500  bool allComplex = isComplex(arg0) && isComplex(arg1);
501  bool allFloatingPoint = isFloatingPoint(arg0) && isFloatingPoint(arg1);
502  bool allInteger = isInteger(arg0) && isInteger(arg1);
503  bool allBool = allInteger && arg0.getType().getIntOrFloatBitWidth() == 1 &&
504  arg1.getType().getIntOrFloatBitWidth() == 1;
505  if (!allComplex && !allFloatingPoint && !allInteger) {
506  if (emitError) {
507  emitError()
508  << "Cannot build binary Linalg operation: expects allComplex, "
509  "allFloatingPoint, or allInteger, got "
510  << arg0.getType() << " and " << arg1.getType();
511  return nullptr;
512  }
513  llvm_unreachable("unsupported non numeric type");
514  }
515  OpBuilder::InsertionGuard g(builder);
516  builder.setInsertionPointToEnd(&block);
517  switch (binaryFn) {
518  case BinaryFn::add:
519  if (allComplex)
520  return complex::AddOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
521  if (allFloatingPoint)
522  return arith::AddFOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
523  if (allBool)
524  return arith::OrIOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
525  return arith::AddIOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
526  case BinaryFn::sub:
527  if (allComplex)
528  return complex::SubOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
529  if (allFloatingPoint)
530  return arith::SubFOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
531  if (allBool) {
532  if (emitError) {
533  emitError() << "unsupported operation: sub with bools";
534  return nullptr;
535  }
536  llvm_unreachable("unsupported operation: sub with bools");
537  }
538  return arith::SubIOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
539  case BinaryFn::mul:
540  if (allComplex)
541  return complex::MulOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
542  if (allFloatingPoint)
543  return arith::MulFOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
544  if (allBool)
545  return arith::AndIOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
546  return arith::MulIOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
547  case BinaryFn::div:
548  if (allComplex)
549  return complex::DivOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
550  if (allFloatingPoint)
551  return arith::DivFOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
552  if (allBool) {
553  if (emitError) {
554  emitError() << "unsupported operation: div with bools";
555  return nullptr;
556  }
557  llvm_unreachable("unsupported operation: div with bools");
558  }
559  return arith::DivSIOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
560  case BinaryFn::div_unsigned:
561  if (!allInteger || allBool) {
562  if (emitError) {
563  emitError() << "unsupported operation: unsigned div not on uint";
564  return nullptr;
565  }
566  llvm_unreachable("unsupported operation: unsigned div not on uint");
567  }
568  return arith::DivUIOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
569  case BinaryFn::max_signed:
570  assert(!allComplex);
571  if (allFloatingPoint)
572  return arith::MaximumFOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
573  return arith::MaxSIOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
574  case BinaryFn::min_signed:
575  assert(!allComplex);
576  if (allFloatingPoint)
577  return arith::MinimumFOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
578  return arith::MinSIOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
579  case BinaryFn::max_unsigned:
580  assert(!allComplex);
581  if (allFloatingPoint)
582  return arith::MaximumFOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
583  return arith::MaxUIOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
584  case BinaryFn::min_unsigned:
585  assert(!allComplex);
586  if (allFloatingPoint)
587  return arith::MinimumFOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
588  return arith::MinUIOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
589  case BinaryFn::powf:
590  assert(allFloatingPoint);
591  return math::PowFOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1);
592  }
593  if (emitError) {
594  emitError() << "unsupported binary function";
595  return nullptr;
596  }
597  llvm_unreachable("unsupported binary function");
598  }
599 
600  // Build the ternary functions defined by OpDSL.
601  Value buildTernaryFn(TernaryFn ternaryFn, Value arg0, Value arg1, Value arg2,
602  function_ref<InFlightDiagnostic()> emitError = {}) {
603  bool headBool =
604  isInteger(arg0) && arg0.getType().getIntOrFloatBitWidth() == 1;
605  bool tailFloatingPoint =
606  isFloatingPoint(arg0) && isFloatingPoint(arg1) && isFloatingPoint(arg2);
607  bool tailInteger = isInteger(arg0) && isInteger(arg1) && isInteger(arg2);
608  OpBuilder::InsertionGuard g(builder);
609  builder.setInsertionPointToEnd(&block);
610  switch (ternaryFn) {
611  case TernaryFn::select:
612  if (!headBool && !(tailFloatingPoint || tailInteger))
613  llvm_unreachable("unsupported non numeric type");
614  return arith::SelectOp::create(builder, arg0.getLoc(), arg0, arg1, arg2);
615  }
616  if (emitError) {
617  emitError() << "unsupported ternary function";
618  return nullptr;
619  }
620  llvm_unreachable("unsupported ternary function");
621  }
622 
623  // Build the type functions defined by OpDSL.
624  Value buildTypeFn(TypeFn typeFn, Type toType, Value operand,
625  function_ref<InFlightDiagnostic()> emitError = {}) {
626  switch (typeFn) {
627  case TypeFn::cast_signed:
628  return cast(toType, operand, false);
629  case TypeFn::cast_unsigned:
630  return cast(toType, operand, true);
631  }
632  if (emitError) {
633  emitError() << "unsupported type conversion function";
634  return nullptr;
635  }
636  llvm_unreachable("unsupported type conversion function");
637  }
638 
639  void yieldOutputs(ValueRange values) {
640  OpBuilder::InsertionGuard g(builder);
641  builder.setInsertionPointToEnd(&block);
642  Location loc = builder.getUnknownLoc();
643  YieldOp::create(builder, loc, values);
644  }
645 
646  Value constant(const std::string &value) {
647  OpBuilder::InsertionGuard g(builder);
648  builder.setInsertionPointToEnd(&block);
649  Location loc = builder.getUnknownLoc();
650  Attribute valueAttr = parseAttribute(value, builder.getContext());
651  return arith::ConstantOp::create(builder, loc,
652  ::cast<TypedAttr>(valueAttr));
653  }
654 
655  Value index(int64_t dim) {
656  OpBuilder::InsertionGuard g(builder);
657  builder.setInsertionPointToEnd(&block);
658  return IndexOp::create(builder, builder.getUnknownLoc(), dim);
659  }
660 
661  Type getIntegerType(unsigned width) {
662  return IntegerType::get(builder.getContext(), width);
663  }
664 
665  Type getFloat32Type() { return Float32Type::get(builder.getContext()); }
666  Type getFloat64Type() { return Float64Type::get(builder.getContext()); }
667 
668 private:
669  // Generates operations to cast the given operand to a specified type.
670  // If the cast cannot be performed, a warning will be issued and the
671  // operand returned as-is (which will presumably yield a verification
672  // issue downstream).
673  Value cast(Type toType, Value operand, bool isUnsignedCast) {
674  OpBuilder::InsertionGuard g(builder);
675  builder.setInsertionPointToEnd(&block);
676  auto loc = operand.getLoc();
677  if (isa<UnknownLoc>(loc)) {
678  if (operand.getDefiningOp())
679  loc = operand.getDefiningOp()->getLoc();
680  else if (operand.getParentBlock() &&
681  operand.getParentBlock()->getParentOp())
682  loc = operand.getParentBlock()->getParentOp()->getLoc();
683  }
684  return convertScalarToDtype(builder, loc, operand, toType, isUnsignedCast);
685  }
686 
687  bool isComplex(Value value) {
688  return llvm::isa<ComplexType>(value.getType());
689  }
690  bool isFloatingPoint(Value value) {
691  return llvm::isa<FloatType>(value.getType());
692  }
693  bool isInteger(Value value) {
694  return llvm::isa<IntegerType>(value.getType());
695  }
696 
697  OpBuilder &builder;
698  Block &block;
699 };
700 
701 } // namespace
702

704 // CopyOp
705 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

709 struct EraseSelfCopy : OpRewritePattern<CopyOp> {
710  using OpRewritePattern<CopyOp>::OpRewritePattern;
711  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(CopyOp copyOp,
712  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
713  if (copyOp.getInputs() != copyOp.getOutputs())
714  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(copyOp, "not a self copy");
715  if (copyOp.hasPureBufferSemantics())
716  rewriter.eraseOp(copyOp);
717  else
718  rewriter.replaceOp(copyOp, copyOp.getInputs());
719 
720  return success();
721  }
722 };
723 
724 } // namespace
725 
726 void CopyOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
727  MLIRContext *context) {
728  results.add<EraseSelfCopy>(context);
729 }

737 /// Fold linalg.fill -> tensor.expand/collapse_shape chain.
738 ///
739 /// For such op chains, we can create new linalg.fill ops with the result
740 /// type of the tensor.expand/collapse_shape op.
741 template <typename TensorReshapeOp>
742 struct FoldFillWithTensorReshape : OpRewritePattern<TensorReshapeOp> {
743  using OpRewritePattern<TensorReshapeOp>::OpRewritePattern;
744  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(TensorReshapeOp reshapeOp,
745  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
746  auto oldFill = reshapeOp.getSrc().template getDefiningOp<FillOp>();
747  if (!oldFill)
748  return failure();
749 
750  Location loc = oldFill.getLoc();
751  TensorReshapeOp newInit;
752  if constexpr (std::is_same<TensorReshapeOp, tensor::ExpandShapeOp>::value) {
753 
754  newInit = TensorReshapeOp::create(
755  rewriter, loc, reshapeOp.getResultType(), oldFill.output(),
756  reshapeOp.getReassociation(), reshapeOp.getOutputShape(),
757  reshapeOp.getStaticOutputShape());
758  } else {
759  newInit = TensorReshapeOp::create(
760  rewriter, loc, reshapeOp.getResultType(), oldFill.output(),
761  reshapeOp.getReassociation());
762  }
763  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<FillOp>(reshapeOp, ValueRange{oldFill.value()},
764  ValueRange{newInit});
765  return success();
766  }
767 };
768 
769 /// Fold tensor.pad(linalg.fill) into linalg.fill if the padding value and the
770 /// filling value are the same.
771 struct FoldFillWithPad final : public OpRewritePattern<tensor::PadOp> {
772  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
773 
774  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(tensor::PadOp padOp,
775  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
776  auto fillOp = padOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<linalg::FillOp>();
777  if (!fillOp)
778  return failure();
779 
780  // We can only fold if the padding value is the same as the original
781  // filling value.
782  Value padValue = padOp.getConstantPaddingValue();
783  if (!padValue || fillOp.value() != padValue)
784  return failure();
785 
786  ReifiedRankedShapedTypeDims reifiedShape;
787  if (failed(reifyResultShapes(rewriter, padOp, reifiedShape)))
788  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
789  padOp, "failed to reify tensor.pad op result shape");
790 
791  auto emptyTensor =
792  tensor::EmptyOp::create(rewriter, padOp.getLoc(), reifiedShape.front(),
793  padOp.getResultType().getElementType());
794  Value replacement =
795  FillOp::create(rewriter, fillOp.getLoc(), ValueRange{padValue},
796  ValueRange{emptyTensor})
797  .getResult(0);
798  if (replacement.getType() != padOp.getResultType()) {
799  replacement = tensor::CastOp::create(rewriter, fillOp.getLoc(),
800  padOp.getResultType(), replacement);
801  }
802  rewriter.replaceOp(padOp, replacement);
803  return success();
804  }
805 };
806 
807 /// Fold tensor.insert_slice(tensor.pad(<input>), linalg.fill) into
808 /// tensor.insert_slice(<input>, linalg.fill) if the padding value and the
809 /// filling value are the same.
810 struct FoldInsertPadIntoFill : public OpRewritePattern<tensor::InsertSliceOp> {
811  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
812 
813  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(tensor::InsertSliceOp insertOp,
814  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
815  auto srcPadOp = insertOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<tensor::PadOp>();
816  if (!srcPadOp)
817  return failure();
818 
819  if (insertOp.getType().getRank() != insertOp.getSourceType().getRank())
820  return failure();
821 
822  // Walk back the tensor.insert_slice chain and find the first destination
823  // value at the start of the chain.
824  Value firstDest = insertOp.getDest();
825  while (auto prevOp = firstDest.getDefiningOp<tensor::InsertSliceOp>()) {
826  if (prevOp.getType().getRank() != prevOp.getSourceType().getRank())
827  return failure();
828 
829  // Make sure the range of values accessed are disjoint. Without this, we
830  // cannot fold tensor.pad away.
831  bool disjoint = false;
832  for (int i = 0, e = prevOp.getType().getRank(); i < e; ++i) {
833  // If the dimension has dynamic offset/size, we cannot guarantee
834  // disjoint. So just skip it.
835  if (insertOp.isDynamicOffset(i) || insertOp.isDynamicSize(i) ||
836  insertOp.isDynamicStride(i) || prevOp.isDynamicOffset(i) ||
837  prevOp.isDynamicSize(i) || prevOp.isDynamicStride(i))
838  continue;
839 
840  // Get the range start and end, inclusively for both.
841  int64_t prevStart = prevOp.getStaticOffset(i);
842  int64_t prevEnd = prevStart + (prevOp.getStaticSize(i) - 1) *
843  prevOp.getStaticStride(i);
844  int64_t nextStart = insertOp.getStaticOffset(i);
845  int64_t nextEnd = nextStart + (insertOp.getStaticSize(i) - 1) *
846  insertOp.getStaticStride(i);
847  if (prevEnd < nextStart || nextEnd < prevStart) {
848  disjoint = true;
849  break;
850  }
851  }
852 
853  if (!disjoint)
854  break;
855  firstDest = prevOp.getDest();
856  }
857 
858  // Check whether the first destination is a fill op. For overlapped cases,
859  // this also cannot be true.
860  auto dstFillOp = firstDest.getDefiningOp<linalg::FillOp>();
861  if (!dstFillOp)
862  return failure();
863 
864  // We can only fold if the padding value is the same as the original
865  // filling value.
866  Value padValue = srcPadOp.getConstantPaddingValue();
867  if (!padValue || dstFillOp.value() != padValue)
868  return failure();
869 
870  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> lowPads = srcPadOp.getMixedLowPad();
871  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> oldOffsets = insertOp.getMixedOffsets();
872 
873  Location loc = insertOp.getLoc();
874  MLIRContext *context = getContext();
875 
876  AffineExpr sym0, sym1;
877  bindSymbols(context, sym0, sym1);
878  auto addMap = AffineMap::get(0, 2, {sym0 + sym1}, context);
879 
880  // Calculate the new offsets for the insert. It should be the old offsets
881  // plus low padding sizes.
882  SmallVector<OpFoldResult, 4> newOffsets;
883  for (const auto &p : llvm::zip(lowPads, oldOffsets)) {
884  newOffsets.push_back(affine::makeComposedFoldedAffineApply(
885  rewriter, loc, addMap, {std::get<0>(p), std::get<1>(p)}));
886  }
887 
888  RankedTensorType srcPadType = srcPadOp.getSourceType();
889  SmallVector<OpFoldResult, 4> newSizes;
890  for (int i = 0, e = srcPadType.getRank(); i < e; ++i) {
891  if (srcPadType.isDynamicDim(i)) {
892  newSizes.push_back(
893  tensor::DimOp::create(rewriter, loc, srcPadOp.getSource(), i)
894  .getResult());
895  } else {
896  newSizes.push_back(rewriter.getIndexAttr(srcPadType.getDimSize(i)));
897  }
898  }
899 
900  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<tensor::InsertSliceOp>(
901  insertOp, srcPadOp.getSource(), insertOp.getDest(), newOffsets,
902  newSizes, insertOp.getMixedStrides());
903  return success();
904  }
905 };
906 
907 /// Fold tensor.extract(linalg.fill(<input>)) into <input>
908 struct FoldFillWithTensorExtract : public OpRewritePattern<tensor::ExtractOp> {
909 public:
910  using OpRewritePattern<tensor::ExtractOp>::OpRewritePattern;
911 
912  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(tensor::ExtractOp extractOp,
913  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
914  // See if tensor input of tensor.extract op is the result of a linalg.fill
915  // op.
916  auto fillOp = extractOp.getTensor().getDefiningOp<linalg::FillOp>();
917  if (!fillOp)
918  return failure();
919 
920  // Get scalar input operand of linalg.fill op.
921  Value extractedScalar = fillOp.getInputs()[0];
922 
923  // Replace tensor.extract op with scalar value used to fill the tensor.
924  rewriter.replaceOp(extractOp, extractedScalar);
925  return success();
926  }
927 };
928 
929 /// Folds pack(fill) into a single fill op if
930 /// 1. The pack op does not have padding value, or
931 /// 2. The filled value and padding value are the same.
932 static FailureOr<FillOp> foldFillPackIntoFillOp(RewriterBase &rewriter,
933  linalg::PackOp packOp) {
934  auto fillOp = packOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<FillOp>();
935  if (!fillOp)
936  return failure();
937 
938  if (auto paddingValue = packOp.getPaddingValue())
939  if (!isEqualConstantIntOrValue(paddingValue, fillOp.value()))
940  return failure();
941 
942  Value packOpDest = packOp.getDest();
943  if (!packOpDest.hasOneUse())
944  return failure();
945 
946  return linalg::FillOp::create(rewriter, packOp.getLoc(), fillOp.getInputs(),
947  packOp.getDest());
948 }
949 
950 /// Wrapper pattern that applies foldFillPackIntoFillOp method.
951 struct FoldFillWithPack : public OpRewritePattern<linalg::PackOp> {
952 public:
953  FoldFillWithPack(MLIRContext *context)
954  : OpRewritePattern<linalg::PackOp>(context) {}
955 
956  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(linalg::PackOp packOp,
957  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
958  auto fillOp = foldFillPackIntoFillOp(rewriter, packOp);
959  if (failed(fillOp))
960  return failure();
961  rewriter.replaceOp(packOp, fillOp.value().result());
962  return success();
963  }
964 };
965 
966 /// Fold fill with copy.
967 struct FoldFillWithCopy : OpRewritePattern<linalg::CopyOp> {
968  using OpRewritePattern<linalg::CopyOp>::OpRewritePattern;
969 
970  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(linalg::CopyOp copyOp,
971  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
972  if (auto fillOp = copyOp.getInputs().front().getDefiningOp<FillOp>()) {
973  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<FillOp>(copyOp, copyOp.getResultTypes(),
974  fillOp.getInputs(),
975  copyOp.getOutputs());
976  return success();
977  }
978  if (auto fillOp = copyOp.getOutputs().front().getDefiningOp<FillOp>()) {
979  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<linalg::CopyOp>(copyOp, copyOp.getInputs(),
980  fillOp.getOutputs());
981  return success();
982  }
983  return failure();
984  }
985 };
986 
987 /// Fold fill with transpose.
988 struct FoldFillWithTranspose : OpRewritePattern<linalg::TransposeOp> {
989  using OpRewritePattern<linalg::TransposeOp>::OpRewritePattern;
990 
991  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(linalg::TransposeOp transposeOp,
992  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
993  if (auto fillOp = transposeOp.getInput().getDefiningOp<FillOp>()) {
994  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<FillOp>(
995  transposeOp, transposeOp.getResultTypes(), fillOp.getInputs(),
996  transposeOp.getDpsInitOperand(0)->get());
997  return success();
998  }
999  return failure();
1000  }
1001 };
1002 
1003 /// Fold a concat with all elements being fills of the same value
1004 /// into a fill of the concat result shape.
1005 struct FoldConcatsOfFill : public OpRewritePattern<tensor::ConcatOp> {
1006  using OpRewritePattern::OpRewritePattern;
1007 
1008  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(tensor::ConcatOp concatOp,
1009  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
1010  auto concatOperands = concatOp.getInputs();
1011  if (concatOperands.empty()) {
1012  return failure();
1013  }
1014 
1015  auto firstFillOp = concatOperands.front().getDefiningOp<linalg::FillOp>();
1016  if (!firstFillOp) {
1017  return failure();
1018  }
1019  // Prefetch the fill value.
1020  OpFoldResult firstFillVal =
1021  getAsOpFoldResult(firstFillOp.getDpsInputOperand(0)->get());
1022  // Collect all the outs values for the fill operations.
1023  SmallVector<Value> allOuts;
1024  allOuts.push_back(firstFillOp.getDpsInitOperand(0)->get());
1025 
1026  auto isDefinedByCompatibleFillOp = [&](Value v) -> bool {
1027  auto fillOp = v.getDefiningOp<linalg::FillOp>();
1028  if (!fillOp) {
1029  return false;
1030  }
1031 
1032  OpFoldResult fillVal =
1033  getAsOpFoldResult(fillOp.getDpsInputOperand(0)->get());
1034  if (fillVal != firstFillVal)
1035  return false;
1036 
1037  allOuts.push_back(fillOp.getDpsInitOperand(0)->get());
1038  return true;
1039  };
1040  if (!llvm::all_of(concatOperands.drop_front(),
1041  isDefinedByCompatibleFillOp)) {
1042  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
1043  concatOp, "not all operands are defined by a compatible fill op");
1044  }
1045 
1046  Value outsConcat = tensor::ConcatOp::create(rewriter, concatOp.getLoc(),
1047  concatOp.getDim(), allOuts);
1048  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<linalg::FillOp>(
1049  concatOp, firstFillOp.getDpsInputOperand(0)->get(), outsConcat);
1050  return success();
1051  }
1052 };
1053 
1054 } // namespace
1055 
1056 void FillOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
1057  MLIRContext *context) {
1058  results.add<FoldConcatsOfFill, FoldFillWithCopy, FoldFillWithTensorExtract,
1059  FoldFillWithPack, FoldFillWithPad,
1060  FoldFillWithTensorReshape<tensor::CollapseShapeOp>,
1061  FoldFillWithTensorReshape<tensor::ExpandShapeOp>,
1062  FoldInsertPadIntoFill, FoldFillWithTranspose>(context);
1063 }

1068 
1069 static void buildGenericRegion(
1070  OpBuilder &builder, Location loc, Region &region, ValueRange inputs,
1071  ValueRange outputs,
1072  function_ref<void(OpBuilder &, Location, ValueRange)> bodyBuild) {
1073  SmallVector<Type, 4> blockArgTypes;
1074  SmallVector<Location, 4> blockArgLocs;
1075  for (ValueRange container : {inputs, outputs}) {
1076  for (Value v : container) {
1077  Type t = v.getType();
1078  blockArgTypes.push_back(
1079  isa<MemRefType, RankedTensorType>(t) ? getElementTypeOrSelf(t) : t);
1080  blockArgLocs.push_back(v.getLoc());
1081  }
1082  }
1083 
1084  OpBuilder::InsertionGuard guard(builder);
1085  Block *bodyBlock =
1086  builder.createBlock(&region, region.end(), blockArgTypes, blockArgLocs);
1087  bodyBuild(builder, loc, bodyBlock->getArguments());
1088 }
1089 
1090 void GenericOp::getAsmBlockArgumentNames(Region &region,
1091  OpAsmSetValueNameFn setNameFn) {
1092  for (Value v : getRegionInputArgs())
1093  setNameFn(v, "in");
1094  for (Value v : getRegionOutputArgs())
1095  setNameFn(v, "out");
1096 }

1098 void GenericOp::build(
1099  OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result, TypeRange resultTensorTypes,
1100  ValueRange inputs, ValueRange outputs, ArrayAttr indexingMaps,
1101  ArrayAttr iteratorTypes, StringAttr doc, StringAttr libraryCall,
1102  function_ref<void(OpBuilder &, Location, ValueRange)> bodyBuild,
1103  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attributes) {
1104  build(builder, result, resultTensorTypes, inputs, outputs, indexingMaps,
1105  iteratorTypes, doc, libraryCall);
1106  result.addAttributes(attributes);
1107  if (bodyBuild)
1108  buildGenericRegion(builder, result.location, *result.regions.front(),
1109  inputs, outputs, bodyBuild);
1110 }

1112 void GenericOp::build(

1114  ValueRange inputs, ValueRange outputs, ArrayRef<AffineMap> indexingMaps,
1115  ArrayRef<utils::IteratorType> iteratorTypes, StringRef doc,
1116  StringRef libraryCall,
1117  function_ref<void(OpBuilder &, Location, ValueRange)> bodyBuild,
1118  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attributes) {
1119  build(builder, result, resultTensorTypes, inputs, outputs,
1120  builder.getAffineMapArrayAttr(indexingMaps),
1121  builder.getArrayAttr(llvm::to_vector(llvm::map_range(
1122  iteratorTypes,
1123  [&](utils::IteratorType iter) -> mlir::Attribute {
1124  return IteratorTypeAttr::get(builder.getContext(), iter);
1125  }))),
1126  doc.empty() ? StringAttr() : builder.getStringAttr(doc),
1127  libraryCall.empty() ? StringAttr() : builder.getStringAttr(libraryCall),
1128  bodyBuild, attributes);
1129 }

1165 void GenericOp::print(OpAsmPrinter &p) {
1166  p << " ";
1167 
1168  // Print extra attributes.
1169  auto genericAttrNames = linalgTraitAttrNames();
1170 
1171  llvm::StringSet<> genericAttrNamesSet;
1172  genericAttrNamesSet.insert_range(genericAttrNames);
1173  SmallVector<NamedAttribute, 8> genericAttrs;
1174  for (auto attr : (*this)->getAttrs()) {
1175  if (attr.getName() == getIteratorTypesAttrName()) {
1176  auto iteratorTypes =
1177  llvm::cast<ArrayAttr>(attr.getValue())
1178  .getAsValueRange<IteratorTypeAttr, utils::IteratorType>();
1179  // Convert IteratorType enums into the string representation. This is
1180  // needed, because tests still use the old format when 'iterator_types'
1181  // attribute is represented as an array of strings.
1182  // TODO: Remove this conversion once tests are fixed.
1183  SmallVector<Attribute> iteratorTypeNames =
1184  llvm::to_vector(llvm::map_range(
1185  iteratorTypes, [&](utils::IteratorType t) -> Attribute {
1186  return StringAttr::get(getContext(), stringifyIteratorType(t));
1187  }));
1188 
1189  genericAttrs.emplace_back(
1190  getIteratorTypesAttrName(),
1191  ArrayAttr::get(getContext(), iteratorTypeNames));
1192  } else if (genericAttrNamesSet.count(attr.getName().strref()) > 0) {
1193  genericAttrs.push_back(attr);
1194  }
1195  }
1196  if (!genericAttrs.empty()) {
1197  auto genericDictAttr = DictionaryAttr::get(getContext(), genericAttrs);
1198  p << genericDictAttr;
1199  }
1200 
1201  // Printing is shared with named ops, except for the region and attributes
1202  printCommonStructuredOpParts(p, getDpsInputs(), getDpsInits());
1203 
1204  genericAttrNames.push_back("operandSegmentSizes");
1205  genericAttrNamesSet.insert(genericAttrNames.back());
1206 
1207  bool hasExtraAttrs = false;
1208  for (NamedAttribute n : (*this)->getAttrs()) {
1209  if ((hasExtraAttrs = !genericAttrNamesSet.contains(n.getName().strref())))
1210  break;
1211  }
1212  if (hasExtraAttrs) {
1213  p << " attrs = ";
1214  p.printOptionalAttrDict((*this)->getAttrs(),
1215  /*elidedAttrs=*/genericAttrNames);
1216  }
1217 
1218  // Print region.
1219  if (!getRegion().empty()) {
1220  p << ' ';
1221  p.printRegion(getRegion());
1222  }
1223 
1224  // Print results.
1225  printNamedStructuredOpResults(p, getResultTensors().getTypes());
1226 }
1227 
1228 ParseResult GenericOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
1229  DictionaryAttr dictAttr;
1230  // Parse the core linalg traits that must check into a dictAttr.
1231  // The name is unimportant as we will overwrite result.attributes.
1232  // The core linalg traits must contain the information necessary to pass the
1233  // verifier.
1234  llvm::SMLoc attributeLocation = parser.getCurrentLocation();
1235  if (parser.parseAttribute(dictAttr, "_", result.attributes))
1236  return failure();
1237  result.attributes.assign(dictAttr.getValue().begin(),
1238  dictAttr.getValue().end());
1239 
1240  // Convert array of string into an array of IteratorType enums. This is
1241  // needed, because tests still use the old format when 'iterator_types'
1242  // attribute is represented as an array of strings.
1243  // TODO: Remove this conversion once tests are fixed.
1244  auto iteratorTypes = dyn_cast_or_null<ArrayAttr>(
1245  result.attributes.get(getIteratorTypesAttrName(result.name)));
1246  if (!iteratorTypes) {
1247  return parser.emitError(attributeLocation)
1248  << "expected " << getIteratorTypesAttrName(result.name)
1249  << " array attribute";
1250  }
1251 
1252  SmallVector<Attribute> iteratorTypeAttrs;
1253 
1254  for (StringRef s : iteratorTypes.getAsValueRange<StringAttr>()) {
1255  auto maybeIteratorType = utils::symbolizeIteratorType(s);
1256  if (!maybeIteratorType.has_value())
1257  return parser.emitError(parser.getCurrentLocation())
1258  << "unexpected iterator_type (" << s << ")";
1259 
1260  iteratorTypeAttrs.push_back(
1261  IteratorTypeAttr::get(parser.getContext(), maybeIteratorType.value()));
1262  }
1263  result.attributes.set(getIteratorTypesAttrName(result.name),
1264  parser.getBuilder().getArrayAttr(iteratorTypeAttrs));
1265 
1266  // Parsing is shared with named ops, except for the region.
1267  SmallVector<Type, 1> inputTypes, outputTypes;
1268  if (parseCommonStructuredOpParts(parser, result, inputTypes, outputTypes))
1269  return failure();
1270 
1271  // Optional attributes may be added.
1272  if (succeeded(parser.parseOptionalKeyword("attrs")))
1273  if (failed(parser.parseEqual()) ||
1274  failed(parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes)))
1275  return failure();
1276 
1277  std::unique_ptr<Region> region = std::make_unique<Region>();
1278  if (parser.parseRegion(*region, {}))
1279  return failure();
1280  result.addRegion(std::move(region));
1281 
1282  // Generic ops may specify that a subset of its outputs are tensors. Such
1283  // outputs are specified in the result type.
1284  // TODO: may need to move output parsing before region parsing.
1285  // Need to wait for declarative assembly resolution to decide.
1286  SmallVector<Type, 1> outputTensorsTypes;
1287  if (parseNamedStructuredOpResults(parser, outputTensorsTypes))
1288  return failure();
1289  result.addTypes(outputTensorsTypes);
1290 
1291  return success();
1292 }
1293 
1294 static void getGenericEffectsImpl(
1295  SmallVectorImpl<SideEffects::EffectInstance<MemoryEffects::Effect>>
1296  &effects,
1297  LinalgOp linalgOp) {
1298  for (auto [index, operand] : llvm::enumerate(linalgOp.getDpsInputs())) {
1299  if (!llvm::isa<MemRefType>(operand.getType()))
1300  continue;
1301  effects.emplace_back(
1302  MemoryEffects::Read::get(), &linalgOp->getOpOperand(index), /*stage=*/0,
1303  /*effectOnFullRegion=*/true, SideEffects::DefaultResource::get());
1304  }
1305 
1306  for (OpOperand &operand : linalgOp.getDpsInitsMutable()) {
1307  if (!llvm::isa<MemRefType>(operand.get().getType()))
1308  continue;
1309  if (linalgOp.payloadUsesValueFromOperand(&operand)) {
1310  effects.emplace_back(MemoryEffects::Read::get(), &operand, /*stage=*/0,
1311  /*effectOnFullRegion=*/true,
1312  SideEffects::DefaultResource::get());
1313  }
1314  effects.emplace_back(MemoryEffects::Write::get(), &operand, /*stage=*/0,
1315  /*effectOnFullRegion=*/true,
1316  SideEffects::DefaultResource::get());
1317  }
1318 }
1319 
1320 void GenericOp::getEffects(
1321  SmallVectorImpl<SideEffects::EffectInstance<MemoryEffects::Effect>>
1322  &effects) {
1323  getGenericEffectsImpl(effects, cast<LinalgOp>(getOperation()));
1324 }
1325 
1326 static Speculation::Speculatability
1327 getGenericSpeculatabilityImpl(LinalgOp linalgOp) {
1328  // Operands with value semantics are speculatable, while operands with memory
1329  // semantics are not.
1330  if (!linalgOp.hasPureTensorSemantics())
1331  return Speculation::NotSpeculatable;
1332  // The body of the op can still have speculation in its region.
1333  return Speculation::RecursivelySpeculatable;
1334 }
1335 
1336 Speculation::Speculatability GenericOp::getSpeculatability() {
1337  return getGenericSpeculatabilityImpl(cast<LinalgOp>(getOperation()));
1338 }
1339 
1340 LogicalResult GenericOp::verify() { return success(); }
1341 
1342 namespace {
1343 
1344 /// Remove linalg operations that are just copying the values from inputs to
1345 /// results. In the memref case, the operation must be copying to and from the
1346 /// same value. Requirements are:
1347 /// 1) All iterator types are parallel
1348 /// 2) The body contains just a yield operation with the yielded values being
1349 /// the arguments corresponding to the operands.
1350 template <typename OpTy>
1351 struct EraseIdentityLinalgOp : public OpRewritePattern<OpTy> {
1352  using OpRewritePattern<OpTy>::OpRewritePattern;
1353 
1354  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(OpTy linalgOp,
1355  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
1356  // All indexing maps must be equal. It follows that they are permutations.
1357  if (!llvm::all_equal(linalgOp.getIndexingMapsArray()))
1358  return failure();
1359 
1360  // Check that the body of the linalg operation is just a linalg.yield
1361  // operation.
1362  Block &body = linalgOp->getRegion(0).front();
1363  if (!llvm::hasSingleElement(body))
1364  return failure();
1365  auto yieldOp = dyn_cast<linalg::YieldOp>(body.getTerminator());
1366  if (!yieldOp)
1367  return failure();
1368 
1369  // In the buffer case, we need to check exact buffer equality.
1370  if (linalgOp.hasPureBufferSemantics()) {
1371  if (linalgOp.getNumDpsInputs() != 1 || linalgOp.getNumDpsInits() != 1 ||
1372  linalgOp.getDpsInputOperand(0)->get() !=
1373  linalgOp.getDpsInitOperand(0)->get()) {
1374  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
1375  linalgOp, "expected single input and output to be the same value");
1376  }
1377 
1378  auto yieldArg = dyn_cast<BlockArgument>(yieldOp.getOperand(0));
1379  if (!yieldArg || yieldArg.getOwner() != &body) {
1380  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(linalgOp,
1381  "cannot fold fill-like op");
1382  }
1383 
1384  rewriter.eraseOp(linalgOp);
1385  return success();
1386  }
1387 
1388  if (!linalgOp.hasPureTensorSemantics()) {
1389  return rewriter.notifyMatchFailure(
1390  linalgOp, "mixed semantics is not supported yet");
1391  }
1392 
1393  // Get the argument number of the returned values. That is the operand
1394  // number to use for replacing uses of this operation.
1395  SmallVector<Value> returnedArgs;
1396  for (const auto &yieldVal : llvm::enumerate(yieldOp.getValues())) {
1397  auto yieldArg = llvm::dyn_cast<BlockArgument>(yieldVal.value());
1398  if (!yieldArg || yieldArg.getOwner() != &body)
1399  return failure();
1400  unsigned argumentNumber = yieldArg.getArgNumber();
1401  Value returnedArg = linalgOp->getOperand(argumentNumber);
1402  Type resultType = linalgOp->getResult(yieldVal.index()).getType();
1403  // The input can have a different type than the result, e.g. a dynamic
1404  // input dimension can be turned into a static output dimension.
1405  Type returnType = returnedArg.getType();
1406  if (returnType != resultType) {
1407  // Distinguish between sparse conversion or dense tensor casting.
1408  // TODO: unify the two ops?
1409  if (sparse_tensor::getSparseTensorEncoding(returnType) ||
1410  sparse_tensor::getSparseTensorEncoding(resultType))
1411  returnedArg = sparse_tensor::ConvertOp::create(
1412  rewriter, linalgOp.getLoc(), resultType, returnedArg);
1413  else {
1414  if (!tensor::CastOp::areCastCompatible(returnedArg.getType(),
1415  resultType))
1416  return failure();
1417  returnedArg = tensor::CastOp::create(rewriter, linalgOp.getLoc(),
1418  resultType, returnedArg);
1419  }
1420  }
1421  returnedArgs.push_back(returnedArg);
1422  }
1423 
1424  if (returnedArgs.size() != linalgOp->getNumResults())
1425  return failure();
1426  rewriter.replaceOp(linalgOp, returnedArgs);
1427  return success();
1428  }
1429 };
1430 
1431 } // namespace
1432 
1433 void GenericOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
1434  MLIRContext *context) {
1435  results.add<EraseIdentityLinalgOp<GenericOp>>(context);
1436 }

1446 static ParseResult parseDstStyleOp(
1447  OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result,
1448  function_ref<ParseResult(OpAsmParser &, NamedAttrList &)> parseAttrsFn =
1449  nullptr) {
1450  // Parse `ins` and `outs`.
1451  SmallVector<Type, 4> inputTypes, outputTypes;
1452  if (parseCommonStructuredOpParts(parser, result, inputTypes, outputTypes,
1453  /*addOperandSegmentSizes=*/false))
1454  return failure();
1455 
1456  // Add result types.
1457  for (Type outputType : outputTypes) {
1458  if (llvm::isa<RankedTensorType>(outputType))
1459  result.addTypes(outputType);
1460  }
1461 
1462  // Parse required attributes.
1463  if (parseAttrsFn && failed(parseAttrsFn(parser, result.attributes)))
1464  return failure();
1465 
1466  // Parse optional attributes.
1467  if (parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes))
1468  return failure();
1469  return success();
1470 }

1483 void MapOp::build(
1484  OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result, ValueRange inputs, Value init,
1485  function_ref<void(OpBuilder &, Location, ValueRange)> bodyBuild,
1486  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attributes) {
1487  build(builder, result, TypeRange{}, inputs, init);
1488  result.addAttributes(attributes);
1489 
1490  // Add output types for `RankedTensorType` output arguments.
1491  Type initType = init.getType();
1492  if (llvm::isa<RankedTensorType>(initType))
1493  result.addTypes(initType);
1494 
1495  if (bodyBuild)
1496  buildGenericRegion(builder, result.location, *result.regions.front(),
1497  inputs, /*outputs=*/{}, bodyBuild);
1498 }
1499 
1500 static void addBodyWithPayloadOp(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result,
1501  const OperationName &payloadOpName,
1502  const NamedAttrList &payloadOpAttrs,
1503  ArrayRef<Value> operands,
1504  bool initFirst = false) {
1505  OpBuilder b(parser.getContext());
1506  Region *body = result.addRegion();
1507  Block &block = body->emplaceBlock();
1508  b.setInsertionPointToStart(&block);
1509  for (auto &operand : operands) {
1510  block.addArgument(
1511  llvm::cast<ShapedType>(operand.getType()).getElementType(),
1512  b.getUnknownLoc());
1513  }
1514  SmallVector<Value> payloadOpOperands;
1515  // If initFirst flag is enabled, we consider init as the first position of
1516  // payload operands.
1517  if (initFirst) {
1518  payloadOpOperands.push_back(block.getArguments().back());
1519  for (const auto &arg : block.getArguments().drop_back())
1520  payloadOpOperands.push_back(arg);
1521  } else {
1522  payloadOpOperands = {block.getArguments().begin(),
1523  block.getArguments().end()};
1524  }
1525 
1526  Operation *payloadOp = b.create(
1527  result.location, b.getStringAttr(payloadOpName.getStringRef()),
1528  payloadOpOperands,
1529  TypeRange{llvm::cast<ShapedType>(result.operands.back().getType())
1530  .getElementType()},
1531  payloadOpAttrs);
1532  YieldOp::create(b, result.location, payloadOp->getResults());
1533 }
1534 
1535 ParseResult MapOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
1536  std::optional<OperationName> payloadOpName;
1537  NamedAttrList payloadOpAttrs;
1538  if (succeeded(parser.parseOptionalLBrace())) {
1539  FailureOr<OperationName> operationName = parser.parseCustomOperationName();
1540  if (failed(operationName))
1541  return failure();
1542  if (parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(payloadOpAttrs))
1543  return failure();
1544  payloadOpName = operationName.value();
1545  if (parser.parseRBrace())
1546  return failure();
1547  }
1548 
1549  if (parseDstStyleOp(parser, result))
1550  return failure();
1551 
1552  if (payloadOpName.has_value()) {
1553  if (!result.operands.empty())
1554  addBodyWithPayloadOp(parser, result, payloadOpName.value(),
1555  payloadOpAttrs,
1556  ArrayRef(result.operands).drop_back());
1557  else
1558  result.addRegion();
1559  } else {
1560  SmallVector<OpAsmParser::Argument> regionArgs;
1561  if (parser.parseArgumentList(regionArgs, OpAsmParser::Delimiter::Paren,
1562  /*allowType=*/true, /*allowAttrs=*/true)) {
1563  return failure();
1564  }
1565  Region *body = result.addRegion();
1566  if (parser.parseRegion(*body, regionArgs))
1567  return failure();
1568  }
1569  return success();
1570 }
1571 
1572 // Retrieve the operation from the body, if it is the only one (except
1573 // yield) and if it gets the same amount of arguments as the body does.
1574 // If initFirst flag is enabled, we check that init takes the first position in
1575 // operands of payload.
1576 static Operation *findPayloadOp(Block *body, bool initFirst = false) {
1577  if (body->getOperations().size() != 2)
1578  return nullptr;
1579  Operation &payload = body->getOperations().front();
1580  assert(isa<YieldOp>(body->getOperations().back()));
1581 
1582  if (payload.getNumOperands() == 0 ||
1583  payload.getNumOperands() != body->getNumArguments())
1584  return nullptr;
1585  if (initFirst) {
1586  // check init
1587  if (payload.getOperands().back() != body->getArgument(0))
1588  return nullptr;
1589  // check rest
1590  for (const auto &[operand, bbArg] :
1591  llvm::zip(payload.getOperands(), body->getArguments().drop_front())) {
1592  if (bbArg != operand)
1593  return nullptr;
1594  }
1595  } else {
1596  for (const auto &[operand, bbArg] :
1597  llvm::zip(payload.getOperands(), body->getArguments())) {
1598  if (bbArg != operand)
1599  return nullptr;
1600  }
1601  }
1602  return &payload;
1603 }
1604 
1605 void printShortForm(OpAsmPrinter &p, Operation *payloadOp) {
1606  SmallVector<StringRef> elidedAttrs;
1607  std::string attrToElide;
1608  p << " { " << payloadOp->getName().getStringRef();
1609  for (const auto &attr : payloadOp->getAttrs()) {
1610  auto fastAttr =
1611  llvm::dyn_cast<mlir::arith::FastMathFlagsAttr>(attr.getValue());
1612  if (fastAttr && fastAttr.getValue() == mlir::arith::FastMathFlags::none) {
1613  attrToElide = attr.getName().str();
1614  elidedAttrs.push_back(attrToElide);
1615  break;
1616  }
1617  }
1618  p.printOptionalAttrDict(payloadOp->getAttrs(), elidedAttrs);
1619  p << " }";
1620 }
1621 
1622 void MapOp::print(OpAsmPrinter &p) {
1623  Block *mapper = getBody();
1624  Operation *payloadOp = findPayloadOp(mapper);
1625  if (payloadOp) {
1626  printShortForm(p, payloadOp);
1627  }
1628 
1629  printCommonStructuredOpParts(p, getDpsInputs(), getDpsInits());
1630  p.printOptionalAttrDict((*this)->getAttrs());
1631 
1632  if (!payloadOp) {
1633  // Print region if the payload op was not detected.
1634  p.increaseIndent();
1635  p.printNewline();
1636  p << "(";
1637  llvm::interleaveComma(mapper->getArguments(), p,
1638  [&](auto arg) { p.printRegionArgument(arg); });
1639  p << ") ";
1640 
1641  p.printRegion(getMapper(), /*printEntryBlockArgs=*/false);
1642  p.decreaseIndent();
1643  }
1644 }
1645 
1646 LogicalResult MapOp::verify() {
1647  auto *bodyBlock = getBody();
1648  auto blockArgs = bodyBlock->getArguments();
1649 
1650  // Checks if the number of `inputs` match the arity of the `mapper` region.
1651  if (getInputs().size() != blockArgs.size())
1652  return emitOpError() << "expects number of operands to match the arity of "
1653  "mapper, but got: "
1654  << getInputs().size() << " and " << blockArgs.size();
1655 
1656  // The parameters of mapper should all match the element type of inputs.
1657  for (const auto &[bbArgType, inputArg] :
1658  llvm::zip(bodyBlock->getArgumentTypes(), getInputs())) {
1659  auto inputElemType =
1660  llvm::cast<ShapedType>(inputArg.getType()).getElementType();
1661  if (bbArgType != inputElemType) {
1662  return emitOpError() << "expected element type of input " << inputElemType
1663  << " to match bbArg type " << bbArgType;
1664  }
1665  }
1666 
1667  // The shape of each input must match the shape of the output.
1668  auto outputShape = getInit().getType().getShape();
1669  for (Type inputArgType : TypeRange{getInputs()}) {
1670  auto inputElemShape = llvm::cast<ShapedType>(inputArgType).getShape();
1671  if (inputElemShape != outputShape) {
1672  return emitOpError() << "expected shape of input (" << inputElemShape
1673  << ") to match shape of output (" << outputShape
1674  << ")";
1675  }
1676  }
1677 
1678  return success();
1679 }
1680 
1681 SmallVector<utils::IteratorType> MapOp::getIteratorTypesArray() {
1682  int64_t rank = getInit().getType().getRank();
1683  return SmallVector<utils::IteratorType>(rank, utils::IteratorType::parallel);
1684 }

1686 ArrayAttr MapOp::getIndexingMaps() {
1687  Builder builder(getContext());
1688  int64_t rank = getInit().getType().getRank();
1689  int64_t numIndexingMaps = getOperands().size();
1690  return builder.getAffineMapArrayAttr(SmallVector<AffineMap>(
1691  numIndexingMaps, builder.getMultiDimIdentityMap(rank)));
1692 }

1722 void ReduceOp::build(
1723  OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &result, ValueRange inputs,
1724  ValueRange inits, ArrayRef<int64_t> dimensions,
1725  function_ref<void(OpBuilder &, Location, ValueRange)> bodyBuild,
1726  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attributes) {

1742 SmallVector<utils::IteratorType> ReduceOp::getIteratorTypesArray() {
1743  int64_t inputRank =
1744  llvm::cast<ShapedType>(getInputs()[0].getType()).getRank();
1745  SmallVector<utils::IteratorType> iteratorTypes(inputRank,
1746  utils::IteratorType::parallel);

1752 ArrayAttr ReduceOp::getIndexingMaps() {
1753  int64_t inputRank =
1754  llvm::cast<ShapedType>(getInputs()[0].getType()).getRank();
1755  SmallVector<AffineMap> affineMaps(
1756  getNumDpsInputs(),
1757  AffineMap::getMultiDimIdentityMap(inputRank, getContext()));
1758  AffineMap resultMap =
1759  AffineMap::getMultiDimIdentityMap(inputRank, getContext())
1760  .dropResults(getDimensions());
1761  for (int64_t i = 0, e = getNumDpsInits(); i < e; ++i)
1762  affineMaps.push_back(resultMap);
1763  return Builder(getContext()).getAffineMapArrayAttr(affineMaps);
1764 }
1765 
1766 void ReduceOp::getEffects(
1767  SmallVectorImpl<SideEffects::EffectInstance<MemoryEffects::Effect>>
1768  &effects) {
1769  getGenericEffectsImpl(effects, cast<LinalgOp>(getOperation()));
1770 }
1771 
1772 Speculation::Speculatability ReduceOp::getSpeculatability() {
1773  return getGenericSpeculatabilityImpl(cast<LinalgOp>(getOperation()));
1774 }

1776 static ParseResult parseDenseI64ArrayAttr(OpAsmParser &parser,
1777  NamedAttrList &attributes,
1778  StringRef attributeName) {
1779  if (parser.parseKeyword(attributeName) || parser.parseEqual())
1780  return failure();
1781 
1782  attributes.set(attributeName, DenseI64ArrayAttr::parse(parser, Type{}));
1783  return success();
1784 }
1785 
1786 ParseResult ReduceOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
1787  std::optional<OperationName> payloadOpName;
1788  NamedAttrList payloadOpAttrs;
1789  if (succeeded(parser.parseOptionalLBrace())) {
1790  FailureOr<OperationName> operationName = parser.parseCustomOperationName();
1791  if (failed(operationName))
1792  return failure();
1793  if (parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(payloadOpAttrs))
1794  return failure();
1795  payloadOpName = operationName.value();
1796  if (parser.parseRBrace())
1797  return failure();
1798  }
1799 
1800  if (parseDstStyleOp(
1801  parser, result, [&](OpAsmParser &parser, NamedAttrList &attributes) {
1802  return parseDenseI64ArrayAttr(parser, attributes, "dimensions");
1803  }))
1804  return failure();
1805 
1806  if (payloadOpName.has_value()) {
1807  addBodyWithPayloadOp(parser, result, payloadOpName.value(), payloadOpAttrs,
1808  ArrayRef(result.operands), /*initFirst=*/true);
1809  } else {
1810  SmallVector<OpAsmParser::Argument> regionArgs;
1811  if (parser.parseArgumentList(regionArgs, OpAsmParser::Delimiter::Paren,
1812  /*allowType=*/true, /*allowAttrs=*/true)) {
1813  return failure();
1814  }
1815 
1816  Region *body = result.addRegion();
1817  if (parser.parseRegion(*body, regionArgs))
1818  return failure();
1819  }
1820 
1821  return success();
1822 }
1823 
1824 static void printDenseI64ArrayAttr(OpAsmPrinter &p, StringRef attributeName,
1825  ArrayRef<int64_t> attributeValue) {
1826  p << ' ' << attributeName << " = [" << attributeValue << "] ";
1827 }
1828 
1829 void ReduceOp::print(OpAsmPrinter &p) {
1830  Block *mapper = getBody();
1831  Operation *payloadOp = findPayloadOp(mapper, /*initFirst=*/true);
1832  if (payloadOp) {
1833  printShortForm(p, payloadOp);
1834  }
1835 
1836  printCommonStructuredOpParts(p, getDpsInputs(), getDpsInits());
1837  printDenseI64ArrayAttr(p, getDimensionsAttrName(), getDimensions());
1838  p.printOptionalAttrDict((*this)->getAttrs(), {getDimensionsAttrName()});
1839  if (!payloadOp) {
1840  // Print region if the payload op was not detected.
1841  p.increaseIndent();
1842  p.printNewline();
1843  p << "(";
1844  llvm::interleaveComma(mapper->getArguments(), p,
1845  [&](auto arg) { p.printRegionArgument(arg); });
1846  p << ") ";
1847 
1848  p.printRegion(getCombiner(), /*printEntryBlockArgs=*/false);
1849  p.decreaseIndent();
1850  }
1851 }
1852 
1853 LogicalResult ReduceOp::verify() {
1854  ArrayRef<int64_t> dimensionsRef = getDimensions();
1855 
1856  for (int64_t i = 1; i < getNumDpsInputs(); ++i) {
1857  if (llvm::cast<ShapedType>(getInputs()[i].getType()).getShape() !=
1858  llvm::cast<ShapedType>(getInputs()[0].getType()).getShape()) {
1859  return emitOpError() << "expects all inputs to have the same shapes. "
1860  "Shape at input-index "
1861  << i
1862  << " is not equal to the shape at input-index 0.";
1863  }
1864  }
1865  for (int64_t i = 1; i < getNumDpsInits(); ++i) {
1866  if (llvm::cast<ShapedType>(getInits()[i].getType()).getShape() !=
1867  llvm::cast<ShapedType>(getInits()[0].getType()).getShape()) {
1868  return emitOpError() << "expects all outputs to have the same shapes. "
1869  "Shape at output-index "
1870  << i
1871  << " is not equal to the shape at output-index 0.";
1872  }
1873  }
1874  auto inputType = llvm::cast<ShapedType>(getInputs()[0].getType());
1875  auto initType = llvm::cast<ShapedType>(getInits()[0].getType());
1876 
1877  DenseSet<int64_t> dimensionsToReduce;
1878  for (int64_t dimension : dimensionsRef) {
1879  if (dimension < 0 || dimension >= inputType.getRank()) {
1880  return emitOpError()
1881  << "dimensions for reduction should be in the range [0, "
1882  << inputType.getRank() - 1 << "].";
1883  }
1884  dimensionsToReduce.insert(dimension);
1885  }
1886 
1887  auto inputDims = inputType.getShape();
1888  auto initDims = initType.getShape();
1889 
1890  // Input dimensions that will be left after the reduction.
1891  SmallVector<int64_t> reducedInputDims;
1892  for (const auto &en : llvm::enumerate(inputDims)) {
1893  if (!dimensionsToReduce.count(en.index()))
1894  reducedInputDims.push_back(en.value());
1895  }
1896 
1897  if (reducedInputDims.size() != static_cast<size_t>(initType.getRank())) {
1898  return emitOpError() << "number of dimensions after reduction "
1899  << reducedInputDims.size()
1900  << " doesn't match the init rank "
1901  << initType.getRank();
1902  }
1903 
1904  if (reducedInputDims != initDims)
1905  return emitOpError() << "init dimensions [" << initDims
1906  << "] doesn't match input dimensions after reduction ["
1907  << reducedInputDims << "]";
1908 
1909  Block *block = getBody();
1910  if (block->getNumArguments() != this->getNumOperands())
1911  return emitOpError()
1912  << "mismatching number of operands and block arguments";
1913 
1914  // Check that the first block arguments match the element type of the inputs.
1915  for (auto [input, bbArg] : llvm::zip(getInputs(), block->getArguments())) {
1916  Type inputElementType =
1917  llvm::cast<ShapedType>(input.getType()).getElementType();
1918  if (inputElementType != bbArg.getType())
1919  return emitOpError()
1920  << "input element type " << inputElementType
1921  << " does not match corresponding block argument type "
1922  << bbArg.getType();
1923  }
1924 
1925  // Check that the last block arguments match the element type of the outputs.
1926  for (auto [output, bbArg] : llvm::zip(
1927  getDpsInits(), block->getArguments().take_back(getNumDpsInits()))) {
1928  auto outputElementType =
1929  llvm::cast<ShapedType>(output.getType()).getElementType();
1930  if (outputElementType != bbArg.getType())
1931  return emitOpError()
1932  << "output element type " << outputElementType
1933  << " does not match corresponding block argument type "
1934  << bbArg.getType();
1935  }
1936  return success();
1937 }

1943 static void buildIdentityRegion(OpBuilder &builder, Location loc,
1944  Region &region, ValueRange inputs,
1945  ValueRange outputs) {
1946  buildGenericRegion(builder, loc, region, inputs, outputs,
1947  [](OpBuilder &b, Location loc, ValueRange args) {
1948  if (!args.empty())
1949  linalg::YieldOp::create(b, loc, args[0]);
1950  });
1951 }

1954  ::mlir::OperationState &result, Value input, Value init,
1955  DenseI64ArrayAttr permutation,
1956  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attributes) {
1957  result.addOperands(input);
1958  result.addOperands(init);
1959  result.addAttribute(getPermutationAttrName(result.name), permutation);
1960  result.addAttributes(attributes);
1961

1964  if (llvm::isa<RankedTensorType>(initType))
1965  result.addTypes(initType);
1966

1968  init);

2005 LogicalResult TransposeOp::verify() {
2006  ArrayRef<int64_t> permutationRef = getPermutation();
2007 
2008  if (!isPermutationVector(permutationRef))
2009  return emitOpError("permutation is not valid");
2010 
2011  auto inputType = getInput().getType();
2012  auto initType = getInit().getType();
2013 
2014  int64_t rank = inputType.getRank();
2015 
2016  if (rank != initType.getRank())
2017  return emitOpError() << "input rank " << rank
2018  << " does not match init rank " << initType.getRank();
2019 
2020  if (rank != static_cast<int64_t>(permutationRef.size()))
2021  return emitOpError() << "size of permutation " << permutationRef.size()
2022  << " does not match the argument rank " << rank;
2023 
2024  auto inputDims = inputType.getShape();
2025  auto initDims = initType.getShape();
2026 
2027  for (int64_t i = 0; i < rank; ++i) {
2028  int64_t inputDim = inputDims[permutationRef[i]];
2029  int64_t initDim = initDims[i];
2030 
2031  if (inputDim != initDim) {
2032  return emitOpError() << "dim(result, " << i << ") = " << initDim
2033  << " doesn't match dim(input, permutation[" << i
2034  << "]) = " << inputDim;
2035  }
2036  }
2037 
2038  return success();
2039 }

2043  return SmallVector<utils::IteratorType>(rank, utils::IteratorType::parallel);

2051  llvm::to_vector_of<unsigned>(getPermutation()), getContext())),
2052  builder.getMultiDimIdentityMap(rank)});

2065 LogicalResult TransposeOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor,
2066  SmallVectorImpl<OpFoldResult> &result) {
2067  // Only the tensor type is supported.
2068  if (!isa<TensorType>(getInput().getType()))
2069  return failure();
2070 
2071  // Single dimension transpose.
2072  if (getPermutation().size() == 0) {
2073  result.push_back(getInput());
2074  return success();
2075  }
2076  // Identity permutation.
2077  if (isIdentityPermutation(getPermutation())) {
2078  result.push_back(getInput());
2079  return success();
2080  }
2081 
2082  return failure();
2083 }
2084 
2085 /// Fold transpose with transpose.
2086 struct FoldTransposeWithTranspose : OpRewritePattern<linalg::TransposeOp> {
2087  using OpRewritePattern<linalg::TransposeOp>::OpRewritePattern;
2088 
2089  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(linalg::TransposeOp transposeOp,
2090  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
2091  auto defTransposeOp = transposeOp.getInput().getDefiningOp<TransposeOp>();
2092  if (!defTransposeOp)
2093  return failure();
2094  ArrayRef<int64_t> defPerms = defTransposeOp.getPermutation();
2095  ArrayRef<int64_t> perms = transposeOp.getPermutation();
2096  SmallVector<int64_t> foldedPerms;
2097  foldedPerms.reserve(perms.size());
2098  for (int64_t perm : perms)
2099  foldedPerms.push_back(defPerms[perm]);
2100 
2101  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<TransposeOp>(
2102  transposeOp, defTransposeOp.getInput(), transposeOp.getInit(),
2103  foldedPerms);
2104  return success();
2105  }
2106 };
2107 
2108 /// This pattern canonicalize transpose by swapping the order of
2109 /// broadcast and transpose:
2110 /// transpose(broadcast(input)) -> broadcast(transpose(input))
2111 struct SwapTransposeWithBroadcast : OpRewritePattern<linalg::TransposeOp> {
2112  using OpRewritePattern<linalg::TransposeOp>::OpRewritePattern;
2113 
2114  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(linalg::TransposeOp transposeOp,
2115  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
2116  Value input = transposeOp.getInput();
2117  BroadcastOp broadcastOp = input.getDefiningOp<BroadcastOp>();
2118  if (!input.hasOneUse() || !broadcastOp)
2119  return failure();
2120 
2121  ArrayRef<int64_t> dimensions = broadcastOp.getDimensions();
2122  ArrayRef<int64_t> perms = transposeOp.getPermutation();
2123 
2124  // Get new perms and new dimensions.
2125  SmallVector<int64_t> resultPerms = dropDims(perms, dimensions);
2126  SmallVector<int64_t> invertPerm = invertPermutationVector(perms);
2127  SmallVector<int64_t> resultDimensions;
2128  unsigned dimensionSize = dimensions.size();
2129  for (unsigned i = 0; i < dimensionSize; ++i)
2130  resultDimensions.push_back(invertPerm[dimensions[i]]);
2131 
2132  // Create transpose result.
2133  Value broadcastInput = broadcastOp.getInput();
2134  Location loc = transposeOp.getLoc();
2135  MLIRContext *ctx = transposeOp.getContext();
2136  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> dims;
2137  auto broadcastInputTy =
2138  mlir::cast<RankedTensorType>(broadcastInput.getType());
2139  unsigned inputRank = broadcastInputTy.getRank();
2140  for (unsigned i = 0; i < inputRank; ++i) {
2141  if (broadcastInputTy.isDynamicDim(i)) {
2142  dims.push_back(tensor::DimOp::create(rewriter, loc, broadcastInput, i)
2143  ->getResult(0));
2144  } else {
2145  dims.push_back(IntegerAttr::get(IndexType::get(ctx),
2146  broadcastInputTy.getDimSize(i)));
2147  }
2148  }
2149  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> transposeResultShapes =
2150  applyPermutation(dims, resultPerms);
2151  Value transposeInit = tensor::EmptyOp::create(
2152  rewriter, transposeOp.getLoc(), transposeResultShapes,
2153  broadcastInputTy.getElementType());
2154 
2155  // Create broadcast(transpose(input)).
2156  Value transposeResult =
2157  TransposeOp::create(rewriter, loc, broadcastOp.getInput(),
2158  transposeInit, resultPerms)
2159  ->getResult(0);
2160  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<BroadcastOp>(
2161  transposeOp, transposeResult, transposeOp.getInit(), resultDimensions);
2162  return success();
2163  }
2164 };
2165 
2166 void TransposeOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
2167  MLIRContext *context) {
2168  results.add<FoldTransposeWithTranspose, SwapTransposeWithBroadcast>(context);
2169 }

2226 
2227 LogicalResult BroadcastOp::verify() {
2228  ArrayRef<int64_t> dimensionsRef = getDimensions();
2229 
2230  auto inputType = getInput().getType();
2231  auto initType = getInit().getType();
2232 
2233  int64_t inputRank = inputType.getRank();
2234  int64_t initRank = initType.getRank();
2235 
2236  auto inputShape = inputType.getShape();
2237  auto initShape = initType.getShape();
2238 
2239  if ((size_t)inputRank + dimensionsRef.size() != (size_t)initRank)
2240  return emitOpError() << "input rank plus added dimensions does not "
2241  "match init rank. input rank: "
2242  << inputRank
2243  << ", dimensions size: " << dimensionsRef.size()
2244  << ", init rank: " << initRank;
2245 
2246  for (const auto &[idx, dim] : llvm::enumerate(dimensionsRef)) {
2247  if (dim < 0 || dim >= initRank)
2248  return emitOpError() << "dimension " << idx
2249  << " is out of range. expected range: [0, "
2250  << initRank - 1 << "], got: " << dim;
2251  }
2252 
2253  // Mapping from input dims to init dims.
2254  SmallVector<int64_t> dimMap;
2255  for (auto dim : llvm::seq<int64_t>(0, initRank)) {
2256  if (!llvm::is_contained(dimensionsRef, dim))
2257  dimMap.push_back(dim);
2258  }
2259 
2260  for (const auto &[inputDimIdx, initDimIdx] : llvm::enumerate(dimMap)) {
2261  // This dimensions is mapped from the input. Init and input dims should
2262  // match.
2263  if (inputShape[inputDimIdx] != initShape[initDimIdx])
2264  return emitOpError() << "input dim " << inputDimIdx
2265  << " should match init dim " << initDimIdx
2266  << ". input: " << inputShape[inputDimIdx]
2267  << ", init: " << initShape[initDimIdx];
2268  }
2269 
2270  return success();
2271 }

2283  builder.getMultiDimIdentityMap(rank)});

2296 /// Fold back-to-back broadcasts together.
2297 struct FoldBroadcasts : OpRewritePattern<linalg::BroadcastOp> {
2298  using OpRewritePattern<linalg::BroadcastOp>::OpRewritePattern;
2299 
2300  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(linalg::BroadcastOp broadcastOp,
2301  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
2302  auto defBroadcastOp = broadcastOp.getInput().getDefiningOp<BroadcastOp>();
2303  if (!defBroadcastOp)
2304  return failure();
2305  ArrayRef<int64_t> defDimensions = defBroadcastOp.getDimensions();
2306  ArrayRef<int64_t> dimensions = broadcastOp.getDimensions();
2307  SmallVector<int64_t> foldedDims(dimensions);
2308  Value init = broadcastOp.getInit();
2309  int64_t initRank = cast<ShapedType>(init.getType()).getRank();
2310  // Mapping from input dims to init dims.
2311  SmallVector<int64_t> dimMap;
2312  for (auto dim : llvm::seq<int64_t>(0, initRank)) {
2313  if (!llvm::is_contained(dimensions, dim))
2314  dimMap.push_back(dim);
2315  }
2316  for (auto dim : defDimensions)
2317  foldedDims.push_back(dimMap[dim]);
2318 
2319  llvm::sort(foldedDims);
2320  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<BroadcastOp>(
2321  broadcastOp, defBroadcastOp.getInput(), init, foldedDims);
2322  return success();
2323  }
2324 };
2325 
2326 void BroadcastOp::getCanonicalizationPatterns(RewritePatternSet &results,
2327  MLIRContext *context) {
2328  results.add<EraseIdentityLinalgOp<BroadcastOp>, FoldBroadcasts>(context);
2329 }
