2343 ParseResult YieldOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
2344  SmallVector<OpAsmParser::UnresolvedOperand, 2> opInfo;
2345  SmallVector<Type, 2> types;
2346  SMLoc loc = parser.getCurrentLocation();
2347  return failure(parser.parseOperandList(opInfo) ||
2348  parser.parseOptionalAttrDict(result.attributes) ||
2349  (!opInfo.empty() && parser.parseColonTypeList(types)) ||
2350  parser.resolveOperands(opInfo, types, loc, result.operands));
2351 }
2352 
2353 // Check the operand number and types must match the element types of the
2354 // LinalgOp interface's shaped operands.
2355 static LogicalResult verifyYield(linalg::YieldOp op, LinalgOp linalgOp) {
2356  if (op.getNumOperands() != linalgOp.getNumDpsInits())
2357  return op.emitOpError("expected number of yield values (")
2358  << op.getNumOperands()
2359  << ") to match the number of inits / outs operands of the enclosing "
2360  << "LinalgOp (" << linalgOp.getNumDpsInits() << ")";
2361 
2362  for (OpOperand &opOperand : op->getOpOperands()) {
2363  OpOperand *outputOperand =
2364  linalgOp.getDpsInitOperand(opOperand.getOperandNumber());
2365  Type elementType = outputOperand->get().getType();
2366  if (isa<MemRefType, RankedTensorType>(elementType))
2367  elementType = getElementTypeOrSelf(outputOperand->get().getType());
2368  if (opOperand.get().getType() != elementType)
2369  return op.emitOpError("type of yield operand ")
2370  << (opOperand.getOperandNumber() + 1) << " ("
2371  << opOperand.get().getType() << ") doesn't match "
2372  << "the element type of the enclosing linalg.generic op ("
2373  << elementType << ")";
2374  }
2375  return success();
2376 }
2377 
2378 LogicalResult linalg::YieldOp::verify() {
2379  auto *parentOp = (*this)->getParentOp();
2380  if (parentOp->getNumRegions() != 1 || parentOp->getRegion(0).empty())
2381  return emitOpError("expected single non-empty parent region");
2382 
2383  if (auto linalgOp = dyn_cast<LinalgOp>(parentOp))
2384  return verifyYield(*this, linalgOp);
2385 
2386  return emitOpError("expected parent op with LinalgOp interface");
2387 }

2389 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2390 // IndexOp
2391 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2392 
2393 LogicalResult IndexOp::verify() {
2394  auto linalgOp = dyn_cast<LinalgOp>((*this)->getParentOp());
2395  if (!linalgOp)
2396  return emitOpError("expected parent op with LinalgOp interface");
2397  if (linalgOp.getNumLoops() <= getDim())
2398  return emitOpError("expected dim (")
2399  << getDim() << ") to be lower than the number of loops ("
2400  << linalgOp.getNumLoops() << ") of the enclosing LinalgOp";
2401  return success();
2402 }
2403 
2404 OpFoldResult IndexOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
2405  auto linalgOp = dyn_cast_or_null<LinalgOp>((*this)->getParentOp());
2406  // Bail out if `linalg.index` does not have a proper parent yet at this
2407  // point, e.g., when calling `createOrFold` during IR construction in
2408  // `genericOp::build`.
2409  if (!linalgOp)
2410  return OpFoldResult{};
2411 
2412  // Index of unit dims is always 0.
2413  SmallVector<int64_t, 4> loopBounds = linalgOp.getStaticLoopRanges();
2414  uint64_t dim = getDim();
2415  assert(dim < loopBounds.size() && "Dim is out of bounds");
2416  if (loopBounds[dim] == 1)
2417  return IntegerAttr::get(IndexType::get(getContext()), 0);
2418 
2419  return OpFoldResult{};
2420 }

2454 SmallVector<AffineExpr, 4> mlir::linalg::concat(ArrayRef<AffineExpr> a,
2455  ArrayRef<AffineExpr> b) {
2456  auto rangeA = llvm::make_range(a.begin(), a.end());
2457  auto rangeB = llvm::make_range(b.begin(), b.end());
2458  auto concatRanges = llvm::concat<const AffineExpr>(rangeA, rangeB);
2459  return llvm::to_vector<4>(concatRanges);
2460 }

2462 static LogicalResult appendMangledType(llvm::raw_string_ostream &ss, Type t) {
2463  if (auto memref = llvm::dyn_cast<MemRefType>(t)) {
2464  ss << "view";
2465  for (auto size : memref.getShape())
2466  if (size < 0)
2467  ss << "sx";
2468  else
2469  ss << size << "x";
2470  if (failed(appendMangledType(ss, memref.getElementType())))
2471  return failure();
2472  if (auto as = memref.getMemorySpace()) {
2473  if (auto attr = llvm::dyn_cast<IntegerAttr>(as))
2474  ss << "as" << attr.getInt();
2475  else
2476  return failure();
2477  }
2478  return success();
2479  }
2480  if (auto vec = llvm::dyn_cast<VectorType>(t)) {
2481  ss << "vector";
2482  llvm::interleave(
2483  vec.getShape(), [&](int64_t i) { ss << i; }, [&]() { ss << "x"; });
2484  if (failed(appendMangledType(ss, vec.getElementType())))
2485  return failure();
2486  return success();
2487  }
2488  if (t.isSignlessIntOrIndexOrFloat()) {
2489  ss << t;
2490  return success();
2491  }
2492  return failure();
2493 }
2494 
2495 std::string mlir::linalg::generateLibraryCallName(Operation *op) {
2496  assert(isa<LinalgOp>(op));
2497  std::string name(op->getName().getStringRef().str());
2498  std::string fun = "";
2499  for (NamedAttribute kv : op->getAttrs()) {
2500  if (UnaryFnAttr ufa = llvm::dyn_cast<UnaryFnAttr>(kv.getValue())) {
2501  fun = stringifyEnum(ufa.getValue()).str() + "_";
2502  } else if (BinaryFnAttr bfa = llvm::dyn_cast<BinaryFnAttr>(kv.getValue())) {
2503  fun = stringifyEnum(bfa.getValue()).str() + "_";
2504  }
2505  }
2506  name.reserve(128);
2507  llvm::replace(name, '.', '_');
2508  llvm::raw_string_ostream ss(name);
2509  ss << "_" << fun;
2510  for (Type t : op->getOperandTypes()) {
2511  if (failed(appendMangledType(ss, t)))
2512  return std::string();
2513  ss << "_";
2514  }
2515  name.pop_back();
2516  return name;
2517 }

2523 namespace {
2524 struct EraseDeadLinalgOp : public OpInterfaceRewritePattern<LinalgOp> {
2525  using OpInterfaceRewritePattern<LinalgOp>::OpInterfaceRewritePattern;
2526 
2527  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(LinalgOp op,
2528  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
2529  for (OpOperand &opOperand : op->getOpOperands()) {
2530  // Linalg "inputs" may be either tensor or memref type.
2531  // tensor<0xelt_type> is a convention that may not always mean
2532  // "0 iterations". Only erase in cases we see memref<...x0x...>.
2533  auto mt = llvm::dyn_cast<MemRefType>(opOperand.get().getType());
2534  if (!mt)
2535  continue;
2536  if (llvm::is_contained(op.getShape(&opOperand), 0)) {
2537  rewriter.eraseOp(op);
2538  return success();
2539  }
2540  }
2541  return failure();
2542  }
2543 };
2544 
2545 /// Fold LinalgOps with `tensor.cast` consumer if the `tensor.cast` has
2546 /// result that is more static than the linalg op.
2547 struct FoldTensorCastConsumerOp : public OpRewritePattern<tensor::CastOp> {
2548  using OpRewritePattern<tensor::CastOp>::OpRewritePattern;
2549 
2550  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(tensor::CastOp castOp,
2551  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
2552  if (!tensor::canFoldIntoProducerOp(castOp))
2553  return failure();
2554 
2555  auto linalgOp = castOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<LinalgOp>();
2556  if (!linalgOp)
2557  return failure();
2558 
2559  // Cast can be in conditionally reachable region, if which case folding will
2560  // generate invalid code. Only conservatively fold ops in same block for
2561  // now.
2562  if (castOp->getBlock() != linalgOp->getBlock())
2563  return failure();
2564 
2565  OpBuilder::InsertionGuard guard(rewriter);
2566  rewriter.setInsertionPoint(linalgOp);
2567 
2568  Location loc = linalgOp.getLoc();
2569  OpResult resultValue = llvm::cast<OpResult>(castOp.getSource());
2570  unsigned resultNumber = resultValue.getResultNumber();
2571  auto resultType =
2572  llvm::cast<RankedTensorType>(castOp->getResult(0).getType());
2573  // Replace the `outs` for the result with a `tensor.cast`. This cast is now
2574  // going from a more dynamic shape to a less dynamic shape. If the producer
2575  // for this cast, i.e. producer of the out operand, is also an operation
2576  // that folds with tensor.cast consumer (like this pattern), the cast will
2577  // continue to propagate as far up the stack as it can go.
2578  OpOperand *outOperand = linalgOp.getDpsInitOperand(resultNumber);
2579  Value newOperand =
2580  tensor::CastOp::create(rewriter, loc, resultType, outOperand->get());
2581  SmallVector<Value> newOperands = linalgOp.getDpsInputs();
2582  SmallVector<Value> outputOperands(linalgOp.getDpsInits().begin(),
2583  linalgOp.getDpsInits().end());
2584  outputOperands[resultNumber] = newOperand;
2585  newOperands.append(outputOperands.begin(), outputOperands.end());
2586 
2587  SmallVector<Type> resultTypes(linalgOp->result_type_begin(),
2588  linalgOp->result_type_end());
2589  resultTypes[resultNumber] = resultType;
2590  Operation *newOp = clone(rewriter, linalgOp, resultTypes, newOperands);
2591 
2592  // Create a tensor.cast operation back to the original type.
2593  Value castBack = tensor::CastOp::create(
2594  rewriter, loc, resultValue.getType(), newOp->getResult(resultNumber));
2595 
2596  SmallVector<Value> results(newOp->result_begin(), newOp->result_end());
2597  results[resultNumber] = castBack;
2598  rewriter.replaceOp(linalgOp, results);
2599  rewriter.replaceOp(castOp, newOp->getResult(resultNumber));
2600  return success();
2601  }
2602 };
2603 
2604 /// For each of the operand in `operands` this function maps the static sizes of
2605 /// dimensions to their affine dim expressions.
2606 static void populateMap(LinalgOp linalgOp, MutableArrayRef<OpOperand> operands,
2607  llvm::DenseMap<AffineExpr, int64_t> &affineExprToSize) {
2608  for (OpOperand &opOperand : operands) {
2609  if (linalgOp.isScalar(&opOperand))
2610  continue;
2611  Value src = opOperand.get();
2612  auto sourceType = llvm::cast<RankedTensorType>(src.getType());
2613  auto sourceMap = linalgOp.getMatchingIndexingMap(&opOperand);
2614 
2615  // Get the `sourceShape` of the `sourceType`. If the operand is a result of
2616  // `tensor.cast` operation and source of the cast operation has a static
2617  // shape, then assign it to the `sourceShape`.
2618  auto *parentOp = src.getDefiningOp();
2619  ArrayRef<int64_t> sourceShape = sourceType.getShape();
2620  if (parentOp) {
2621  if (auto castOp = dyn_cast<tensor::CastOp>(parentOp)) {
2622  Value castSource = castOp.getSource();
2623  auto castSourceType =
2624  llvm::dyn_cast<RankedTensorType>(castSource.getType());
2625  if (castSourceType && castSourceType.hasStaticShape())
2626  sourceShape = castSourceType.getShape();
2627  }
2628  }
2629 
2630  // If the source shape's dimension has a static shape, map the affine dim
2631  // expression to the known static size.
2632  for (unsigned i = 0; i < sourceShape.size(); i++) {
2633  if (sourceType.isDynamicDim(i))
2634  continue;
2635  if (auto affineDimExpr = dyn_cast<AffineDimExpr>(sourceMap.getResult(i)))
2636  affineExprToSize.try_emplace(affineDimExpr, sourceShape[i]);
2637  }
2638  }
2639 }
2640 
2641 /// Creates new operand w.r.t 'opOperand' of `linalgOp` with static sizes
2642 /// mapped in `affineExprToSize`. New operands are created in `newOperands` and
2643 /// their result types is stored in `resultTypes`. If `opOperand` requires no
2644 /// change then `changeNeeded` is false and same operand is added in the
2645 /// `newOperands` list.
2646 static void createNewOperandWithStaticSizes(
2647  Location loc, PatternRewriter &rewriter, OpOperand *opOperand,
2648  llvm::DenseMap<AffineExpr, int64_t> &affineExprToSize, LinalgOp linalgOp,
2649  SmallVector<Value> &newOperands, SmallVector<Type> &resultTypes,
2650  bool &changeNeeded) {
2651  Value src = opOperand->get();
2652  newOperands.push_back(src);
2653  if (linalgOp.isScalar(opOperand))
2654  return;
2655  auto sourceType = llvm::cast<RankedTensorType>(src.getType());
2656  Type resultType = sourceType;
2657  if (sourceType.hasStaticShape() && linalgOp.isDpsInit(opOperand)) {
2658  resultTypes.push_back(resultType);
2659  return;
2660  }
2661  ArrayRef<int64_t> sourceShape = sourceType.getShape();
2662  AffineMap sourceMap = linalgOp.getMatchingIndexingMap(opOperand);
2663  SmallVector<int64_t> newShape;
2664  // If operand is updated with new shape, `newOperandNeeded` will be
2665  // true.
2666  bool newOperandNeeded = false;
2667  for (unsigned i = 0; i < sourceShape.size(); i++) {
2668  int64_t dimShape = sourceShape[i];
2669  AffineExpr dimExpr = sourceMap.getResult(i);
2670  if (!affineExprToSize.contains(dimExpr) || !sourceType.isDynamicDim(i)) {
2671  newShape.push_back(dimShape);
2672  continue;
2673  }
2674  // Dimension has a dynamic shape and corresponding affine dim
2675  // expression is present in the map. So assign the size for the
2676  // given affine dim expression to the dimension.
2677  newShape.push_back(affineExprToSize[dimExpr]);
2678  newOperandNeeded = true;
2679  }
2680  resultType = RankedTensorType::get(newShape, sourceType.getElementType(),
2681  sourceType.getEncoding());
2682  if (newOperandNeeded) {
2683  changeNeeded = true;
2684  // Get the new operand value given its size and element type by
2685  // casting it.
2686  Value newOperand = tensor::CastOp::create(rewriter, loc, resultType, src);
2687  unsigned index = opOperand->getOperandNumber();
2688  newOperands[index] = newOperand;
2689  }
2690  if (linalgOp.isDpsInit(opOperand))
2691  resultTypes.push_back(resultType);
2692 }
2693 
2694 /// Static shapes for the operands can be inferred if any one of the operands
2695 /// have a static shape. This can be done by referring to the affine dim
2696 /// expressions for the operand.
2697 struct InferStaticShapeOfOperands : public OpInterfaceRewritePattern<LinalgOp> {
2698  using OpInterfaceRewritePattern<LinalgOp>::OpInterfaceRewritePattern;
2699 
2700  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(LinalgOp linalgOp,
2701  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
2702  if (!linalgOp.hasPureTensorSemantics())
2703  return failure();
2704 
2705  // Maps must be projected permutations.
2706  if (llvm::any_of(linalgOp.getIndexingMapsArray(), [](AffineMap map) {
2707  return !map.isProjectedPermutation();
2708  }))
2709  return failure();
2710 
2711  // Maps affine dim expressions to the static size of that dimension.
2712  llvm::DenseMap<AffineExpr, int64_t> affineExprToSize;
2713  Location loc = linalgOp.getLoc();
2714 
2715  // For each of the affine dim expression, check if the size is known. If
2716  // known add that in the map.
2717  populateMap(linalgOp, linalgOp->getOpOperands(), affineExprToSize);
2718 
2719  SmallVector<Value> newOperands;
2720  SmallVector<Type> resultTypes;
2721 
2722  // `changeNeeded` is `false` if the operands of `linalgOp` require no
2723  // change in their types.
2724  bool changeNeeded = false;
2725  newOperands.reserve(linalgOp->getNumOperands());
2726  resultTypes.reserve(linalgOp.getNumDpsInits());
2727 
2728  // Iterate over all the operands and update the static sizes.
2729  for (OpOperand &opOperand : linalgOp->getOpOperands()) {
2730  createNewOperandWithStaticSizes(loc, rewriter, &opOperand,
2731  affineExprToSize, linalgOp, newOperands,
2732  resultTypes, changeNeeded);
2733  }
2734 
2735  // If the generic op has all the required static information, no
2736  // canonicalization needed.
2737  if (!changeNeeded)
2738  return failure();
2739 
2740  // Clone op.
2741  Operation *newOp = clone(rewriter, linalgOp, resultTypes, newOperands);
2742  SmallVector<Value> replacements;
2743  replacements.reserve(newOp->getNumResults());
2744  for (auto it : llvm::zip(linalgOp->getResults(), newOp->getResults())) {
2745  Value newResult = std::get<1>(it);
2746  Value oldResult = std::get<0>(it);
2747  Type newType = newResult.getType();
2748  Type oldType = oldResult.getType();
2749  replacements.push_back(
2750  (newType != oldType)
2751  ? tensor::CastOp::create(rewriter, loc, oldType, newResult)
2752  : newResult);
2753  }
2754  rewriter.replaceOp(linalgOp, replacements);
2755  return success();
2756  }
2757 };
2758 
2759 } // namespace

2761 // All named ops canonicalizers and folders are auto-generated in the
2762 // .cpp.inc.

2767 
2768 LogicalResult SoftmaxOp::verify() {
2769  ShapedType inputType = getInputOperandType();
2770  ShapedType outputType = getOutputOperandType();
2771 
2772  ArrayRef<int64_t> inputShape = inputType.getShape();
2773  ArrayRef<int64_t> outputShape = outputType.getShape();
2774  if (failed(verifyCompatibleShape(inputShape, outputShape)))
2775  return emitOpError("incompatible output shape");
2776 
2777  int64_t inputRank = getInputOperandRank();
2778  int64_t dimension = getDimension();
2779  if ((dimension < 0) || (dimension >= inputRank))
2780  return emitOpError("incorrect dimension specified");
2781 
2782  return success();
2783 }
2784 
2785 SmallVector<Range> SoftmaxOp::getIterationDomain(OpBuilder &builder) {
2786  int64_t operandRank = getInputOperandRank();
2787  SmallVector<Range> loopBounds(operandRank);
2788  Location loc = getLoc();
2789  Value zero = arith::ConstantIndexOp::create(builder, loc, 0);
2790  Value one = arith::ConstantIndexOp::create(builder, loc, 1);
2791  Value source = getInput();
2792  for (auto dim : llvm::seq<int64_t>(0, operandRank)) {
2793  loopBounds[dim].offset = zero;
2794  loopBounds[dim].size = getDimValue(builder, loc, source, dim);
2795  loopBounds[dim].stride = one;
2796  }
2797  return loopBounds;
2798 }

2800 SmallVector<utils::IteratorType> SoftmaxOp::getLoopIteratorTypes() {
2801  SmallVector<utils::IteratorType> iteratorTypes(getInputOperandRank(),
2802  utils::IteratorType::parallel);
2803  iteratorTypes[getDimension()] = utils::IteratorType::reduction;
2804  return iteratorTypes;
2805 }

2807 FailureOr<TilingResult>
2808 SoftmaxOp::getTiledImplementation(OpBuilder &builder,
2809  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> offsets,
2810  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> sizes) {
2811  int64_t rank = getInputOperandRank();
2812  auto oneAttr = builder.getI64IntegerAttr(1);
2813  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> strides(rank, oneAttr);
2814  SmallVector<Value> tiledOperands;
2815  Operation *inputSlice =
2816  getSlice(builder, getLoc(), getInput(), offsets, sizes, strides);
2817  if (!inputSlice) {
2818  return emitOpError("failed to compute input slice");
2819  }
2820  tiledOperands.emplace_back(inputSlice->getResult(0));
2821  Operation *outputSlice =
2822  getSlice(builder, getLoc(), getOutput(), offsets, sizes, strides);
2823  if (!outputSlice) {
2824  return emitOpError("failed to compute output slice");
2825  }
2826  tiledOperands.emplace_back(outputSlice->getResult(0));
2827 
2828  SmallVector<Type, 4> resultTypes;
2829  if (hasPureTensorSemantics())
2830  resultTypes.push_back(tiledOperands[1].getType());
2831  Operation *tiledOp =
2832  mlir::clone(builder, getOperation(), resultTypes, tiledOperands);
2833 
2834  return TilingResult{
2835  {tiledOp},
2836  SmallVector<Value>(tiledOp->getResults()),
2837  llvm::to_vector(ArrayRef<Operation *>{inputSlice, outputSlice})};
2838 }

2840 LogicalResult SoftmaxOp::getResultTilePosition(
2841  OpBuilder &builder, unsigned resultNumber, ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> offsets,
2842  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> sizes, SmallVector<OpFoldResult> &resultOffsets,
2843  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> &resultSizes) {
2844  if (resultNumber == 0) {
2845  resultOffsets.assign(offsets.begin(), offsets.end());
2846  resultSizes.assign(sizes.begin(), sizes.end());
2847  return success();
2848  }
2849  return failure();
2850 }

2853 LogicalResult SoftmaxOp::fold(FoldAdaptor, SmallVectorImpl<OpFoldResult> &) {

2856 
2857 LogicalResult
2858 SoftmaxOp::reifyResultShapes(OpBuilder &b,
2859  ReifiedRankedShapedTypeDims &reifiedReturnShapes) {
2860  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> shapes;
2861  Location loc = getOperation()->getLoc();
2862  IRRewriter rewriter(b);
2863  auto inputShapedType = llvm::cast<ShapedType>(getInputOperandType());
2864  auto outputShapedType = llvm::cast<ShapedType>(getOutputOperandType());
2865  for (int64_t dim : llvm::seq<int64_t>(0, getOutputOperandRank())) {
2866  if (!outputShapedType.isDynamicDim(dim)) {
2867  // Static dim: Return IntegerAttr.
2868  shapes.push_back(b.getIndexAttr(inputShapedType.getDimSize(dim)));
2869  } else {
2870  // Dynamic dim: Return Value.
2871  OpFoldResult ofr = createOrFoldDimOp(b, loc, getInput(), dim);
2872  shapes.push_back(getValueOrCreateConstantIndexOp(b, loc, ofr));
2873  }
2874  }
2875  reifiedReturnShapes.emplace_back(std::move(shapes));
2876  return success();
2877 }
2878 
2879 void SoftmaxOp::getEffects(
2880  SmallVectorImpl<SideEffects::EffectInstance<MemoryEffects::Effect>>
2881  &effects) {
2882  for (auto [index, operand] : llvm::enumerate(getDpsInputs())) {
2883  if (!llvm::isa<MemRefType>(operand.getType()))
2884  continue;
2885  effects.emplace_back(MemoryEffects::Read::get(),
2886  &getOperation()->getOpOperand(index), /*stage=*/0,
2887  /*effectOnFullRegion=*/true,
2888  SideEffects::DefaultResource::get());
2889  }
2890 
2891  for (OpOperand &operand : getDpsInitsMutable()) {
2892  if (!llvm::isa<MemRefType>(operand.get().getType()))
2893  continue;
2894  effects.emplace_back(MemoryEffects::Read::get(), &operand, /*stage=*/0,
2895  /*effectOnFullRegion=*/true,
2896  SideEffects::DefaultResource::get());
2897  effects.emplace_back(MemoryEffects::Write::get(), &operand, /*stage=*/0,
2898  /*effectOnFullRegion=*/true,
2899  SideEffects::DefaultResource::get());
2900  }
2901 }
2902 
2903 // Helper functions for softmax decomposition.
2904 // @{
2905 
2906 // Helper function to produce the iterator types (reduction or parallel) and
2907 // affine maps for the iterators used in the decomposition of softmax.
2908 // This method creates:
2909 // If allParallel == true:
2910 // - iterator type: {parallel, ..., parallel}
2911 // - affine maps:
2912 // -- identity with inputRank dimensions.
2913 // -- (d0, ..., dN) -> (d0, ..., d_dim-1, d_dim+1, ..., dN),
2914 // where N == inputRank.
2915 //
2916 // If allParallel == false:
2917 // - iterator type at dim(i) == parallel for i != \p dim and
2918 // dim(dim) == reduction.
2919 // - affine map:
2920 // -- identity with inputRank dimensions.
2921 // -- (d0, ..., dN) -> (d0, ..., d_dim-1, d_dim+1, ..., dN),
2922 // where N == inputRank.
2923 static std::tuple<SmallVector<utils::IteratorType>, SmallVector<AffineMap>>
2924 computeIteratorTypesAndIndexingMaps(OpBuilder &builder, int64_t inputRank,
2925  int64_t dim, bool allParallel = false) {
2926  SmallVector<utils::IteratorType> iteratorTypes(inputRank,
2927  utils::IteratorType::parallel);
2928  if (!allParallel)
2929  iteratorTypes[dim] = utils::IteratorType::reduction;
2930  MLIRContext *ctxt = builder.getContext();
2931  auto identityMap = AffineMap::getMultiDimIdentityMap(inputRank, ctxt);
2932  SmallVector<AffineExpr, 2> affineExprs;
2933  for (int i = 0; i < inputRank; i++) {
2934  if (i != dim)
2935  affineExprs.push_back(mlir::getAffineDimExpr(i, ctxt));
2936  }
2937  auto reductionMap =
2938  AffineMap::get(inputRank, /*symbols=*/0, affineExprs, ctxt);
2939  SmallVector<AffineMap> indexingMaps{identityMap, reductionMap};
2940  return std::make_tuple(iteratorTypes, indexingMaps);
2941 }
2942 
2943 // Helper function to produce a linalg.generic that computes a reduction on
2944 // dimension \p dim with the operation type \p T.
2945 template <typename T>
2946 static Value reduce(OpBuilder &builder, Location loc, Value input, Value output,
2947  int64_t dim) {
2948  auto inputType = cast<ShapedType>(input.getType());
2949  ArrayRef<int64_t> inputShape = inputType.getShape();
2950  int64_t inputRank = inputShape.size();
2951  auto [iteratorTypes, indexingMaps] =
2952  computeIteratorTypesAndIndexingMaps(builder, inputRank, dim);
2953  assert(indexingMaps.size() == 2 &&
2954  "We should have two maps: 1 for the input, 1 for the output");
2955  assert(indexingMaps[0].isIdentity() && "input map should be identity");
2956 
2957  auto genericOp = linalg::GenericOp::create(
2958  builder, loc, output.getType(), input, output, indexingMaps,
2959  iteratorTypes, [&](OpBuilder &b, Location loc, ValueRange args) {
2960  Value result = T::create(b, loc, args[0], args[1]);
2961  linalg::YieldOp::create(b, loc, result);
2962  });
2963  return genericOp.getResult(0);
2964 }
2965 
2966 /// Produce a linalg generic that computes the second step of the softmax
2967 /// decomposition: res = exp(input - max), where \p max is the max of \p input
2968 /// on dimension \p dim.
2969 static Value buildSubAndExpOp(OpBuilder &builder, Location loc, Value input,
2970  Value max, Value output, int64_t dim) {
2971  auto inputType = cast<ShapedType>(input.getType());
2972  ArrayRef<int64_t> inputShape = inputType.getShape();
2973  int64_t inputRank = inputShape.size();
2974  auto [iteratorTypes, indexingMaps] = computeIteratorTypesAndIndexingMaps(
2975  builder, inputRank, dim, /*allParallel=*/true);
2976  assert(indexingMaps.size() == 2 && "We should have one map for each input");
2977  assert(indexingMaps[0].isIdentity() && "input map should be identity");
2978  // Add the affine map for the output argument.
2979  indexingMaps.push_back(indexingMaps[0]);
2980  auto genericOp = linalg::GenericOp::create(
2981  builder, loc, input.getType(), ValueRange{input, max}, output,
2982  indexingMaps, iteratorTypes,
2983  [&](OpBuilder &b, Location loc, ValueRange args) {
2984  Value diff = arith::SubFOp::create(b, loc, args[0], args[1]);
2985  Value result = math::ExpOp::create(b, loc, diff);
2986  linalg::YieldOp::create(b, loc, result);
2987  });
2988  return genericOp.getResult(0);
2989 }
2990 
2991 /// Produce a linalg generic that computes the final step of the softmax
2992 /// decomposition.
2993 /// \returns linalg.generic ins(\p numerator, \p denominator) outs(\p output) {
2994 /// yield n / d
2995 /// }
2996 static Value buildDivOp(OpBuilder &builder, Location loc, Value numerator,
2997  Value denominator, Value output, int64_t dim) {
2998  auto inputType = cast<ShapedType>(numerator.getType());
2999  ArrayRef<int64_t> inputShape = inputType.getShape();
3000  int64_t inputRank = inputShape.size();
3001  auto [iteratorTypes, indexingMaps] = computeIteratorTypesAndIndexingMaps(
3002  builder, inputRank, dim, /*allParallel=*/true);
3003  assert(indexingMaps.size() == 2 &&
3004  "We should have one map for each input (2)");
3005  assert(indexingMaps[0].isIdentity() && "Numerator map should be identity");
3006  // Add the affine map for the output tensor.
3007  indexingMaps.push_back(indexingMaps[0]);
3008  auto genericOp = linalg::GenericOp::create(
3009  builder, loc, numerator.getType(), ValueRange{numerator, denominator},
3010  output, indexingMaps, iteratorTypes,
3011  [&](OpBuilder &b, Location loc, ValueRange args) {
3012  Value result = arith::DivFOp::create(b, loc, args[0], args[1]);
3013  linalg::YieldOp::create(b, loc, result);
3014  });
3015  return genericOp.getResult(0);
3016 }
3017 // @} End helper functions for softmax decomposition.
3018 
3019 /// Given an N-dimensional tensor x, this method converts
3020 /// softmax(x) to the following sequence of operations:
3021 ///
3022 /// 1. Compute the max of x along dimension d. This results
3023 /// in a N-1 dimensional tensor m.
3024 /// m = max(x, dim = d)
3025 ///
3026 /// 2. Subtract a broadcasted m from x and exponentiate. This results in
3027 /// a N dimensional tensor z.
3028 /// z = exp(x - m)
3029 ///
3030 /// 3. Compute the sum of z along dimension d. This results in
3031 /// a N-1 dimensional tensor l.
3032 /// l = sum(z, dim = d)
3033 ///
3034 /// 4. Divide z and l. This gives the N-dimensional softmax.
3035 /// softmax = z / l
3036 ///
3037 FailureOr<SmallVector<Value>> SoftmaxOp::decomposeOperation(OpBuilder &b) {
3038  OpBuilder::InsertionGuard guard(b);
3039  b.setInsertionPoint(*this);
3040  Location loc = getLoc();
3041  Value input = getInput();
3042  ShapedType inputType = getInputOperandType();
3043  Type elementType = inputType.getElementType();
3044  int64_t reductionDim = getDimension();
3045  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> dims = tensor::getMixedSizes(b, loc, input);
3046  Value output = getOutput();
3047  dims.erase(dims.begin() + reductionDim);
3048  // Step 1: Compute max along dim.
3049  Value outputReduce = tensor::EmptyOp::create(b, loc, dims, elementType);
3050  Value neutralForMaxF = arith::getIdentityValue(arith::AtomicRMWKind::maxnumf,
3051  elementType, b, loc,
3052  /*useOnlyFiniteValue=*/true);
3053  Value neutralForMaxFInit =
3054  linalg::FillOp::create(b, loc, Value{neutralForMaxF}, outputReduce)
3055  .result();
3056  Value max =
3057  reduce<arith::MaxNumFOp>(b, loc, input, neutralForMaxFInit, reductionDim);
3058 
3059  // Step 2: Subtract max from input and exponentiate.
3060  Value numerator = buildSubAndExpOp(b, loc, input, max, output, reductionDim);
3061 
3062  // Step 3: Compute sum along dim.
3063  Value zero = arith::getIdentityValue(arith::AtomicRMWKind::addf, elementType,
3064  b, loc, /*useOnlyFiniteValue=*/true);
3065  Value zeroInit =
3066  linalg::FillOp::create(b, loc, Value{zero}, outputReduce).result();
3067  Value denominator =
3068  reduce<arith::AddFOp>(b, loc, numerator, zeroInit, reductionDim);
3069 
3070  // Step 4: Compute softmax.
3071  Value result =
3072  buildDivOp(b, loc, numerator, denominator, output, reductionDim);
3073  return SmallVector<Value>{result};
3074 }

3080 LogicalResult WinogradFilterTransformOp::verify() {
3081  auto filterType = cast<ShapedType>(getFilter().getType());
3082  ArrayRef<int64_t> filterShape = filterType.getShape();
3083  int64_t filterH = filterShape[getFilterHDim()];
3084  int64_t filterW = filterShape[getFilterWDim()];
3085  WinogradConv2DFmr fmr = getFmr();
3086  int64_t m, r;
3087  std::tie(m, r) = getFmrFromWinogradConv2DFmr(fmr);
3088 
3089  if (filterH != r && filterH != 1)
3090  return emitOpError("expect filter height either equals to r or 1");
3091  if (filterW != r && filterW != 1)
3092  return emitOpError("expect filter width either equals to r or 1");
3093  if (filterH == 1 && filterW == 1)
3094  return emitOpError("expect either filter height or width equals to r");
3095 
3096  SmallVector<int64_t> expectedOutputShape;
3097  expectedOutputShape.push_back(filterH == r ? m + r - 1 : 1);
3098  expectedOutputShape.push_back(filterW == r ? m + r - 1 : 1);
3099  expectedOutputShape.push_back(filterShape[getFilterCDim()]);
3100  expectedOutputShape.push_back(filterShape[getFilterFDim()]);
3101 
3102  auto outputType = cast<ShapedType>(getOutput().getType());
3103  ArrayRef<int64_t> outputShape = outputType.getShape();
3104  if (failed(verifyCompatibleShape(expectedOutputShape, outputShape))) {
3105  return emitOpError("the output shape is not expected");
3106  }
3107  return success();
3108 }

3110 SmallVector<Range>
3111 WinogradFilterTransformOp::getIterationDomain(OpBuilder &builder) {
3112  Location loc = getLoc();
3113  IntegerAttr zeroAttr = builder.getIndexAttr(0);
3114  IntegerAttr oneAttr = builder.getIndexAttr(1);
3115  Value filter = getFilter();
3116  int64_t filterRank = getFilterOperandRank();
3117  SmallVector<Range> loopBounds(filterRank);
3118  for (unsigned dim = 0; dim < filterRank; ++dim) {
3119  loopBounds[dim].offset = zeroAttr;
3120  loopBounds[dim].size = getDimValue(builder, loc, filter, dim);
3121  loopBounds[dim].stride = oneAttr;
3122  }
3123  return loopBounds;
3124 }

3134 LogicalResult WinogradFilterTransformOp::getResultTilePosition(
3135  OpBuilder &builder, unsigned resultNumber, ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> offsets,
3136  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> sizes, SmallVector<OpFoldResult> &resultOffsets,
3137  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> &resultSizes) {
3138  IntegerAttr zeroAttr = builder.getI64IntegerAttr(0);
3139  ShapedType filterType = getFilterOperandType();
3140  ArrayRef<int64_t> filterShape = filterType.getShape();
3141  int64_t filterH = filterShape[getFilterHDim()];
3142  int64_t filterW = filterShape[getFilterWDim()];
3143  WinogradConv2DFmr fmr = getFmr();
3144  int64_t m, r;
3145  std::tie(m, r) = getFmrFromWinogradConv2DFmr(fmr);
3146  int64_t alpha = m + r - 1;
3147  int64_t alphaH = filterH != 1 ? alpha : 1;
3148  int64_t alphaW = filterW != 1 ? alpha : 1;
3149  IntegerAttr alphaHAttr = builder.getI64IntegerAttr(alphaH);
3150  IntegerAttr alphaWAttr = builder.getI64IntegerAttr(alphaW);
3151 
3152  resultOffsets.append(
3153  {zeroAttr, zeroAttr, offsets[getFilterCDim()], offsets[getFilterFDim()]});
3154  resultSizes.append(
3155  {alphaHAttr, alphaWAttr, sizes[getFilterCDim()], sizes[getFilterFDim()]});
3156 
3157  return success();
3158 }

3160 /// Implement tiling for winograd_filter_transform
3161 /// The input of winograd_filter_transform is (F, KH, KW, C).
3162 /// The output of winograd_filter_transform is (alphaH, alphaW, C, F)
3163 /// Users can specify the tile sizes of F and C.
3164 /// `offsets` are the values for the offsets of F, KH, KW, C for one tile.
3165 /// `sizes` are the values for the sizes of F, KH, KW, C for one tile.
3166 FailureOr<TilingResult> WinogradFilterTransformOp::getTiledImplementation(
3167  OpBuilder &builder, ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> offsets,
3168  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> sizes) {
3169  IntegerAttr oneAttr = builder.getI64IntegerAttr(1);
3170  IntegerAttr zeroAttr = builder.getI64IntegerAttr(0);
3171  ShapedType filterType = getFilterOperandType();
3172  ArrayRef<int64_t> filterShape = filterType.getShape();
3173  int64_t filterH = filterShape[getFilterHDim()];
3174  int64_t filterW = filterShape[getFilterWDim()];
3175  IntegerAttr filterHAttr = builder.getI64IntegerAttr(filterH);
3176  IntegerAttr filterWAttr = builder.getI64IntegerAttr(filterW);
3177  SmallVector<Value> tiledOperands;
3178  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> sliceOffsets, sliceSizes;
3179 
3180  sliceOffsets.append(
3181  {offsets[getFilterFDim()], zeroAttr, zeroAttr, offsets[getFilterCDim()]});
3182  sliceSizes.append({sizes[getFilterFDim()], filterHAttr, filterWAttr,
3183  sizes[getFilterCDim()]});
3184  int64_t filterRank = getFilterOperandRank();
3185  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> filterStrides(filterRank, oneAttr);
3186  Location loc = getLoc();
3187  auto filterSlice = tensor::ExtractSliceOp::create(
3188  builder, loc, getFilter(), sliceOffsets, sliceSizes, filterStrides);
3189  tiledOperands.emplace_back(filterSlice);
3190 
3191  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> resultOffsets, resultSizes;
3192  if (failed(getResultTilePosition(builder, 1, offsets, sizes, resultOffsets,
3193  resultSizes)))
3194  return failure();
3195 
3196  int64_t outputRank = getOutputOperandRank();
3197  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> outputStrides(outputRank, oneAttr);
3198  auto outputSlice = tensor::ExtractSliceOp::create(
3199  builder, loc, getOutput(), resultOffsets, resultSizes, outputStrides);
3200  tiledOperands.emplace_back(outputSlice);
3201 
3202  SmallVector<Type> resultTypes;
3203  resultTypes.push_back(tiledOperands[1].getType());
3204  Operation *tiledOp =
3205  mlir::clone(builder, getOperation(), resultTypes, tiledOperands);
3206 
3207  return TilingResult{
3208  {tiledOp},
3209  SmallVector<Value>(tiledOp->getResults()),
3210  llvm::to_vector(ArrayRef<Operation *>{filterSlice, outputSlice})};
3211 }

3217 LogicalResult WinogradInputTransformOp::verify() {
3218  auto inputType = cast<ShapedType>(getInput().getType());
3219  ArrayRef<int64_t> inputShape = inputType.getShape();
3220  int64_t inputH = inputShape[getInputHDim()];
3221  int64_t inputW = inputShape[getInputWDim()];
3222  WinogradConv2DFmr fmr = getFmr();
3223  int64_t m, r;
3224  std::tie(m, r) = getFmrFromWinogradConv2DFmr(fmr);
3225  int64_t tileSize = m + r - 1;
3226 
3227  auto outputType = cast<ShapedType>(getOutput().getType());
3228  ArrayRef<int64_t> outputShape = outputType.getShape();
3229  bool leftTransform = outputShape[getOutputAlphaHDim()] != 1;
3230  bool rightTransform = outputShape[getOutputAlphaWDim()] != 1;
3231 
3232  SmallVector<int64_t> expectedOutputShape(6, inputH);
3233  if (ShapedType::isDynamic(inputH)) {
3234  expectedOutputShape[getOutputAlphaHDim()] = tileSize;
3235  expectedOutputShape[getOutputTileHDim()] = ShapedType::kDynamic;
3236  } else {
3237  expectedOutputShape[getOutputAlphaHDim()] = leftTransform ? tileSize : 1;
3238  expectedOutputShape[getOutputTileHDim()] =
3239  leftTransform ? (inputH - (r - 1)) / m : inputH;
3240  }
3241  if (ShapedType::isDynamic(inputW)) {
3242  expectedOutputShape[getOutputAlphaWDim()] = tileSize;
3243  expectedOutputShape[getOutputTileWDim()] = ShapedType::kDynamic;
3244  } else {
3245  expectedOutputShape[getOutputAlphaWDim()] = rightTransform ? tileSize : 1;
3246  expectedOutputShape[getOutputTileWDim()] =
3247  rightTransform ? (inputW - (r - 1)) / m : inputW;
3248  }
3249  expectedOutputShape[getOutputNDim()] = inputShape[getInputNDim()];
3250  expectedOutputShape[getOutputCDim()] = inputShape[getInputCDim()];
3251 
3252  if (failed(verifyCompatibleShape(expectedOutputShape, outputShape))) {
3253  return emitOpError("the output shape is not expected");
3254  }
3255  return success();
3256 }

3313 /// Implement tiling for winograd_input_transform
3314 /// The input of winograd_input_transform is (N, H, W, C).
3315 /// The output of winograd_input_transform is (alphaH, alphaW, tileH, tileW, N,
3316 /// C) Users can specify the tile sizes of tileH, tileW, N, and C. `offsets` are
3317 /// the values for the offsets of tileH, tileW, N, C for one tile. `sizes` are
3318 /// the values for the sizes of tileH, tileW, N, C for one tile.
3319 FailureOr<TilingResult>
3320 WinogradInputTransformOp::getTiledImplementation(OpBuilder &builder,
3321  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> offsets,
3322  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> sizes) {
3323  IntegerAttr oneAttr = builder.getI64IntegerAttr(1);
3324  WinogradConv2DFmr fmr = getFmr();
3325  int64_t m, r;
3326  std::tie(m, r) = getFmrFromWinogradConv2DFmr(fmr);
3327 
3328  ShapedType outputType = getOutputOperandType();
3329  ArrayRef<int64_t> outputShape = outputType.getShape();
3330  int64_t alphaH = outputShape[getOutputAlphaHDim()];
3331  int64_t alphaW = outputShape[getOutputAlphaWDim()];
3332 
3333  Location loc = getLoc();
3334  MLIRContext *context = builder.getContext();
3335  auto identityAffineMap =
3336  AffineMap::get(1, 0, {builder.getAffineDimExpr(0)}, context);
3337  auto offsetAffineMap =
3338  AffineMap::get(1, 0, {builder.getAffineDimExpr(0) * m}, context);
3339  Value mappedOffsetH = affine::makeComposedAffineApply(
3340  builder, loc, (alphaH != 1 ? offsetAffineMap : identityAffineMap),
3341  offsets[getOutputTileHDim()]);
3342  Value mappedOffsetW = affine::makeComposedAffineApply(
3343  builder, loc, (alphaW != 1 ? offsetAffineMap : identityAffineMap),
3344  offsets[getOutputTileWDim()]);
3345  auto sizeAffineMap = AffineMap::get(
3346  1, 0, {builder.getAffineDimExpr(0) * m + (r - 1)}, context);
3347  Value mappedSizeH = affine::makeComposedAffineApply(
3348  builder, loc, sizeAffineMap, sizes[getOutputTileHDim()]);
3349  Value mappedSizeW = affine::makeComposedAffineApply(
3350  builder, loc, sizeAffineMap, sizes[getOutputTileWDim()]);
3351 
3352  SmallVector<Value> tiledOperands;
3353  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> sliceOffsets, sliceSizes;
3354 
3355  OpFoldResult offsetH = OpFoldResult(mappedOffsetH);
3356  OpFoldResult offsetW = OpFoldResult(mappedOffsetW);
3357  sliceOffsets.append(
3358  {offsets[getOutputNDim()], offsetH, offsetW, offsets[getOutputCDim()]});
3359  OpFoldResult sizeH =
3360  alphaH != 1 ? OpFoldResult(mappedSizeH) : OpFoldResult(oneAttr);
3361  OpFoldResult sizeW =
3362  alphaW != 1 ? OpFoldResult(mappedSizeW) : OpFoldResult(oneAttr);
3363  sliceSizes.append(
3364  {sizes[getOutputNDim()], sizeH, sizeW, sizes[getOutputCDim()]});
3365  int64_t inputRank = getInputOperandRank();
3366  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> inputStrides(inputRank, oneAttr);
3367  auto inputSlice = tensor::ExtractSliceOp::create(
3368  builder, loc, getInput(), sliceOffsets, sliceSizes, inputStrides);
3369  tiledOperands.emplace_back(inputSlice);
3370 
3371  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> resultOffsets, resultSizes;
3372  if (failed(getResultTilePosition(builder, 1, offsets, sizes, resultOffsets,
3373  resultSizes)))
3374  return failure();
3375 
3376  int64_t outputRank = getOutputOperandRank();
3377  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> outputStrides(outputRank, oneAttr);
3378  auto outputSlice = tensor::ExtractSliceOp::create(
3379  builder, loc, getOutput(), resultOffsets, resultSizes, outputStrides);
3380  tiledOperands.emplace_back(outputSlice);
3381 
3382  SmallVector<Type> resultTypes;
3383  resultTypes.push_back(tiledOperands[1].getType());
3384  Operation *tiledOp =
3385  mlir::clone(builder, getOperation(), resultTypes, tiledOperands);
3386 
3387  return TilingResult{
3388  {tiledOp},
3389  SmallVector<Value>(tiledOp->getResults()),
3390  llvm::to_vector(ArrayRef<Operation *>{inputSlice, outputSlice})};
3391 }
3392 
3393 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3394 // WinogradOutputTransformOp
3395 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3396 
3397 LogicalResult WinogradOutputTransformOp::verify() {
3398  auto valueType = cast<ShapedType>(getValue().getType());
3399  ArrayRef<int64_t> valueShape = valueType.getShape();
3400  int64_t valueH = valueShape[getValueAlphaHDim()];
3401  int64_t valueW = valueShape[getValueAlphaWDim()];
3402  int64_t valueTileH = valueShape[getValueTileHDim()];
3403  int64_t valueTileW = valueShape[getValueTileWDim()];
3404  WinogradConv2DFmr fmr = getFmr();
3405  int64_t m, r;
3406  std::tie(m, r) = getFmrFromWinogradConv2DFmr(fmr);
3407  bool leftTransform = valueH != 1;
3408  bool rightTransform = valueW != 1;
3409 
3410  int64_t outputRank = getOutputOperandRank();
3411  SmallVector<int64_t> expectedOutputShape(outputRank, valueH);
3412  if (ShapedType::isDynamic(valueH) || ShapedType::isDynamic(valueTileH)) {
3413  expectedOutputShape[getOutputHDim()] = ShapedType::kDynamic;
3414  } else {
3415  if (valueH != (leftTransform ? m + r - 1 : 1))
3416  return emitOpError("expect input height equals to input tile size");
3417  expectedOutputShape[getOutputHDim()] = (leftTransform ? m : 1) * valueTileH;
3418  }
3419  if (ShapedType::isDynamic(valueW) || ShapedType::isDynamic(valueTileW)) {
3420  expectedOutputShape[getOutputWDim()] = ShapedType::kDynamic;
3421  } else {
3422  if (valueW != (rightTransform ? m + r - 1 : 1))
3423  return emitOpError("expect input width equals to input tile size");
3424  expectedOutputShape[getOutputWDim()] =
3425  (rightTransform ? m : 1) * valueTileW;
3426  }
3427  expectedOutputShape[getOutputNDim()] = valueShape[getValueNDim()];
3428  expectedOutputShape[getOutputFDim()] = valueShape[getValueFDim()];
3429 
3430  auto outputType = cast<ShapedType>(getOutput().getType());
3431  ArrayRef<int64_t> outputShape = outputType.getShape();
3432  if (failed(verifyCompatibleShape(expectedOutputShape, outputShape))) {
3433  return emitOpError("the output shape is not expected");
3434  }
3435  return success();
3436 }
3437 
3438 SmallVector<Range>
3439 WinogradOutputTransformOp::getIterationDomain(OpBuilder &builder) {
3440  Location loc = getLoc();
3441  IntegerAttr zeroAttr = builder.getIndexAttr(0);
3442  IntegerAttr oneAttr = builder.getIndexAttr(1);
3443  Value value = getValue();
3444  int64_t valueRank = getValueOperandRank();
3445  SmallVector<Range> loopBounds(valueRank);
3446  for (unsigned dim = 0; dim < valueRank; ++dim) {
3447  loopBounds[dim].offset = zeroAttr;
3448  // alphaH, alphaW, tileH, tileW, N, F
3449  loopBounds[dim].size = getDimValue(builder, loc, value, dim);
3450  loopBounds[dim].stride = oneAttr;
3451  }
3452  return loopBounds;
3453 }

3455 SmallVector<utils::IteratorType>
3456 WinogradOutputTransformOp::getLoopIteratorTypes() {
3457  int64_t valueRank = getValueOperandRank();
3458  SmallVector<utils::IteratorType> iteratorTypes(valueRank,
3459  utils::IteratorType::parallel);
3460  return iteratorTypes;
3461 }
3462 
3463 LogicalResult WinogradOutputTransformOp::getResultTilePosition(
3464  OpBuilder &builder, unsigned resultNumber, ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> offsets,
3465  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> sizes, SmallVector<OpFoldResult> &resultOffsets,
3466  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> &resultSizes) {
3467  WinogradConv2DFmr fmr = getFmr();
3468  int64_t m, r;
3469  std::tie(m, r) = getFmrFromWinogradConv2DFmr(fmr);
3470 
3471  Location loc = getLoc();
3472  MLIRContext *context = builder.getContext();
3473  auto identityAffineMap =
3474  AffineMap::get(1, 0, {builder.getAffineDimExpr(0)}, context);
3475  auto affineMap =
3476  AffineMap::get(1, 0, {builder.getAffineDimExpr(0) * m}, context);
3477 
3478  ShapedType valueType = getValueOperandType();
3479  ArrayRef<int64_t> valueShape = valueType.getShape();
3480  int64_t valueH = valueShape[0];
3481  int64_t valueW = valueShape[1];
3482  Value mappedOffsetH = affine::makeComposedAffineApply(
3483  builder, loc, (valueH != 1 ? affineMap : identityAffineMap),
3484  offsets[getValueTileHDim()]);
3485  Value mappedOffsetW = affine::makeComposedAffineApply(
3486  builder, loc, (valueW != 1 ? affineMap : identityAffineMap),
3487  offsets[getValueTileWDim()]);
3488  Value mappedSizeH = affine::makeComposedAffineApply(
3489  builder, loc, affineMap, sizes[getValueTileHDim()]);
3490  Value mappedSizeW = affine::makeComposedAffineApply(
3491  builder, loc, affineMap, sizes[getValueTileWDim()]);
3492 
3493  IntegerAttr oneAttr = builder.getI64IntegerAttr(1);
3494  OpFoldResult offsetH = OpFoldResult(mappedOffsetH);
3495  OpFoldResult offsetW = OpFoldResult(mappedOffsetW);
3496  OpFoldResult sizeH =
3497  valueH != 1 ? OpFoldResult(mappedSizeH) : OpFoldResult(oneAttr);
3498  OpFoldResult sizeW =
3499  valueW != 1 ? OpFoldResult(mappedSizeW) : OpFoldResult(oneAttr);
3500 
3501  resultOffsets.append(
3502  {offsets[getValueNDim()], offsetH, offsetW, offsets[getValueFDim()]});
3503  resultSizes.append(
3504  {sizes[getValueNDim()], sizeH, sizeW, sizes[getValueFDim()]});
3505  return success();
3506 }
3507 
3508 /// Implement tiling for winograd_output_transform
3509 /// The input of winograd_output_transform is (alphaH, alphaW, tileH, tileW, N,
3510 /// F). The output of winograd_output_transform is (N, H, W, F) Users can
3511 /// specify the tile sizes of tileH, tileW, N, and F. `offsets` are the values
3512 /// for the offsets of tileH, tileW, N, F for one tile. `sizes` are the values
3513 /// for the sizes of tileH, tileW, N, F for one tile.
3514 FailureOr<TilingResult> WinogradOutputTransformOp::getTiledImplementation(
3515  OpBuilder &builder, ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> offsets,
3516  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> sizes) {
3517  IntegerAttr oneAttr = builder.getI64IntegerAttr(1);
3518  IntegerAttr zeroAttr = builder.getI64IntegerAttr(0);
3519  Location loc = getLoc();
3520  SmallVector<Value> tiledOperands;
3521  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> sliceOffsets, sliceSizes;
3522 
3523  ShapedType valueType = getValueOperandType();
3524  ArrayRef<int64_t> valueShape = valueType.getShape();
3525  int64_t alphaH = valueShape[getValueAlphaHDim()];
3526  int64_t alphaW = valueShape[getValueAlphaWDim()];
3527  IntegerAttr alphaHAttr = builder.getI64IntegerAttr(alphaH);
3528  IntegerAttr alphaWAttr = builder.getI64IntegerAttr(alphaW);
3529 
3530  sliceOffsets.append({zeroAttr, zeroAttr, offsets[getValueTileHDim()],
3531  offsets[getValueTileWDim()], offsets[getValueNDim()],
3532  offsets[getValueFDim()]});
3533  sliceSizes.append({alphaHAttr, alphaWAttr, sizes[getValueTileHDim()],
3534  sizes[getValueTileWDim()], sizes[getValueNDim()],
3535  sizes[getValueFDim()]});
3536  int64_t valueRank = getValueOperandRank();
3537  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> sliceStrides(valueRank, oneAttr);
3538  auto valueSlice = tensor::ExtractSliceOp::create(
3539  builder, loc, getValue(), sliceOffsets, sliceSizes, sliceStrides);
3540  tiledOperands.emplace_back(valueSlice);
3541 
3542  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> resultOffsets, resultSizes;
3543  if (failed(getResultTilePosition(builder, 1, offsets, sizes, resultOffsets,
3544  resultSizes)))
3545  return failure();
3546 
3547  int64_t outputRank = getOutputOperandRank();
3548  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> strides(outputRank, oneAttr);
3549  auto outputSlice = tensor::ExtractSliceOp::create(
3550  builder, loc, getOutput(), resultOffsets, resultSizes, strides);
3551  tiledOperands.emplace_back(outputSlice);
3552 
3553  SmallVector<Type> resultTypes;
3554  resultTypes.push_back(tiledOperands[1].getType());
3555  Operation *tiledOp =
3556  mlir::clone(builder, getOperation(), resultTypes, tiledOperands);
3557 
3558  return TilingResult{
3559  {tiledOp},
3560  SmallVector<Value>(tiledOp->getResults()),
3561  llvm::to_vector(ArrayRef<Operation *>{valueSlice, outputSlice})};
3562 }

3568 
3569 // Returns true if the result expression of `subMap` are a subset of `fullMap`.
3570 static bool areResultExprsSubsetOf(AffineMap subMap, AffineMap fullMap) {
3571  auto explicitRange = subMap.getResults();
3572  auto defaultRange = fullMap.getResults();
3573  DenseSet<AffineExpr> explicitSet(explicitRange.begin(), explicitRange.end());
3574  DenseSet<AffineExpr> defaultSet(defaultRange.begin(), defaultRange.end());
3575  llvm::set_union(explicitSet, defaultSet);
3576  return explicitSet == defaultSet;
3577 }
3578 
3579 /// Check if the user defined map is valid broadcast map. Here broadcast
3580 /// indexing maps are defined in context of corresponding default indexing maps
3581 /// for the given Op. This way the check becomes very simple i.e just check the
3582 /// number of result dims.
3583 /// Returns true if the explictMap is broadcasted with respect to the
3584 /// defaultMap.
3585 static bool isBroadcasted(AffineMap explictMap, AffineMap defaultMap) {
3586  return explictMap.getNumResults() < defaultMap.getNumResults();
3587 }
3588 
3589 /// Verifies the broadcast and transpose semantic sepecified by the explicit
3590 /// indexing map for the MatmulOp \p op for each operand specified by \p
3591 /// opIndex.
3592 static LogicalResult verifyExtendedMatmulSemantic(MatmulOp matmulOp,
3593  unsigned opIndex) {
3594  SmallVector<AffineMap, 3> opIndexingMaps = matmulOp.getIndexingMapsArray();
3595  SmallVector<AffineMap, 3> defaultIndexingMaps =
3596  matmulOp.getDefaultIndexingMaps(matmulOp->getContext());
3597 
3598  auto opIndexingMap = opIndexingMaps[opIndex];
3599  auto defaultIndexingMap = defaultIndexingMaps[opIndex];
3600  // Check general validity of indexing map results.
3601  if (!areResultExprsSubsetOf(opIndexingMap, defaultIndexingMap))
3602  return matmulOp->emitOpError()
3603  << "Unexpected dim expression in map result.";
3604 
3605  if (isBroadcasted(opIndexingMap, defaultIndexingMap)) {
3606  if (!matmulOp.isValidLhsRhsBroadcastMap(opIndexingMap)) {
3607  return matmulOp->emitOpError()
3608  << "Invalid broadcast requested, should be (d2).";
3609  }
3610  return success();
3611  }
3612  return success();
3613 }
3614 
3615 // Check general validity of input indexing map of
3616 // BatchMatmulOp/BatchReduceMatmulOp.
3617 template <typename OpTy>
3618 static LogicalResult verifyInputMaps(OpTy batchVariantMatmulOp,
3619  AffineMap opIndexingMap,
3620  AffineMap defaultIndexingMap, bool isLHS) {
3621  assert((isa<BatchMatmulOp>(batchVariantMatmulOp) ||
3622  isa<BatchReduceMatmulOp>(batchVariantMatmulOp)) &&
3623  "Expected BatchMatmulOp or BatchReduceMatmulOp");
3624  // Check the result dims are valid.
3625  if (!areResultExprsSubsetOf(opIndexingMap, defaultIndexingMap))
3626  return batchVariantMatmulOp->emitOpError()
3627  << "Unexpected result dim expression (outside the set of default "
3628  "result dims).";
3629 
3630  // Check for valid number of result dims of input maps.
3631  if (opIndexingMap.getNumResults() > 3)
3632  return batchVariantMatmulOp->emitOpError()
3633  << "no. of result dim expressions exceeds 3.";
3634 
3635  auto hasValidBatchDim = [](AffineMap map) {
3636  AffineExpr batchDim = map.getResult(0);
3637  return batchDim.isFunctionOfDim(0);
3638  };
3639 
3640  // Check if the requested broadcast is valid.
3641  if (isBroadcasted(opIndexingMap, defaultIndexingMap)) {
3642  if (!batchVariantMatmulOp.isValidLhsRhsBroadcastMap(opIndexingMap, isLHS))
3643  return batchVariantMatmulOp->emitOpError()
3644  << "Invalid broadcast requested.";
3645  } else if (!hasValidBatchDim(opIndexingMap)) {
3646  return batchVariantMatmulOp->emitOpError()
3647  << "Invalid batch dimension expression.";
3648  }
3649  return success();
3650 }
3651 
3652 /// This function checks if the given AffineMap for the output of a
3653 /// BatchMatmulOp/BatchReduceMatmulOp has exactly the desired number of result
3654 /// dimensions and if the output map result dimensions are valid.
3655 template <typename OpTy>
3656 static LogicalResult verifyOutputMap(OpTy batchVariantMatmulOp,
3657  AffineMap opIndexingMap) {
3658  assert((isa<BatchMatmulOp>(batchVariantMatmulOp) ||
3659  isa<BatchReduceMatmulOp>(batchVariantMatmulOp)) &&
3660  "Expected BatchMatmulOp or BatchReduceMatmulOp");
3661  if (isa<BatchMatmulOp>(batchVariantMatmulOp) &&
3662  opIndexingMap.getNumResults() != 3) {
3663 
3664  return batchVariantMatmulOp->emitOpError()
3665  << "expects 3 dims, but got (" << opIndexingMap.getNumResults()
3666  << ").";
3667  }
3668  if (isa<BatchReduceMatmulOp>(batchVariantMatmulOp) &&
3669  opIndexingMap.getNumResults() != 2) {
3670  return batchVariantMatmulOp->emitOpError()
3671  << "expects 2 dims, but got (" << opIndexingMap.getNumResults()
3672  << ").";
3673  }
3674 
3675  auto areValidOutputResultDim = [&](AffineMap outputMap) {
3676  return isa<BatchMatmulOp>(batchVariantMatmulOp)
3677  ? outputMap.getResult(0).isFunctionOfDim(0) &&
3678  outputMap.getResult(1).isFunctionOfDim(1) &&
3679  outputMap.getResult(2).isFunctionOfDim(2)
3680  : outputMap.getResult(0).isFunctionOfDim(1) &&
3681  outputMap.getResult(1).isFunctionOfDim(2);
3682  };
3683 
3684  if (!areValidOutputResultDim(opIndexingMap)) {
3685  return batchVariantMatmulOp->emitOpError()
3686  << "Invalid output map result dimension.";
3687  }
3688 
3689  return success();
3690 }
3691 
3692 /// Verifies the broadcast and transpose semantic specified by the explicit
3693 /// indexing map for the BatchMatmulOp/BatchReduceMatmulOp op for each operand
3694 /// specified by opIndex.
3695 template <typename OpTy>
3696 static LogicalResult
3697 verifyExtendedBatchVariantMatmulSemantic(OpTy batchVariantMatmulOp,
3698  unsigned opIndex) {
3699  SmallVector<AffineMap, 3> opIndexingMaps =
3700  batchVariantMatmulOp.getIndexingMapsArray();
3701  SmallVector<AffineMap, 3> defaultIndexingMaps =
3702  batchVariantMatmulOp.getDefaultIndexingMaps(
3703  batchVariantMatmulOp->getContext());
3704 
3705  if (opIndexingMaps.size() != 3)
3706  return batchVariantMatmulOp->emitOpError()
3707  << "Indexing_map attribute must have 3 affine maps.";
3708 
3709  auto opIndexingMap = opIndexingMaps[opIndex];
3710  auto defaultIndexingMap = defaultIndexingMaps[opIndex];
3711 
3712  if (opIndex == 2 &&
3713  failed(verifyOutputMap(batchVariantMatmulOp, opIndexingMap)))
3714  return failure();
3715 
3716  if (opIndex != 2 &&
3717  failed(verifyInputMaps(batchVariantMatmulOp, opIndexingMap,
3718  defaultIndexingMap, opIndex == 0)))
3719  return failure();
3720 
3721  return success();
3722 }

3727 std::optional<WinogradConv2DFmr> getWinogradConv2DFmr(int64_t m, int64_t r) {
3728  if (m == 2 && r == 3)
3729  return WinogradConv2DFmr::F_2_3;
3730  if (m == 4 && r == 3)
3731  return WinogradConv2DFmr::F_4_3;
3732  if (m == 2 && r == 5)
3733  return WinogradConv2DFmr::F_2_5;
3734  return std::nullopt;
3735 }
3736 
3737 std::pair<int64_t, int64_t> getFmrFromWinogradConv2DFmr(WinogradConv2DFmr fmr) {
3738  switch (fmr) {
3739  case WinogradConv2DFmr::F_2_3:
3740  return {2, 3};
3741  case WinogradConv2DFmr::F_4_3:
3742  return {4, 3};
3743  case WinogradConv2DFmr::F_2_5:
3744  return {2, 5};
3745  }
3746 }

3752 /// Returns a list of AffineMap with the typical matmul indexing charactristic.
3753 SmallVector<AffineMap> MatmulOp::getDefaultIndexingMaps(MLIRContext *context) {
3754  AffineExpr d0, d1, d2;
3755  SmallVector<AffineMap> indexingMaps;
3756  bindDims(context, d0, d1, d2);
3757  indexingMaps.push_back(AffineMap::get(3, 0, {d0, d2}, context));
3758  indexingMaps.push_back(AffineMap::get(3, 0, {d2, d1}, context));
3759  indexingMaps.push_back(AffineMap::get(3, 0, {d0, d1}, context));
3760  return indexingMaps;
3761 }

3775 bool MatmulOp::hasDynamicIndexingMaps() { return true; }

3777 /// Check if the op has broadcast and/or transpose semantic. Returns true if
3778 /// the user defined indexing maps are not equal to default map.
3779 bool MatmulOp::hasUserDefinedMaps() {
3780  SmallVector<AffineMap, 3> defaultMaps =
3781  getDefaultIndexingMaps(this->getContext());
3782  SmallVector<AffineMap, 3> explicitMaps = getIndexingMapsArray();
3783  return defaultMaps != explicitMaps;
3784 }
3785 
3786 /// Implements the block region builder for the MatmulOp. This is called by
3787 /// 'fillStructuredOpRegion'.
3788 void MatmulOp::regionBuilder(ImplicitLocOpBuilder &b, Block &block,
3789  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attrs,
3790  function_ref<InFlightDiagnostic()> emitError) {
3791  if (emitError && block.getNumArguments() != 3) {
3792  emitError() << "MatmulOp regionBuilder expects 3 args, got "
3793  << block.getNumArguments();
3794  return;
3795  }
3796  assert(block.getNumArguments() == 3 &&
3797  "MatmulOp regionBuilder expects 3 args");
3798  RegionBuilderHelper helper(b, block);
3799  SmallVector<Value> yields;
3800 
3801  TypeFn castVal = TypeFn::cast_signed;
3802  const auto *castIter = llvm::find_if(attrs, [&](const NamedAttribute &attr) {
3803  return attr.getName() == "cast";
3804  });
3805  if (castIter != attrs.end()) {
3806  if (auto attr = llvm::dyn_cast<TypeFnAttr>(castIter->getValue()))
3807  castVal = attr.getValue();
3808  }
3809 
3810  Value value1 = helper.buildTypeFn(castVal, block.getArgument(2).getType(),
3811  block.getArgument(0));
3812  Value value2 = helper.buildTypeFn(castVal, block.getArgument(2).getType(),
3813  block.getArgument(1));
3814  Value value3 = helper.buildBinaryFn(BinaryFn::mul, value1, value2, emitError);
3815  if (!value3)
3816  return;
3817  Value value4 = helper.buildBinaryFn(BinaryFn::add, block.getArgument(2),
3818  value3, emitError);
3819  if (!value4)
3820  return;
3821  yields.push_back(value4);
3822  helper.yieldOutputs(yields);
3823 }
3824 
3825 /// Returns true if the given bcastMap map is a valid broadcast map. A valid
3826 /// broadcast map must include K dimension.
3827 /// TODO: Strict inclusion of K dimension in the broadcast map is not
3828 /// necessary for both input matrices simultaneously. We can relax this
3829 /// condition to have K dimension for one input matrix map and infer the K
3830 /// dimension for other input matrix map from the one already having K
3831 /// dimension.
3832 bool MatmulOp::isValidLhsRhsBroadcastMap(AffineMap bcastMap) {
3833  assert(bcastMap.getNumResults() == 1 && "Expected single result dim expr.");
3834  AffineExpr expr = bcastMap.getResult(0);
3835  // Invalid map if the common dimension of matmul not found.
3836  return expr.isFunctionOfDim(bcastMap.getNumDims() - 1);
3837 }
3838 
3839 FailureOr<ArrayAttr> parseIndexingMapsAttr(OpAsmParser &parser) {
3840  if (parser.parseOptionalKeyword("indexing_maps"))
3841  return ArrayAttr{
3842  nullptr}; // Success in case indexing_maps was not provided.
3843 
3844  ArrayAttr arrayAttr;
3845  if (parser.parseEqual() || parser.parseAttribute(arrayAttr))
3846  return failure();
3847 
3848  if (llvm::any_of(arrayAttr,
3849  [](auto elt) { return !dyn_cast<AffineMapAttr>(elt); }))
3850  return parser.emitError(parser.getCurrentLocation())
3851  << "element of indexing_maps array is not an affine_map";
3852 
3853  return arrayAttr;
3854 }
3855 
3856 ParseResult MatmulOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
3857  FailureOr<ArrayAttr> indexingMapsAttr = parseIndexingMapsAttr(parser);
3858  if (failed(indexingMapsAttr))
3859  return failure();
3860 
3861  if (*indexingMapsAttr == nullptr) {
3862  auto indexingMapAttrs = llvm::map_to_vector(
3863  MatmulOp::getDefaultIndexingMaps(parser.getContext()),
3864  [](AffineMap map) -> Attribute { return AffineMapAttr::get(map); });
3865  indexingMapsAttr = parser.getBuilder().getArrayAttr(indexingMapAttrs);
3866  }
3867 
3868  result.addAttribute("indexing_maps", *indexingMapsAttr);
3869  return parseNamedStructuredOp(parser, result, MatmulOp::getNumRegionArgs(),
3870  MatmulOp::getRegionBuilder());
3871 }
3872 
3873 void MatmulOp::print(OpAsmPrinter &p) {
3874  SmallVector<Attribute, 3> indexingMaps = llvm::map_to_vector<3>(
3875  MatmulOp::getDefaultIndexingMaps(getContext()),
3876  [](AffineMap map) -> Attribute { return AffineMapAttr::get(map); });
3877  if (!llvm::equal(getIndexingMaps(), indexingMaps))
3878  p << " indexing_maps = " << llvm::interleaved_array(getIndexingMaps());
3879 
3880  std::array<StringRef, 3> elidedAttrs = {
3881  "operandSegmentSizes", "linalg.memoized_indexing_maps", "indexing_maps"};
3882  printNamedStructuredOp(p, getOperation(), getInputs(), getOutputs(),
3883  elidedAttrs);
3884 }
3885 
3886 /// Verify the user defined indexing maps.
3887 LogicalResult MatmulOp::verify() {
3888  // Verification of pure matmul is handled by verifyStructuredOpInterface().
3889  if (!hasUserDefinedMaps())
3890  return success();
3891 
3892  for (unsigned opIndex = 0; opIndex < 2; opIndex++) {
3893  if (failed(verifyExtendedMatmulSemantic(*this, opIndex)))
3894  return failure();
3895  }
3896  return success();
3897 }

3912  return getGenericSpeculatabilityImpl(cast<LinalgOp>(getOperation()));
3913 }
3914 
3915 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3916 // ContractOp
3917 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
3918 
3919 SmallVector<utils::IteratorType> ContractOp::getIteratorTypesArray() {
3920  AffineMap outAffineMap = getIndexingMapsArray().pop_back_val();
3921  // On well-formed IR, indexing_maps is non-empty, contained affine_maps'
3922  // domains are all the same, and each implements a projected permutation.
3923  // Each iteration space dim must occur for at least one operand and either
3924  // takes part in a contraction/reduction or else has parallel iteration type.
3925  // We have that a dim is a contraction/reduction dim if and only if the dim
3926  // occurs for the output operand. We use this fact for fast inference:
3927  // NB: In case we allow dims to occur solely for one input, the above still
3928  // holds: per the einsum semantics, these are reduction dims as well.
3929  SmallVector<bool> dimsInOutput(outAffineMap.getNumDims(), false);
3930  for (auto result : outAffineMap.getResults()) {
3931  auto dimExpr = dyn_cast<AffineDimExpr>(result);
3932  assert(dimExpr && "affine_map is a projected permutation");
3933  dimsInOutput[dimExpr.getPosition()] = true;
3934  }
3935 
3936  SmallVector<utils::IteratorType> iteratorTypes;
3937  for (auto dimOccursInOutput : dimsInOutput)
3938  iteratorTypes.push_back(dimOccursInOutput ? utils::IteratorType::parallel
3939  : utils::IteratorType::reduction);
3940 
3941  return iteratorTypes;
3942 }
3943 
3944 unsigned ContractOp::getNumRegionArgs() { return 3; }
3945 
3946 /// Implement block region builder, which is called by 'fillStructuredOpRegion'.
3947 void ContractOp::regionBuilder(ImplicitLocOpBuilder &b, Block &block,
3948  ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attrs,
3949  function_ref<InFlightDiagnostic()> emitError) {
3950  if (emitError && block.getNumArguments() != 3) {
3951  emitError() << "ContractOp regionBuilder expects 3 args, got "
3952  << block.getNumArguments();
3953  return;
3954  }
3955  assert(block.getNumArguments() == 3 &&
3956  "ContractOp regionBuilder expects 3 args");
3957  RegionBuilderHelper helper(b, block);
3958 
3959  TypeFn castSignedness = TypeFn::cast_signed;
3960  auto castIter = llvm::find_if(attrs, [&](const NamedAttribute &attr) {
3961  return attr.getName() == "cast";
3962  });
3963  if (castIter != attrs.end()) {
3964  if (auto attr = llvm::dyn_cast<TypeFnAttr>(castIter->getValue()))
3965  castSignedness = attr.getValue();
3966  }
3967 
3968  // TODO: Support fields with operators besides mult & add.
3969  Type outType = block.getArgument(2).getType();
3970  Value lhsAtOutType =
3971  helper.buildTypeFn(castSignedness, outType, block.getArgument(0));
3972  Value rhsAtOutType =
3973  helper.buildTypeFn(castSignedness, outType, block.getArgument(1));
3974  Value productAtOutType = helper.buildBinaryFn(BinaryFn::mul, lhsAtOutType,
3975  rhsAtOutType, emitError);
3976  if (!productAtOutType)
3977  return;
3978  Value result = helper.buildBinaryFn(BinaryFn::add, block.getArgument(2),
3979  productAtOutType, emitError);
3980  if (!result)
3981  return;
3982  helper.yieldOutputs({result});
3983 }

3985 ParseResult ContractOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
3986  FailureOr<ArrayAttr> indexingMapsAttr = parseIndexingMapsAttr(parser);
3987  if (failed(indexingMapsAttr) || *indexingMapsAttr == nullptr)
3988  return parser.emitError(parser.getCurrentLocation(),
3989  "expected 'indexing_maps' attribute");
3990  result.addAttribute("indexing_maps", *indexingMapsAttr);
3991 
3992  return parseNamedStructuredOp(parser, result, getNumRegionArgs(),
3993  regionBuilder);
3994 }

4000  /*elidedAttrs=*/{"indexing_maps", "operandSegmentSizes"});

4002 
4003 LogicalResult ContractOp::verify() {
4004  int iterationSpaceDims = -1;
4005  // Map iter space dims to #occurrences in inputs' and output's affine_maps:
4006  // e.g., inOccurrences[0] will hold #times that dim (with index) 0 is used to
4007  // access an input operand (so occurrence count can be at most 2) and
4008  // outOccurrences[1] will indicate whether dim 1 occurred in the output, etc.
4009  SmallVector<size_t> inOccurrences;
4010  SmallVector<size_t> outOccurrences;
4011 
4012  // A helper so that for each operand's affine_map and type we check that ...
4013  auto checkAffineMapAndType = [&](AffineMap affineMap, Type operandType,
4014  bool isInput) -> LogicalResult {
4015  // ... the affine_map is a projected permutation;
4016  if (!affineMap.isProjectedPermutation())
4017  return emitError("provided affine_map is not a projected permutation");
4018 
4019  // ... the rank of the affine_map's results and corresponding type match;
4020  if (auto shapedType = dyn_cast<ShapedType>(operandType)) {
4021  if (affineMap.getNumResults() != shapedType.getRank())
4022  return emitError("ranks of shaped operand and results of corresponding "
4023  "affine_map differ");
4024  } else if (affineMap.getNumResults() != 0) {
4025  return emitError("affine_map specifies shaped access while operand has "
4026  "non-shaped type");
4027  }
4028 
4029  // ... the rank of the affine_map's domain is the same as those seen prior;
4030  if (iterationSpaceDims == -1) {
4031  iterationSpaceDims = affineMap.getNumDims();
4032  inOccurrences = SmallVector<size_t>(iterationSpaceDims, 0);
4033  outOccurrences = SmallVector<size_t>(iterationSpaceDims, 0);
4034  } else if (iterationSpaceDims != (int)affineMap.getNumDims()) {
4035  return emitError("iteration spaces of provided affine_maps differ");
4036  }
4037 
4038  // ... update counts of dims used to access either an input or the output.
4039  for (AffineExpr affineExpr : affineMap.getResults()) {
4040  auto affineDimExpr = dyn_cast<AffineDimExpr>(affineExpr);
4041  if (!affineDimExpr)
4042  llvm_unreachable("affine_map is a projected permutation");
4043 
4044  if (isInput)
4045  inOccurrences[affineDimExpr.getPosition()] += 1;
4046  else
4047  outOccurrences[affineDimExpr.getPosition()] += 1;
4048  }
4049 
4050  return success();
4051  };
4052 
4053  for (auto &&[affineMap, operandType, isInput] :
4054  llvm::zip(getIndexingMapsArray(), getOperandTypes(),
4055  SmallVector<bool>{true, true, false})) {
4056  if (failed(checkAffineMapAndType(affineMap, operandType, isInput)))
4057  return failure(); // NB: checkAffineMapAndType will emit relevant error.
4058  }
4059 
4060  bool hasContractingDim = false;
4061  for (size_t dimIndex = 0; dimIndex < (size_t)iterationSpaceDims; dimIndex++) {
4062  size_t inOccCount = inOccurrences[dimIndex];
4063  size_t outOccCount = outOccurrences[dimIndex];
4064 
4065  // We have a contracting dim if and only if ...
4066  hasContractingDim |= inOccCount == 2 && outOccCount == 0;
4067 
4068  if (inOccCount == 0 && outOccCount == 0)
4069  return emitError() << "iteration space dim at index " << dimIndex
4070  << " not used to access any operand";
4071 
4072  // NB: We disallow a dim which occurs for only one input operand and not
4073  // for the output. In terms of einsum semantics such dims have a
4074  // sensible meaning - namely an additional reduction per each such dim.
4075  // By contrast, the ContractionOpInterface does not know about this
4076  // iter type - cf. inferContractionDims' supported dim kinds. Similarly,
4077  // while vector.contract's verifier accepts dims of this kind many of
4078  // its lowerings give up on encountering these dims.
4079  // TODO: Remove following once we have comprehensive support for input-only
4080  // reduction dims, at both the linalg- and vector-dialect levels.
4081  if (inOccCount == 1 && outOccCount != 1)
4082  return emitError()
4083  << "iteration space dim at index " << dimIndex
4084  << " is neither a contracting dim nor of parallel iteration type";
4085  }
4086 
4087  if (!hasContractingDim)
4088  return emitError("'indexing_maps' do not specify a contracting dimension");
4089 
4090  return success();
4091 }

4094  return memref::foldMemRefCast(*this);
4095 }

4112 SmallVector<AffineMap>
4113 BatchMatmulOp::getDefaultIndexingMaps(MLIRContext *context) {
4114  AffineExpr d0, d1, d2, d3;
4115  SmallVector<AffineMap> indexingMaps;
4116  bindDims(context, d0, d1, d2, d3);
4117  indexingMaps.push_back(AffineMap::get(4, 0, {d0, d1, d3}, context));
4118  indexingMaps.push_back(AffineMap::get(4, 0, {d0, d3, d2}, context));
4119  indexingMaps.push_back(AffineMap::get(4, 0, {d0, d1, d2}, context));
4120  return indexingMaps;
4121 }

4135 /// Check if the op has broadcast and/or transpose semantic. Returns true if
4136 /// the user defined indexing maps are not equal to default map.
4137 bool BatchMatmulOp::hasUserDefinedMaps() {
4138  SmallVector<AffineMap, 3> defaultMaps =
4139  getDefaultIndexingMaps(this->getContext());
4140  SmallVector<AffineMap, 3> explicitMaps = getIndexingMapsArray();
4141  return defaultMaps != explicitMaps;
4142 }
4143 
4144 /// Returns true if the given bcastMap map is a valid broadcast map. A valid
4145 /// broadcast map must include K dimension.
4146 /// TODO: Strict inclusion of K dimension in the broadcast map is not
4147 /// necessary for both input matrices simultaneously. We can relax this
4148 /// condition to have K dimension for one input matrix map and infer the K
4149 /// dimension for other input matrix map from the one already having K
4150 /// dimension.
4151 bool BatchMatmulOp::isValidLhsRhsBroadcastMap(AffineMap bcastMap, bool isLHS) {
4152  assert(bcastMap.getNumResults() < 3 &&
4153  "Expected less than 3 result dim expr.");
4154  bool isValid = false;
4155  enum Indices { batchPos, mPos, nPos, kPos };
4156  if (bcastMap.getNumResults() == 1) {
4157  AffineExpr expr = bcastMap.getResult(0);
4158  isValid = expr.isFunctionOfDim(kPos);
4159  } else if (bcastMap.getNumResults() == 2) {
4160  AffineExpr expr0 = bcastMap.getResult(0);
4161  AffineExpr expr1 = bcastMap.getResult(1);
4162  isValid =
4163  isLHS ? ((expr0.isFunctionOfDim(batchPos) ||
4164  expr0.isFunctionOfDim(mPos)) &&
4165  expr1.isFunctionOfDim(kPos))
4166  : ((expr0.isFunctionOfDim(batchPos) &&
4167  expr1.isFunctionOfDim(kPos)) ||
4168  (expr0.isFunctionOfDim(kPos) && expr1.isFunctionOfDim(nPos)));
4169  }
4170  return isValid;
4171 }
4172 
4173 void BatchMatmulOp::regionBuilder(
4174  ImplicitLocOpBuilder &b, Block &block, ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attrs,
4175  function_ref<InFlightDiagnostic()> emitError) {
4176  if (emitError && block.getNumArguments() != 3) {
4177  emitError() << "BatchMatmulOp regionBuilder expects 3 args, got "
4178  << block.getNumArguments();
4179  return;
4180  }
4181  assert(block.getNumArguments() == 3 &&
4182  "BatchMatmulOp regionBuilder expects 3 args");
4183  RegionBuilderHelper helper(b, block);
4184  SmallVector<Value> yields;
4185 
4186  TypeFn castVal = TypeFn::cast_signed;
4187  auto castIter = llvm::find_if(attrs, [&](const NamedAttribute &attr) {
4188  return attr.getName() == "cast";
4189  });
4190  if (castIter != attrs.end()) {
4191  if (auto attr = llvm::dyn_cast<TypeFnAttr>(castIter->getValue()))
4192  castVal = attr.getValue();
4193  }
4194 
4195  auto toType = block.getArgument(2).getType();
4196  Value castValA = helper.buildTypeFn(castVal, toType, block.getArgument(0));
4197  Value castValB = helper.buildTypeFn(castVal, toType, block.getArgument(1));
4198  Value mulVal = helper.buildBinaryFn(BinaryFn::mul, castValA, castValB);
4199  Value addVal =
4200  helper.buildBinaryFn(BinaryFn::add, block.getArgument(2), mulVal);
4201  yields.push_back(addVal);
4202  helper.yieldOutputs(yields);
4203 }

4205 ParseResult BatchMatmulOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
4206  SmallVector<Attribute, 3> indexingMapsAttr;
4207  Attribute mapAttr;
4208  if (succeeded(parser.parseOptionalKeyword("indexing_maps"))) {
4209  if (parser.parseEqual())
4210  return failure();
4211 
4212  if (parser.parseLSquare())
4213  return failure();
4214 
4215  do {
4216  if (parser.parseAttribute(mapAttr))
4217  return failure();
4218  if (!isa<AffineMapAttr>(mapAttr)) {
4219  return parser.emitError(parser.getCurrentLocation(),
4220  "expected affine map attribute");
4221  }
4222  indexingMapsAttr.push_back(mapAttr);
4223 
4224  if (parser.parseOptionalComma())
4225  break;
4226  } while (true);
4227 
4228  if (parser.parseRSquare())
4229  return failure();
4230  }
4231  // Initialize indexingMaps, if not supplied explicitly.
4232  if (indexingMapsAttr.empty()) {
4233  indexingMapsAttr = llvm::map_to_vector(
4234  BatchMatmulOp::getDefaultIndexingMaps(parser.getContext()),
4235  [](AffineMap map) -> Attribute { return AffineMapAttr::get(map); });
4236  }
4237  result.addAttribute("indexing_maps",
4238  parser.getBuilder().getArrayAttr(indexingMapsAttr));
4239 
4240  return ::parseNamedStructuredOp(parser, result,
4241  BatchMatmulOp::getNumRegionArgs(),
4242  BatchMatmulOp::getRegionBuilder());
4243 }

4247  BatchMatmulOp::getDefaultIndexingMaps(getContext()),
4248  [](AffineMap map) -> Attribute { return AffineMapAttr::get(map); });
4249  if (!llvm::equal(getIndexingMaps(), indexingMaps))
4250  p << " indexing_maps = " << llvm::interleaved_array(getIndexingMaps());
4251 
4252  std::array<StringRef, 3> elidedAttrs = {
4253  "operandSegmentSizes", "linalg.memoized_indexing_maps", "indexing_maps"};
4254  ::printNamedStructuredOp(p, getOperation(), getInputs(), getOutputs(),
4255  elidedAttrs);
4256 }

4289 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4290 // ElementwiseOp
4291 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

4293 namespace {
4294 struct ArityGroupAndKind {
4295  // The enum class {Unary, Binary, Ternary, ..}
4296  ElementwiseArityGroup arityGroup;
4297 
4298  // The kind (e.g. `exp` or `add`) belonging to the arity group.
4299  union Kind {
4300  UnaryFn unaryFn;
4301  BinaryFn binaryFn;
4302  TernaryFn ternaryFn;
4303  } kind;
4304 };
4305 
4306 unsigned getArityGroupAsUInt(ElementwiseArityGroup arityGroup) {
4307  return static_cast<unsigned>(arityGroup);
4308 }
4309 } // namespace
4310 
4311 static ArityGroupAndKind getArityGroupAndKind(ElementwiseKind kind) {
4312  constexpr int lastUnary = static_cast<int>(ElementwiseCaseLimits::LastUnary);
4313  constexpr int lastBinary =
4314  static_cast<int>(ElementwiseCaseLimits::LastBinary);
4315  constexpr int lastTernary =
4316  static_cast<int>(ElementwiseCaseLimits::LastTernary);
4317 
4318  int val = static_cast<int>(kind);
4319  ArityGroupAndKind result;
4320 
4321  if (val < lastUnary) {
4322  result.arityGroup = ElementwiseArityGroup::Unary;
4323  result.kind.unaryFn = static_cast<UnaryFn>(val);
4324  return result;
4325  }
4326  if (val < lastBinary) {
4327  result.arityGroup = ElementwiseArityGroup::Binary;
4328  result.kind.binaryFn = static_cast<BinaryFn>(val - lastUnary);
4329  return result;
4330  }
4331  if (val >= lastTernary) {
4332  llvm_unreachable("unhandled ElementwiseFn");
4333  }
4334  result.arityGroup = ElementwiseArityGroup::Ternary;
4335  result.kind.ternaryFn = static_cast<TernaryFn>(val - lastBinary);
4336  return result;
4337 }
4338 
4339 SmallVector<utils::IteratorType> ElementwiseOp::getIteratorTypesArray() {
4340  auto rank = getResultRank();
4341  return SmallVector<utils::IteratorType>(rank, utils::IteratorType::parallel);
4342 }
