4344 SmallVector<AffineMap>
4345 ElementwiseOp::getDefaultIndexingMaps(unsigned numMaps, unsigned numDims,
4346  MLIRContext *context) {
4347  auto map = AffineMap::getMultiDimIdentityMap(numDims, context);
4348  return SmallVector<AffineMap>(numMaps, map);
4349 }
4350 
4351 ParseResult ElementwiseOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser, OperationState &result) {
4352  // Expect e.g. `kind = #linalg.elemwise_kind<add>`
4353  Attribute attr;
4354  mlir::linalg::ElementwiseKind elemwiseKindVal;
4355  if (parser.parseKeyword("kind") || parser.parseEqual())
4356  return failure();
4357 
4358  if (succeeded(parser.parseAttribute(attr))) {
4359  auto elemwiseKindAttr = dyn_cast<ElementwiseKindAttr>(attr);
4360  if (!elemwiseKindAttr)
4361  return parser.emitError(parser.getCurrentLocation(),
4362  "expected ElementwiseKind attribute");
4363  elemwiseKindVal = elemwiseKindAttr.getValue();
4364  } else {
4365  return parser.emitError(parser.getCurrentLocation(),
4366  "expected operation 'kind' attribute");
4367  }
4368  result.addAttribute(
4369  "kind", ElementwiseKindAttr::get(parser.getContext(), elemwiseKindVal));
4370 
4371  // Parse optional `indexing_maps`
4372  SmallVector<Attribute, 3> indexingMapsAttr;
4373  Attribute mapAttr;
4374  if (succeeded(parser.parseOptionalKeyword("indexing_maps"))) {
4375  if (parser.parseEqual())
4376  return failure();
4377  if (parser.parseLSquare())
4378  return failure();
4379  do {
4380  if (parser.parseAttribute(mapAttr))
4381  return failure();
4382  if (!isa<AffineMapAttr>(mapAttr))
4383  return parser.emitError(parser.getCurrentLocation(),
4384  "expected affine map attribute");
4385  indexingMapsAttr.push_back(mapAttr);
4386  if (parser.parseOptionalComma())
4387  break;
4388  } while (true);
4389  if (parser.parseRSquare())
4390  return failure();
4391  }
4392  // At this stage of parsing the only way to infer number of region
4393  // args is through op kind, as input output tensors are not parsed yet.
4394  auto arityGroupAndKind = getArityGroupAndKind(elemwiseKindVal);
4395  int numRegionArgs =
4396  getArityGroupAsUInt(arityGroupAndKind.arityGroup) + 1 /*output*/;
4397  if (parseNamedStructuredOp(parser, result, numRegionArgs,
4398  ElementwiseOp::getRegionBuilder())) {
4399  return parser.emitError(parser.getCurrentLocation(),
4400  "unable to parse elemwise op");
4401  }
4402 
4403  // Initialize indexingMaps, if not supplied explicitly.
4404  if (indexingMapsAttr.empty()) {
4405  // We need to infer the numDims of the indexing maps from the output
4406  // type which is already parsed by now.
4407  auto resultType = result.operands[result.operands.size() - 1].getType();
4408  auto shapedType = llvm::dyn_cast<ShapedType>(resultType);
4409  if (!shapedType)
4410  return parser.emitError(parser.getCurrentLocation(),
4411  "return type needs to be shaped type");
4412  auto numDims = shapedType.getRank();
4413  indexingMapsAttr = llvm::map_to_vector(
4414  ElementwiseOp::getDefaultIndexingMaps(numRegionArgs, numDims,
4415  parser.getContext()),
4416  [](AffineMap map) -> Attribute { return AffineMapAttr::get(map); });
4417  }
4418 
4419  result.addAttribute("indexing_maps",
4420  parser.getBuilder().getArrayAttr(indexingMapsAttr));
4421  return success();
4422 }
4423 
4424 void ElementwiseOp::print(OpAsmPrinter &p) {
4425  p << " kind=";
4426  p.printAttribute(getKindAttr());
4427  SmallVector<StringRef, 3> elidedAttrs = {"operandSegmentSizes", "kind",
4428  "indexing_maps"};
4429  unsigned arity =
4430  getArityGroupAsUInt(getArityGroupAndKind(getKind()).arityGroup);
4431  unsigned numDims = getResultRank();
4432 
4433  SmallVector<Attribute, 3> indexingMaps = llvm::map_to_vector<3>(
4434  ElementwiseOp::getDefaultIndexingMaps(arity + 1 /*output*/, numDims,
4435  getContext()),
4436  [](AffineMap map) -> Attribute { return AffineMapAttr::get(map); });
4437 
4438  if (!llvm::equal(getIndexingMaps(), indexingMaps))
4439  p << " indexing_maps = " << llvm::interleaved_array(getIndexingMaps());
4440 
4441  printNamedStructuredOp(p, getOperation(), getInputs(), getOutputs(),
4442  elidedAttrs);
4443 }
4444 
4445 LogicalResult ElementwiseOp::verify() {
4446  // All necessary checks are done either by
4447  // - EnumAttr (e.g. unknown operation kind)
4448  // - verifyStructuredOpInterface (incorrect map, sizes).
4449  return success();
4450 }
4451 
4452 /// Implements the block region builder for the ElementwiseOp. This is called by
4453 /// 'fillStructuredOpRegion'.
4454 void ElementwiseOp::regionBuilder(
4455  ImplicitLocOpBuilder &b, Block &block, ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attrs,
4456  function_ref<InFlightDiagnostic()> emitError) {
4457  ElementwiseKind elemwiseKind;
4458  for (auto attr : attrs) {
4459  if (attr.getName() == b.getStringAttr("kind")) {
4460  auto kindAttr = dyn_cast<ElementwiseKindAttr>(attr.getValue());
4461  assert(kindAttr && "op kind attribute incorrectly set");
4462  elemwiseKind = kindAttr.getValue();
4463  break;
4464  }
4465  }
4466 
4467  ArityGroupAndKind groupAndKind = getArityGroupAndKind(elemwiseKind);
4468  auto arityGroup = groupAndKind.arityGroup;
4469  auto kind = groupAndKind.kind;
4470  if (emitError && block.getNumArguments() !=
4471  getArityGroupAsUInt(arityGroup) + 1 /*output*/) {
4472  emitError() << "Elementwise regionBuilder expects "
4473  << (getArityGroupAsUInt(arityGroup) + 1) << " args, got "
4474  << block.getNumArguments();
4475  return;
4476  }
4477  assert(block.getNumArguments() ==
4478  getArityGroupAsUInt(arityGroup) + 1 /*output*/
4479  && "Elementwise regionBuilder number of block args mismatch");
4480 
4481  RegionBuilderHelper helper(b, block);
4482  SmallVector<Value> yields;
4483  Value result;
4484 
4485  if (arityGroup == ElementwiseArityGroup::Unary) {
4486  result = helper.buildUnaryFn(kind.unaryFn, block.getArgument(0));
4487 
4488  } else if (arityGroup == ElementwiseArityGroup::Binary) {
4489  result = helper.buildBinaryFn(kind.binaryFn, block.getArgument(0),
4490  block.getArgument(1));
4491 
4492  } else if (arityGroup == ElementwiseArityGroup::Ternary) {
4493  result = helper.buildTernaryFn(kind.ternaryFn, block.getArgument(0),
4494  block.getArgument(1), block.getArgument(2));
4495 
4496  } else {
4497  assert(false && "found unhandled category in elemwise");
4498  }
4499 
4500  yields.push_back(result);
4501  helper.yieldOutputs(yields);
4502 }
4503 
4504 LogicalResult ElementwiseOp::fold(FoldAdaptor,
4505  SmallVectorImpl<OpFoldResult> &) {
4506  return memref::foldMemRefCast(*this);
4507 }

4510  SmallVectorImpl<SideEffects::EffectInstance<MemoryEffects::Effect>>
4511  &effects) {
4512  if (hasPureTensorSemantics())
4513  return;
4514  getGenericEffectsImpl(effects, cast<LinalgOp>(getOperation()));
4515 }

4525 template <typename OpTy, typename>
4526 SmallVector<int64_t>
4527 getPackedOuterShapeWithoutTransposition(OpTy packOrUnPack) {
4528  RankedTensorType packedType = (std::is_same<OpTy, PackOp>::value)
4529  ? packOrUnPack.getDestType()
4530  : packOrUnPack.getSourceType();
4531  RankedTensorType unpackedType = (std::is_same<OpTy, PackOp>::value)
4532  ? packOrUnPack.getSourceType()
4533  : packOrUnPack.getDestType();
4534  SmallVector<int64_t> result(
4535  packedType.getShape().take_front(unpackedType.getRank()));
4536  if (!packOrUnPack.getOuterDimsPerm().empty()) {
4537  applyPermutationToVector(
4538  result, invertPermutationVector(packOrUnPack.getOuterDimsPerm()));
4539  }
4540  return result;
4541 }
4542 template SmallVector<int64_t>
4543  getPackedOuterShapeWithoutTransposition<PackOp>(PackOp);
4544 template SmallVector<int64_t>
4545  getPackedOuterShapeWithoutTransposition<UnPackOp>(UnPackOp);
4546 
4547 // Given the (potentially) updated packed type, `newPackedTy`, generates an
4548 // updated mixed-tile-sizes attribute. A tile size is updated only
4549 // when:
4550 // * a dim from newPackedTy is static, and
4551 // * the corresponding size from mixedTiles is still dynamic.
4552 // Otherwise, the original tile size is preserved.
4553 // Note - packed-type-dim and mixed-tile-size should always match!
4554 static SmallVector<OpFoldResult>
4555 getNewMixedTileSizes(PatternRewriter &rewriter, Type newPackedTy,
4556  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> mixedTiles) {
4557  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> newMixedTileSizes;
4558  for (auto it : llvm::zip(cast<ShapedType>(newPackedTy)
4559  .getShape()
4560  .take_back(mixedTiles.size()),
4561  mixedTiles)) {
4562  int64_t shape = std::get<0>(it);
4563  if (shape == ShapedType::kDynamic) {
4564  newMixedTileSizes.push_back(std::get<1>(it));
4565  continue;
4566  }
4567 
4568  // If the current result dim is static, update the dynamic mixed-size
4569  // (provided the original value is dynamic).
4570  OpFoldResult tile = std::get<1>(it);
4571  if (Attribute attr = llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<Attribute>(tile)) {
4572  // Already a constant
4573  newMixedTileSizes.push_back(tile);
4574  } else {
4575  assert(getConstantIntValue(tile).value() == shape &&
4576  "tile size and dim size don't match!");
4577  newMixedTileSizes.push_back(
4578  (rewriter.getIntegerAttr(rewriter.getIndexType(), shape)));
4579  }
4580  }
4581 
4582  return newMixedTileSizes;
4583 }
4584 
4585 template <typename OpTy>
4586 static LogicalResult
4587 reifyResultShapesImpl(OpTy op, OpBuilder &builder,
4588  ReifiedRankedShapedTypeDims &reifiedReturnShapes) {
4589  static_assert(llvm::is_one_of<OpTy, PackOp, UnPackOp>::value,
4590  "applies to only pack or unpack operations");
4591  int64_t destRank = op.getDestRank();
4592  reifiedReturnShapes.resize(1, SmallVector<OpFoldResult>(destRank));
4593  reifiedReturnShapes[0] =
4594  tensor::getMixedSizes(builder, op.getLoc(), op.getDest());
4595  return success();
4596 }
4597 
4598 template <typename OpTy>
4599 static DenseMap<int64_t, OpFoldResult> getDimAndTileMappingImpl(OpTy op) {
4600  static_assert(llvm::is_one_of<OpTy, PackOp, UnPackOp>::value,
4601  "applies to only pack or unpack operations");
4602  DenseMap<int64_t, OpFoldResult> dimAndTileMapping;
4603  ArrayRef<int64_t> dimsToTile = op.getInnerDimsPos();
4604  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> tiles = op.getMixedTiles();
4605  assert(tiles.size() == dimsToTile.size() &&
4606  "tiles must match indices of dimension to block");
4607  // bind the dimension `i` with the tile factor.
4608  for (auto i : llvm::seq<int64_t>(0, dimsToTile.size()))
4609  dimAndTileMapping[dimsToTile[i]] = tiles[i];
4610  return dimAndTileMapping;
4611 }
4612 
4613 template <typename OpTy>
4614 static SmallVector<OpFoldResult> getMixedTilesImpl(OpTy op) {
4615  static_assert(llvm::is_one_of<OpTy, PackOp, UnPackOp>::value,
4616  "applies to only pack or unpack operations");
4617  Builder builder(op);
4618  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> mixedInnerTiles;
4619  unsigned dynamicValIndex = 0;
4620  for (int64_t staticTile : op.getStaticInnerTiles()) {
4621  if (ShapedType::isStatic(staticTile))
4622  mixedInnerTiles.push_back(builder.getI64IntegerAttr(staticTile));
4623  else
4624  mixedInnerTiles.push_back(op.getInnerTiles()[dynamicValIndex++]);
4625  }
4626  return mixedInnerTiles;
4627 }
4628 
4629 template <typename OpTy>
4630 static SmallVector<int64_t> getStaticTilesImpl(OpTy op) {
4631  static_assert(llvm::is_one_of<OpTy, PackOp, UnPackOp>::value,
4632  "applies to only pack or unpack operations");
4633  SmallVector<Value> dynamicTiles;
4634  SmallVector<int64_t> staticTiles;
4635  dispatchIndexOpFoldResults(op.getMixedTiles(), dynamicTiles, staticTiles);
4636  return staticTiles;
4637 }
4638 
4639 /// Returns true if `dimsPos` is invalid. It is invalid when:
4640 /// a) It contains duplicate.
4641 /// b) At least one dimension is out of bound (`dimPos` is >= 0 and < rank).
4642 /// c) The number of elements in `dimsPos` is > than `rank`.
4643 static bool isInvalidPackingPosSpecification(ArrayRef<int64_t> dimsPos,
4644  size_t rank) {
4645  size_t dimsPosSize = dimsPos.size();
4646  if (dimsPosSize > rank)
4647  return true;
4648  DenseSet<int64_t> uniqued(llvm::from_range, dimsPos);
4649  if (dimsPosSize != uniqued.size())
4650  return true;
4651  return llvm::any_of(dimsPos, [rank](int64_t dimPos) {
4652  return dimPos < 0 || dimPos >= static_cast<int64_t>(rank);
4653  });
4654 }
4655 
4656 template <typename OpTy>
4657 static LogicalResult commonVerifierPackAndUnPackOp(OpTy packOrUnPack) {
4658  static_assert(llvm::is_one_of<OpTy, PackOp, UnPackOp>::value,
4659  "applies to only pack or unpack operations");
4660  Operation *op = packOrUnPack.getOperation();
4661 
4662  // Return true if we have a zero-value tile.
4663  auto hasZeros = [&](ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> tiles) {
4664  return llvm::any_of(tiles, isZeroInteger);
4665  };
4666 
4667  // Verify tiles. Do not allow zero tiles.
4668  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> mixedTiles = packOrUnPack.getMixedTiles();
4669  if (hasZeros(mixedTiles))
4670  return op->emitError("invalid zero tile factor");
4671 
4672  // Verify inner_dims_pos and outer_dims_perm.
4673  RankedTensorType unpackedType = (std::is_same<OpTy, PackOp>::value)
4674  ? packOrUnPack.getSourceType()
4675  : packOrUnPack.getDestType();
4676  size_t unpackedRank = unpackedType.getRank();
4677  ArrayRef<int64_t> innerDimsPos = packOrUnPack.getInnerDimsPos();
4678  ArrayRef<int64_t> outerDimPerm = packOrUnPack.getOuterDimsPerm();
4679  if (isInvalidPackingPosSpecification(innerDimsPos, unpackedRank))
4680  return op->emitError("invalid inner_dims_pos vector");
4681  if (isInvalidPackingPosSpecification(outerDimPerm, unpackedRank))
4682  return op->emitError("invalid outer_dims_perm vector");
4683  if (!outerDimPerm.empty() && outerDimPerm.size() != unpackedRank)
4684  return op->emitError("outer_dims_perm must be a permutation or empty");
4685 
4686  // Tiling factors must be less than or equal to the input rank for pack (or
4687  // output rank for unpack), and must match the number of `inner_dims_pos`.
4688  if (mixedTiles.size() > unpackedRank) {
4689  return op->emitError("tiling factors must be less than or equal to the "
4690  "input rank for pack or output rank for unpack");
4691  }
4692  if (mixedTiles.size() != innerDimsPos.size()) {
4693  return op->emitError(
4694  "tiling factors must equal the number of dimensions to tile");
4695  }
4696 
4697  ShapedType packedType = (std::is_same<OpTy, PackOp>::value)
4698  ? packOrUnPack.getDestType()
4699  : packOrUnPack.getSourceType();
4700  size_t packedRank = packedType.getRank();
4701  // Require output rank to match input rank + number of blocking factors.
4702  size_t expectedPackedRank = unpackedRank + mixedTiles.size();
4703  if (expectedPackedRank != packedRank) {
4704  return op->emitError(
4705  "packed rank != (unpacked rank + num tiling factors), got ")
4706  << packedRank << " != " << expectedPackedRank;
4707  }
4708 
4709  // Verify result shape is greater than the minimum expected
4710  // by the pack operation, and that the output shape
4711  // represents full tiles.
4712  RankedTensorType expectedPackedType = PackOp::inferPackedType(
4713  unpackedType, packOrUnPack.getStaticTiles(), innerDimsPos, outerDimPerm);
4714  if (!llvm::all_of(
4715  llvm::zip(packedType.getShape().take_back(mixedTiles.size()),
4716  mixedTiles),
4717  [](std::tuple<int64_t, OpFoldResult> it) {
4718  int64_t shape = std::get<0>(it);
4719  if (Attribute attr =
4720  llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<Attribute>(std::get<1>(it))) {
4721  IntegerAttr intAttr = dyn_cast_or_null<IntegerAttr>(attr);
4722  int64_t staticTileSize = intAttr.getValue().getSExtValue();
4723  return shape == staticTileSize;
4724  }
4725  return ShapedType::isDynamic(shape);
4726  })) {
4727  return op->emitError("mismatch in inner tile sizes specified and shaped of "
4728  "tiled dimension in the packed type");
4729  }
4730  if (failed(verifyCompatibleShape(expectedPackedType.getShape(),
4731  packedType.getShape()))) {
4732  return op->emitError("expected ")
4733  << expectedPackedType << " for the packed domain value, got "
4734  << packedType;
4735  }
4736  return success();
4737 }
4738 
4739 namespace {
4740 /// Subset of PackOp/UnPackOp fields used to compute the result of applying
4741 /// various permutations to the op.
4742 // TODO: Add linalg.transpose + pack/unpack folding patterns that just reuse
4743 // these. These may or may not become true foldings / canonicalizations
4744 // depending on how aggressive we want to be in automatically folding
4745 // transposes.
4746 struct PackOrUnPackTransposeResult {
4747  SmallVector<int64_t> innerDimsPos;
4748  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> innerTiles;
4749  SmallVector<int64_t> outerDimsPerm;
4750 };
4751 } // namespace
4752 
4753 template <typename OpTy>
4754 static PackOrUnPackTransposeResult
4755 commonPermutationOfPackAndUnPackOp(OpTy packOrUnPackOp,
4756  ArrayRef<int64_t> innerPermutation,
4757  ArrayRef<int64_t> outerPermutation) {
4758  static_assert(llvm::is_one_of<OpTy, PackOp, UnPackOp>::value,
4759  "applies to only pack or unpack operations");
4760  assert((!innerPermutation.empty() || !outerPermutation.empty()) &&
4761  "some permutation must be non-empty");
4762  PackOrUnPackTransposeResult metadata;
4763  metadata.innerDimsPos =
4764  SmallVector<int64_t>(packOrUnPackOp.getInnerDimsPos());
4765  metadata.innerTiles =
4766  SmallVector<OpFoldResult>(packOrUnPackOp.getMixedTiles());
4767  int64_t numOuterDims = std::is_same<OpTy, PackOp>::value
4768  ? packOrUnPackOp.getSourceRank()
4769  : packOrUnPackOp.getDestRank();
4770  metadata.outerDimsPerm =
4771  packOrUnPackOp.getOuterDimsPerm().empty()
4772  ? llvm::to_vector(llvm::seq<int64_t>(0, numOuterDims))
4773  : SmallVector<int64_t>(packOrUnPackOp.getOuterDimsPerm());
4774  if (!innerPermutation.empty()) {
4775  assert(innerPermutation.size() == metadata.innerDimsPos.size() &&
4776  isPermutationVector(innerPermutation) &&
4777  "invalid inner permutation");
4778  applyPermutationToVector(metadata.innerDimsPos, innerPermutation);
4779  applyPermutationToVector(metadata.innerTiles, innerPermutation);
4780  }
4781  if (!outerPermutation.empty()) {
4782  assert(outerPermutation.size() == metadata.outerDimsPerm.size() &&
4783  isPermutationVector(outerPermutation) &&
4784  "invalid outer permutation");
4785  applyPermutationToVector(metadata.outerDimsPerm, outerPermutation);
4786  }
4787  return metadata;
4788 }

4798 void PackOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &state, Value source,
4799  Value dest, ArrayRef<int64_t> innerDimsPos,
4800  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> innerTiles,
4801  std::optional<Value> paddingValue,
4802  ArrayRef<int64_t> outerDimsPerm) {
4803  assert(innerDimsPos.size() == innerTiles.size() &&
4804  "number of tile sizes specified must match the specified number of "
4805  "original dimensions to be tiled");
4806  SmallVector<int64_t> staticTileSizes;
4807  SmallVector<Value> dynamicTileSizes;
4808  dispatchIndexOpFoldResults(innerTiles, dynamicTileSizes, staticTileSizes);
4809  build(builder, state, dest.getType(), source, dest,
4810  paddingValue ? *paddingValue : nullptr,
4811  outerDimsPerm.empty() ? nullptr
4812  : builder.getDenseI64ArrayAttr(outerDimsPerm),
4813  builder.getDenseI64ArrayAttr(innerDimsPos), dynamicTileSizes,
4814  builder.getDenseI64ArrayAttr(staticTileSizes));
4815 }

4841 SmallVector<int64_t> PackOp::getTiledOuterDims() {
4842  auto innerDimsPos = getInnerDimsPos();
4843  auto packedShape = getDestType().getShape();
4844  SmallVector<int64_t> res;

4851 
4852 bool PackOp::requirePaddingValue(ArrayRef<int64_t> inputShape,
4853  ArrayRef<int64_t> innerDimsPos,
4854  ArrayRef<int64_t> outputShape,
4855  ArrayRef<int64_t> outerDimsPerm,
4856  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> innerTiles) {
4857  SmallVector<int64_t> outputTileSizes(
4858  outputShape.take_front(inputShape.size()));
4859  if (!outerDimsPerm.empty()) {
4860  assert(outerDimsPerm.size() == outputTileSizes.size() &&
4861  "expected output and outer_dims_perm to have same size");
4862  applyPermutationToVector(outputTileSizes,
4863  invertPermutationVector(outerDimsPerm));
4864  }
4865  for (auto [pos, tileSize] : llvm::zip_equal(innerDimsPos, innerTiles)) {
4866  if (ShapedType::isDynamic(inputShape[pos]))
4867  continue;
4868  std::optional<int64_t> constantTile = getConstantIntValue(tileSize);
4869 
4870  if (!constantTile) {
4871  if (ShapedType::isStatic(outputTileSizes[pos]) &&
4872  (inputShape[pos] % outputTileSizes[pos] != 0))
4873  return true;
4874  } else if (inputShape[pos] % (*constantTile) != 0) {
4875  return true;
4876  }
4877  }
4878  return false;
4879 }
4880 
4881 LogicalResult PackOp::verify() {
4882  if (failed(commonVerifierPackAndUnPackOp(*this)))
4883  return failure();
4884 
4885  // Verify padding value, and bail out if the tile does not divide the
4886  // dimension fully. In the case of dynamic tile factors or dimensions, having
4887  // a partial tile is undefined behavior.
4888  auto paddingValue = getPaddingValue();
4889  if (paddingValue &&
4890  paddingValue.getType() != getSourceType().getElementType()) {
4891  return emitOpError("expected padding_value has ")
4892  << getSourceType().getElementType()
4893  << " but got: " << paddingValue.getType();
4894  }
4895 
4896  if (!paddingValue &&
4897  requirePaddingValue(getSourceType().getShape(), getInnerDimsPos(),
4898  getDestType().getShape(), getOuterDimsPerm(),
4899  getMixedTiles())) {
4900  return emitOpError(
4901  "invalid tile factor or output size provided. Only full tiles are "
4902  "supported when padding_value is not set");
4903  }
4904  return success();
4905 }
4906 
4907 /// Converts OpFoldResults to int64_t shape entries, unconditionally mapping all
4908 /// Value's to kDynamic, even if they are arith.constant values.
4909 static SmallVector<int64_t>
4910 asShapeWithAnyValueAsDynamic(ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> ofrs) {
4911  SmallVector<int64_t> result;
4912  for (auto o : ofrs) {
4913  // Have to do this first, as getConstantIntValue special-cases constants.
4914  if (llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<Value>(o))
4915  result.push_back(ShapedType::kDynamic);
4916  else
4917  result.push_back(getConstantIntValue(o).value_or(ShapedType::kDynamic));
4918  }
4919  return result;
4920 }
4921 
4922 /// Helper for PackOp::{getResultShape,inferPackedType}. Returns the shape of
4923 /// the packed type. Having a shared helper helps implement these two methods in
4924 /// a way that ensures that they agree on which dimensions are dynamic.
4925 static SmallVector<int64_t> getPackOpResultTypeShape(
4926  ArrayRef<int64_t> sourceShape, ArrayRef<int64_t> innerTileSizes,
4927  ArrayRef<int64_t> innerDimsPos, ArrayRef<int64_t> outerDimsPerm) {
4928  SmallVector<int64_t> resultShape = llvm::to_vector(sourceShape);
4929  for (auto tiledDim : llvm::enumerate(llvm::to_vector(innerDimsPos))) {
4930  if (ShapedType::isDynamic(resultShape[tiledDim.value()]))
4931  continue;
4932  if (ShapedType::isDynamic(innerTileSizes[tiledDim.index()])) {
4933  resultShape[tiledDim.value()] = ShapedType::kDynamic;
4934  continue;
4935  }
4936  resultShape[tiledDim.value()] = llvm::divideCeilSigned(
4937  resultShape[tiledDim.value()], innerTileSizes[tiledDim.index()]);
4938  }
4939 
4940  // Swap tile loops if outer_dims_perm is available.
4941  if (!outerDimsPerm.empty())
4942  applyPermutationToVector(resultShape, outerDimsPerm);
4943 
4944  // Append the inner tile dimensions.
4945  resultShape.append(innerTileSizes.begin(), innerTileSizes.end());
4946  return resultShape;
4947 }
4948 
4949 SmallVector<OpFoldResult> PackOp::getResultShape(
4950  OpBuilder &builder, Location loc, ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> sourceDims,
4951  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> innerTileSizes, ArrayRef<int64_t> innerDimsPos,
4952  ArrayRef<int64_t> outerDimsPerm) {
4953  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> resultDims = llvm::to_vector(sourceDims);
4954 
4955  AffineExpr s0, s1;
4956  bindSymbols(builder.getContext(), s0, s1);
4957  AffineExpr ceilDivExpr = s0.ceilDiv(s1);
4958  for (auto tiledDim : llvm::enumerate(llvm::to_vector(innerDimsPos))) {
4959  resultDims[tiledDim.value()] = affine::makeComposedFoldedAffineApply(
4960  builder, loc, ceilDivExpr,
4961  {resultDims[tiledDim.value()], innerTileSizes[tiledDim.index()]});
4962  }
4963  if (!outerDimsPerm.empty())
4964  applyPermutationToVector(resultDims, outerDimsPerm);
4965  resultDims.append(innerTileSizes.begin(), innerTileSizes.end());
4966 
4967  SmallVector<int64_t> resultTypeShape =
4968  getPackOpResultTypeShape(asShapeWithAnyValueAsDynamic(sourceDims),
4969  asShapeWithAnyValueAsDynamic(innerTileSizes),
4970  innerDimsPos, outerDimsPerm);
4971 
4972  // Fix-up `resultDims` to ensure that they are Value's if and only if the
4973  // result type shape says it's a dynamic dim. This is needed as callers may
4974  // use dispatchIndexOpFoldResults on the result, and rely on exact number of
4975  // dynamic dims returned by that.
4976  for (unsigned i = 0; i < resultDims.size(); ++i) {
4977  if (ShapedType::isStatic(resultTypeShape[i]))
4978  continue;
4979  resultDims[i] =
4980  getValueOrCreateConstantIndexOp(builder, loc, resultDims[i]);
4981  }
4982 
4983  return resultDims;
4984 }
4985 
4986 /// Get the expected packed type based on source type, tile factors, position of
4987 /// the inner tiles and permutation of the outer tiled loop.
4988 RankedTensorType PackOp::inferPackedType(RankedTensorType sourceType,
4989  ArrayRef<int64_t> innerTileSizes,
4990  ArrayRef<int64_t> innerDimsPos,
4991  ArrayRef<int64_t> outerDimsPerm) {
4992  SmallVector<int64_t> resultShape = getPackOpResultTypeShape(
4993  sourceType.getShape(), innerTileSizes, innerDimsPos, outerDimsPerm);
4994  return RankedTensorType::get(resultShape, sourceType.getElementType());
4995 }
4996 
4997 Value PackOp::createDestinationTensor(OpBuilder &b, Location loc, Value source,
4998  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> innerTileSizes,
4999  ArrayRef<int64_t> innerDimsPos,
5000  ArrayRef<int64_t> outerDimsPerm) {
5001  AffineExpr dim0, dim1;
5002  bindDims(b.getContext(), dim0, dim1);
5003  auto ceilDiv = [&](OpFoldResult v1, OpFoldResult v2) -> OpFoldResult {
5004  return affine::makeComposedFoldedAffineApply(b, loc, dim0.ceilDiv(dim1),
5005  {v1, v2});
5006  };
5007 
5008  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> mixedSizes;
5009  for (auto [index, value] : llvm::enumerate(
5010  llvm::cast<RankedTensorType>(source.getType()).getShape())) {
5011  if (ShapedType::isDynamic(value))
5012  mixedSizes.push_back(
5013  tensor::DimOp::create(b, loc, source, index).getResult());
5014  else
5015  mixedSizes.push_back(b.getIndexAttr(value));
5016  }
5017  for (auto it : llvm::zip(innerDimsPos, innerTileSizes)) {
5018  int64_t dimPos = std::get<0>(it);
5019  OpFoldResult tileSize = std::get<1>(it);
5020  mixedSizes[dimPos] = ceilDiv(mixedSizes[dimPos], tileSize);
5021  }
5022  if (!outerDimsPerm.empty())
5023  applyPermutationToVector<OpFoldResult>(mixedSizes, outerDimsPerm);
5024 
5025  mixedSizes.append(innerTileSizes.begin(), innerTileSizes.end());
5026  auto elemType = llvm::cast<ShapedType>(source.getType()).getElementType();
5027  return tensor::EmptyOp::create(b, loc, mixedSizes, elemType);
5028 }
5029 
5030 PackOp PackOp::createTransposedClone(OpBuilder &b, Location loc,
5031  ArrayRef<int64_t> innerPermutation,
5032  ArrayRef<int64_t> outerPermutation) {
5033  PackOrUnPackTransposeResult metadata = commonPermutationOfPackAndUnPackOp(
5034  *this, innerPermutation, outerPermutation);
5035  Value transposedDest =
5036  createDestinationTensor(b, loc, getSource(), metadata.innerTiles,
5037  metadata.innerDimsPos, metadata.outerDimsPerm);
5038  return PackOp::create(b, loc, getSource(), transposedDest,
5039  metadata.innerDimsPos, metadata.innerTiles,
5040  getPaddingValue(), metadata.outerDimsPerm);
5041 }
5042 
5043 /// Returns true if the tiles and the tiled dims are constant.
5044 template <typename OpTy>
5045 bool areTilesAndTiledDimsAllConstant(OpTy op) {
5046  static_assert(llvm::is_one_of<OpTy, PackOp, UnPackOp>::value,
5047  "applies to only pack or unpack operations");
5048  ShapedType packedType = (std::is_same<OpTy, PackOp>::value)
5049  ? op.getDestType()
5050  : op.getSourceType();
5051  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> mixedTiles = op.getMixedTiles();
5052  for (auto [dimDest, tile] : llvm::zip(
5053  packedType.getShape().take_back(mixedTiles.size()), mixedTiles)) {
5054  std::optional<int64_t> constTileSize = getConstantIntValue(tile);
5055  if (!constTileSize || ShapedType::isDynamic(dimDest))
5056  return false;
5057  }
5058  return true;
5059 }
5060 
5061 Speculation::Speculatability PackOp::getSpeculatability() {
5062  if (getPaddingValue())
5063  return Speculation::Speculatable;
5064 
5065  // The verifier rejects already operations if we can statically prove that the
5066  // sizes of the tiles do not divide perfectly the dimension; thus, check only
5067  // to have constant tiles and tiled inner dimensions.
5068  if (!areTilesAndTiledDimsAllConstant(*this))
5069  return Speculation::NotSpeculatable;
5070 
5071  return Speculation::Speculatable;
5072 }
5073 
5074 // Return true if `inner_dims_pos` and `outer_dims_perm` target the same
5075 // dimensions for pack and unpack.
5076 static bool hasSameInnerOuterAttribute(PackOp packOp, UnPackOp unPackOp) {
5077  if (packOp.getInnerDimsPos() != unPackOp.getInnerDimsPos())
5078  return false;
5079  if (packOp.getOuterDimsPerm() == unPackOp.getOuterDimsPerm())
5080  return true;
5081  // Outer dims permutation is optional.
5082  // To compare unbalanced pack-unpack pair, treat no permutation as equal to
5083  // identity permutation.
5084  return isIdentityPermutation(packOp.getOuterDimsPerm()) &&
5085  isIdentityPermutation(unPackOp.getOuterDimsPerm());
5086 }
5087 
5088 // Return true if pack and unpack have the same tiles.
5089 // Same SSA values or same integer constants.
5090 static bool haveSameTiles(PackOp packOp, UnPackOp unPackOp) {
5091  auto packTiles = packOp.getMixedTiles();
5092  auto unPackTiles = unPackOp.getMixedTiles();
5093  if (packTiles.size() != unPackTiles.size())
5094  return false;
5095  for (size_t i = 0, e = packTiles.size(); i < e; i++) {
5096  if (!isEqualConstantIntOrValue(packTiles[i], unPackTiles[i]))
5097  return false;
5098  }
5099  return true;
5100 }
5101 
5102 /// Returns true if the pack op does not need a padding value.
5103 static bool paddingIsNotNeeded(PackOp op) {
5104  auto srcType = op.getSourceType();
5105  if (llvm::any_of(op.getInnerDimsPos(),
5106  [&](int64_t pos) { return srcType.isDynamicDim(pos); }))
5107  return false;
5108  if (ShapedType::isDynamicShape(op.getStaticInnerTiles()))
5109  return false;
5110  return !PackOp::requirePaddingValue(
5111  srcType.getShape(), op.getInnerDimsPos(), op.getDestType().getShape(),
5112  op.getOuterDimsPerm(), op.getMixedTiles());
5113 }
5114 
5115 /// Returns true if the `srcShape` or `destShape` is different from the one in
5116 /// `packOp` and populates each with the inferred static shape.
5117 static bool inferStaticShape(PackOp packOp, SmallVectorImpl<int64_t> &srcShape,
5118  SmallVectorImpl<int64_t> &destShape) {
5119  bool changeNeeded = false;
5120  srcShape.assign(packOp.getSourceType().getShape().begin(),
5121  packOp.getSourceType().getShape().end());
5122  destShape.assign(packOp.getDestType().getShape().begin(),
5123  packOp.getDestType().getShape().end());
5124  llvm::SmallSetVector<int64_t, 4> innerDims;
5125  innerDims.insert_range(packOp.getInnerDimsPos());
5126  SmallVector<int64_t> inverseOuterDimsPerm;
5127  if (!packOp.getOuterDimsPerm().empty())
5128  inverseOuterDimsPerm = invertPermutationVector(packOp.getOuterDimsPerm());
5129  int srcRank = packOp.getSourceRank();
5130  for (auto i : llvm::seq<int64_t>(0, srcRank)) {
5131  if (innerDims.contains(i))
5132  continue;
5133  int64_t srcPos = i;
5134  int64_t destPos = i;
5135  if (!inverseOuterDimsPerm.empty())
5136  destPos = inverseOuterDimsPerm[srcPos];
5137  if (ShapedType::isDynamic(srcShape[srcPos]) ==
5138  ShapedType::isDynamic(destShape[destPos])) {
5139  continue;
5140  }
5141  int64_t size = srcShape[srcPos];
5142  if (ShapedType::isDynamic(size))
5143  size = destShape[destPos];
5144  srcShape[srcPos] = size;
5145  destShape[destPos] = size;
5146  changeNeeded = true;
5147  }
5148  return changeNeeded;
5149 }
5150 
5151 LogicalResult PackOp::canonicalize(PackOp packOp, PatternRewriter &rewriter) {
5152  // Fold an pack(unpack(x)) to x.
5153  if (auto unPackOp = packOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<UnPackOp>()) {
5154  if (unPackOp.getSourceType() != packOp.getDestType())
5155  return failure();
5156  if (packOp.getPaddingValue() ||
5157  !hasSameInnerOuterAttribute(packOp, unPackOp) ||
5158  !haveSameTiles(packOp, unPackOp))
5159  return failure();
5160  rewriter.replaceOp(packOp, unPackOp.getSource());
5161  return success();
5162  }
5163 
5164  // Fold optional PaddingValue operand away if padding is not needed.
5165  if (packOp.getPaddingValue() && paddingIsNotNeeded(packOp)) {
5166  rewriter.startOpModification(packOp);
5167  packOp.getPaddingValueMutable().clear();
5168  rewriter.finalizeOpModification(packOp);
5169  return success();
5170  }
5171 
5172  // Insert tensor.cast ops if static shape inference is available..
5173  SmallVector<int64_t> srcShape, destShape;
5174  if (inferStaticShape(packOp, srcShape, destShape)) {
5175  Location loc = packOp.getLoc();
5176  Value source = packOp.getSource();
5177  if (srcShape != packOp.getSourceType().getShape()) {
5178  auto newSrcType = packOp.getSourceType().clone(srcShape);
5179  source =
5180  tensor::CastOp::create(rewriter, loc, newSrcType, packOp.getSource());
5181  }
5182  Value dest = packOp.getDest();
5183  RankedTensorType originalResultType = packOp.getDestType();
5184  bool needUpdateDestType = (destShape != originalResultType.getShape());
5185  if (needUpdateDestType) {
5186  auto newDestType = packOp.getDestType().clone(destShape);
5187  dest =
5188  tensor::CastOp::create(rewriter, loc, newDestType, packOp.getDest());
5189  }
5190  rewriter.modifyOpInPlace(packOp, [&] {
5191  packOp.getSourceMutable().assign(source);
5192  packOp.getDestMutable().assign(dest);
5193  packOp.getResult().setType(cast<RankedTensorType>(dest.getType()));
5194  });
5195  // Insert a cast if needed
5196  if (needUpdateDestType) {
5197  rewriter.setInsertionPointAfter(packOp);
5198  auto castOp =
5199  tensor::CastOp::create(rewriter, loc, originalResultType, packOp);
5200  rewriter.replaceAllUsesExcept(packOp, castOp, castOp);
5201  }
5202  return success();
5203  }
5204 
5205  return failure();
5206 }
5207 
5208 template <typename PackOrUnpackOp>
5209 static bool isLikePadUnPad(PackOrUnpackOp packOp,
5210  RankedTensorType packedTensorType) {
5211  static_assert(std::is_same<PackOrUnpackOp, PackOp>::value ||
5212  std::is_same<PackOrUnpackOp, UnPackOp>::value,
5213  "Function meant for pack/unpack");
5214  // This is a pad if packing only adds ones and we don't transpose dimensions.
5215 
5216  // Check that we are not transposing any dimensions.
5217  ArrayRef<int64_t> innerDimsPos = packOp.getInnerDimsPos();
5218  int64_t numPackedDims = innerDimsPos.size();
5219  auto orderedDims = llvm::to_vector<4>(llvm::seq<int64_t>(0, numPackedDims));
5220  if (orderedDims != innerDimsPos) {
5221  // Dimensions don't happen in order.
5222  return false;
5223  }
5224 
5225  ArrayRef<int64_t> packedShape = packedTensorType.getShape();
5226  int64_t packedRank = packedTensorType.getRank();
5227  // At this point we know that we are taking numPackedDims outer
5228  // dimensions and pushing them all the way as the inner most dimensions.
5229  // What's left on the outer most dimensions is, in this order:
5230  // - the factor of the packed dimensions, then
5231  // - the untouched dimensions
5232  // This shifting inward of dimensions is a no-op (as opposed to a transpose)
5233  // if all the dimensions that bubble outerward are ones.
5234  // Therefore check that all the dimensions but the numPackedDims inner most
5235  // ones are ones.
5236  return llvm::all_of(
5237  llvm::seq<int64_t>(0, packedRank - numPackedDims),
5238  [&packedShape](int64_t i) { return packedShape[i] == 1; });
5239 }
5240 
5241 bool PackOp::isLikePad() {
5242  auto packedTensorType =
5243  llvm::cast<RankedTensorType>((*this)->getResultTypes().front());
5244  return isLikePadUnPad(*this, packedTensorType);
5245 }
5246 
5247 OpFoldResult PackOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
5248  std::optional<Attribute> paddingValue;
5249  if (auto pad = adaptor.getPaddingValue())
5250  paddingValue = pad;
5251  if (OpFoldResult reshapedSource = reshapeConstantSource(
5252  llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<DenseElementsAttr>(adaptor.getSource()),
5253  getDestType(), paddingValue))
5254  return reshapedSource;
5255  return {};
5256 }
5257 
5258 /// Folds a tensor.cast op into a consuming PackOp op if the
5259 /// `tensor.cast` has source that is more static than the consuming op.
5260 ///
5261 /// Example:
5262 /// ```mlir
5263 /// %1 = tensor.cast %0 : tensor<8x16xf32> to tensor<?x?xf32>
5264 /// %2 = tensor.pack %1 ... : tensor<?x?xf32> ...
5265 /// ```
5266 ///
5267 /// folds into:
5268 ///
5269 /// ```mlir
5270 /// %2 = tensor.pack %0 ... : tensor<8x16xf32> ...
5271 /// ```
5272 struct FoldTensorCastPackOp : public OpRewritePattern<PackOp> {
5273  using OpRewritePattern<PackOp>::OpRewritePattern;
5274 
5275  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(PackOp op,
5276  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
5277  if (!tensor::hasFoldableTensorCastOperand(op))
5278  return failure();
5279 
5280  SmallVector<Type> newResultTypes(op->getResultTypes());
5281  SmallVector<Value> newOperands =
5282  tensor::getUpdatedOperandsAfterCastOpFolding(op, newResultTypes);
5283 
5284  // Get the updated mixed-tile-sizes attribute.
5285  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> newMixedTileSizes =
5286  getNewMixedTileSizes(rewriter, newResultTypes[0], op.getMixedTiles());
5287 
5288  // Clone op.
5289  // TODO: Strictly speaking, discardable attributes should be _discarded_ at
5290  // this point. However, in practice, we use them for things that we'd like
5291  // to preserve. Implement a better abstraction.
5292  PackOp newOp =
5293  PackOp::create(rewriter, op.getLoc(), newOperands[0], newOperands[1],
5294  op.getInnerDimsPos(), newMixedTileSizes,
5295  op.getPaddingValue(), op.getOuterDimsPerm());
5296  newOp->setDiscardableAttrs(op->getDiscardableAttrDictionary());
5297 
5298  // Replace op.
5299  Value oldResult = op.getResult();
5300  Value newResult = newOp.getResult();
5301  Value replacement =
5302  (newResult.getType() != oldResult.getType())
5303  ? tensor::CastOp::create(rewriter, op->getLoc(),
5304  oldResult.getType(), newResult)
5305  : newResult;
5306 
5307  rewriter.replaceOp(op, {replacement});
5308 
5309  return success();
5310  }
5311 };

5369 void UnPackOp::build(OpBuilder &builder, OperationState &state, Value source,
5370  Value dest, ArrayRef<int64_t> innerDimsPos,
5371  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> innerTiles,
5372  ArrayRef<int64_t> outerDimsPerm) {
5373  assert(innerDimsPos.size() == innerTiles.size() &&
5374  "number of tile sizes specified must match the specified number of "
5375  "original dimensions to be tiled");
5376  SmallVector<int64_t> staticTileSizes;
5377  SmallVector<Value> dynamicTileSizes;
5378  dispatchIndexOpFoldResults(innerTiles, dynamicTileSizes, staticTileSizes);
5379  build(builder, state, dest.getType(), source, dest,
5380  outerDimsPerm.empty() ? nullptr
5381  : builder.getDenseI64ArrayAttr(outerDimsPerm),
5382  builder.getDenseI64ArrayAttr(innerDimsPos), dynamicTileSizes,
5383  builder.getDenseI64ArrayAttr(staticTileSizes));
5384 }
5385 
5386 Value UnPackOp::createDestinationTensor(OpBuilder &b, Location loc,
5387  Value source,
5388  ArrayRef<OpFoldResult> innerTileSizes,
5389  ArrayRef<int64_t> innerDimsPos,
5390  ArrayRef<int64_t> outerDimsPerm) {
5391  AffineExpr sym0, sym1;
5392  bindSymbols(b.getContext(), sym0, sym1);
5393  auto dimMul = [&](OpFoldResult v1, OpFoldResult v2) -> OpFoldResult {
5394  return affine::makeComposedFoldedAffineApply(b, loc, sym0 * sym1, {v1, v2});
5395  };
5396 
5397  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> mixedSizes;
5398  auto srcType = llvm::cast<RankedTensorType>(source.getType());
5399  for (auto i :
5400  llvm::seq<unsigned>(0, srcType.getRank() - innerTileSizes.size())) {
5401  if (srcType.isDynamicDim(i))
5402  mixedSizes.push_back(
5403  tensor::DimOp::create(b, loc, source, i).getResult());
5404  else
5405  mixedSizes.push_back(b.getIndexAttr(srcType.getDimSize(i)));
5406  }
5407  if (!outerDimsPerm.empty()) {
5408  applyPermutationToVector<OpFoldResult>(
5409  mixedSizes, invertPermutationVector(outerDimsPerm));
5410  }
5411 
5412  for (auto [dimPos, tileSize] : llvm::zip_equal(innerDimsPos, innerTileSizes))
5413  mixedSizes[dimPos] = dimMul(mixedSizes[dimPos], tileSize);
5414 
5415  auto elemType = srcType.getElementType();
5416  return tensor::EmptyOp::create(b, loc, mixedSizes, elemType);
5417 }

5419 UnPackOp UnPackOp::createTransposedClone(OpBuilder &b, Location loc,
5420  Value transposedSource,
5421  ArrayRef<int64_t> innerPermutation,
5422  ArrayRef<int64_t> outerPermutation) {
5423  PackOrUnPackTransposeResult metadata = commonPermutationOfPackAndUnPackOp(
5424  *this, innerPermutation, outerPermutation);
5425  return UnPackOp::create(b, loc, transposedSource, getDest(),
5426  metadata.innerDimsPos, metadata.innerTiles,
5427  metadata.outerDimsPerm);
5428 }

5430 /// Returns true if the `srcShape` or `destShape` is different from the one in
5431 /// `op` and populates each with the inferred static shape.
5432 static bool inferStaticShape(UnPackOp op, SmallVectorImpl<int64_t> &srcShape,
5433  SmallVectorImpl<int64_t> &destShape) {
5434  bool changeNeeded = false;
5435  srcShape.assign(op.getSourceType().getShape().begin(),
5436  op.getSourceType().getShape().end());
5437  destShape.assign(op.getDestType().getShape().begin(),
5438  op.getDestType().getShape().end());
5439  llvm::SmallSetVector<int64_t, 4> innerDims;
5440  innerDims.insert_range(op.getInnerDimsPos());
5441  SmallVector<int64_t> inverseOuterDimsPerm;
5442  if (!op.getOuterDimsPerm().empty())
5443  inverseOuterDimsPerm = invertPermutationVector(op.getOuterDimsPerm());
5444  int destRank = op.getDestRank();
5445  for (auto i : llvm::seq<int64_t>(0, destRank)) {
5446  if (innerDims.contains(i))
5447  continue;
5448  int64_t srcPos = i;
5449  int64_t destPos = i;
5450  if (!inverseOuterDimsPerm.empty())
5451  srcPos = inverseOuterDimsPerm[destPos];
5452  if (ShapedType::isDynamic(srcShape[srcPos]) ==
5453  ShapedType::isDynamic(destShape[destPos])) {
5454  continue;
5455  }
5456  int64_t size = srcShape[srcPos];
5457  if (ShapedType::isDynamic(size))
5458  size = destShape[destPos];
5459  srcShape[srcPos] = size;
5460  destShape[destPos] = size;
5461  changeNeeded = true;
5462  }
5463  return changeNeeded;
5464 }
5465 
5466 LogicalResult UnPackOp::canonicalize(UnPackOp unPackOp,
5467  PatternRewriter &rewriter) {
5468  /// unpack(pack(x)) -> x
5469  if (PackOp packOp = unPackOp.getSource().getDefiningOp<PackOp>()) {
5470  if (packOp.getSourceType() != unPackOp.getDestType())
5471  return failure();
5472  if (packOp.getPaddingValue() ||
5473  !hasSameInnerOuterAttribute(packOp, unPackOp) ||
5474  !haveSameTiles(packOp, unPackOp))
5475  return failure();
5476  rewriter.replaceOp(unPackOp, packOp.getSource());
5477  return success();
5478  }
5479  /// unpack(destinationStyleOp(x)) -> unpack(x)
5480  if (auto dstStyleOp =
5481  unPackOp.getDest().getDefiningOp<DestinationStyleOpInterface>()) {
5482  auto destValue = cast<OpResult>(unPackOp.getDest());
5483  Value newDest = dstStyleOp.getDpsInits()[destValue.getResultNumber()];
5484  rewriter.modifyOpInPlace(unPackOp,
5485  [&]() { unPackOp.setDpsInitOperand(0, newDest); });
5486  return success();
5487  }
5488  /// extract_slice(unpack(x into y)) -> unpack(x into extract_slice(y))
5489  if (unPackOp->hasOneUse()) {
5490  auto extractSliceUser =
5491  dyn_cast<tensor::ExtractSliceOp>(*unPackOp->getUsers().begin());
5492  if (extractSliceUser && unPackOp.canFoldSliceOp(extractSliceUser)) {
5493  OpBuilder::InsertionGuard g(rewriter);
5494  rewriter.setInsertionPoint(unPackOp);
5495  auto newDest = tensor::ExtractSliceOp::create(
5496  rewriter, unPackOp->getLoc(), unPackOp.getDest(),
5497  extractSliceUser.getMixedOffsets(), extractSliceUser.getMixedSizes(),
5498  extractSliceUser.getMixedStrides());
5499  rewriter.modifyOpInPlace(unPackOp, [&]() {
5500  unPackOp.setDpsInitOperand(0, newDest);
5501  unPackOp.getResult().setType(newDest.getType());
5502  });
5503  rewriter.replaceOp(extractSliceUser, unPackOp);
5504  return success();
5505  }
5506  }
5507 
5508  // Insert tensor.cast ops if static shape inference is available..
5509  SmallVector<int64_t> srcShape, destShape;
5510  if (inferStaticShape(unPackOp, srcShape, destShape)) {
5511  Location loc = unPackOp.getLoc();
5512  Value source = unPackOp.getSource();
5513  if (srcShape != unPackOp.getSourceType().getShape()) {
5514  auto newSrcType = unPackOp.getSourceType().clone(srcShape);
5515  source = tensor::CastOp::create(rewriter, loc, newSrcType,
5516  unPackOp.getSource());
5517  }
5518  Value dest = unPackOp.getDest();
5519  if (destShape != unPackOp.getDestType().getShape()) {
5520  auto newDestType = unPackOp.getDestType().clone(destShape);
5521  dest = tensor::CastOp::create(rewriter, loc, newDestType,
5522  unPackOp.getDest());
5523  }
5524  Value newOp = UnPackOp::create(
5525  rewriter, loc, source, dest, unPackOp.getInnerDimsPos(),
5526  unPackOp.getMixedTiles(), unPackOp.getOuterDimsPerm());
5527  rewriter.replaceOpWithNewOp<tensor::CastOp>(
5528  unPackOp, unPackOp.getResult().getType(), newOp);
5529  return success();
5530  }
5531 
5532  return failure();
5533 }
5534 
5535 bool UnPackOp::canFoldSliceOp(tensor::ExtractSliceOp sliceOp) {
5536  // Rank-reduced folding is not supported.
5537  if (sliceOp.getResultType().getRank() != this->getDestType().getRank())
5538  return false;
5539  if (!areAllConstantIntValue(sliceOp.getMixedOffsets(), 0) ||
5540  !areAllConstantIntValue(sliceOp.getMixedStrides(), 1))
5541  return false;
5542  RankedTensorType unpackedTypeAfterFold = sliceOp.getResultType();
5543  SmallVector<int64_t> outerShapeWithoutTranspose =
5544  getPackedOuterShapeWithoutTransposition(*this);
5545  for (auto [pos, tileSize] :
5546  llvm::zip_equal(this->getInnerDimsPos(), this->getStaticInnerTiles())) {
5547  if (unpackedTypeAfterFold.isDynamicDim(pos))
5548  return false;
5549  if (ShapedType::isDynamic(outerShapeWithoutTranspose[pos]))
5550  return false;
5551  if (ShapedType::isDynamic(tileSize))
5552  return false;
5553  int64_t paddingSize = outerShapeWithoutTranspose[pos] * tileSize -
5554  unpackedTypeAfterFold.getDimSize(pos);
5555  if (paddingSize >= tileSize)
5556  return false;
5557  }
5558  return true;
5559 }
5560 
5561 bool UnPackOp::isLikeUnPad() {
5562  RankedTensorType packedTensorType = getSourceType();
5563  return isLikePadUnPad(*this, packedTensorType);
5564 }

5566 OpFoldResult UnPackOp::fold(FoldAdaptor adaptor) {
5567  if (OpFoldResult reshapedSource = reshapeConstantSource(
5568  llvm::dyn_cast_if_present<DenseElementsAttr>(adaptor.getSource()),
5569  getResult().getType()))
5570  return reshapedSource;
5571  return {};
5572 }
5573 
5574 /// Folds a tensor.cast op into a consuming UnPackOp op if the
5575 /// `tensor.cast` has source that is more static than the consuming op.
5576 ///
5577 /// Example:
5578 /// ```mlir
5579 /// %1 = tensor.cast %0 : tensor<1x1x8x1xi32> to tensor<1x1x?x1xi32>
5580 /// %2 = tensor.unpack %1 ... : tensor<1x1x?x1xi32> -> tensor<7x?xi32>
5581 /// ```
5582 ///
5583 /// folds into:
5584 ///
5585 /// ```mlir
5586 /// %2 = tensor.unpack %0 ... tensor<1x1x8x1xi32> -> tensor<7x?xi32>
5587 /// ```
5588 struct FoldTensorCastUnPackOp : public OpRewritePattern<UnPackOp> {
5589  using OpRewritePattern<UnPackOp>::OpRewritePattern;
5590 
5591  LogicalResult matchAndRewrite(UnPackOp op,
5592  PatternRewriter &rewriter) const override {
5593  if (!tensor::hasFoldableTensorCastOperand(op))
5594  return failure();
5595 
5596  SmallVector<Type> newResultTypes(op->getResultTypes());
5597  SmallVector<Value> newOperands =
5598  tensor::getUpdatedOperandsAfterCastOpFolding(op, newResultTypes);
5599  Value sourceTensor = newOperands[0];
5600 
5601  // Get the updated mixed-tile-sizes attribute.
5602  SmallVector<OpFoldResult> newMixedTileSizes = getNewMixedTileSizes(
5603  rewriter, sourceTensor.getType(), op.getMixedTiles());
5604 
5605  // Clone op.
5606  // TODO: Strictly speaking, discardable attributes should be _discarded_ at
5607  // this point. However, in practice, we use them for things that we'd like
5608  // to preserve. Implement a better abstraction.
5609  UnPackOp newOp = UnPackOp::create(rewriter, op.getLoc(), sourceTensor,
5610  newOperands[1], op.getInnerDimsPos(),
5611  newMixedTileSizes, op.getOuterDimsPerm());
5612  newOp->setDiscardableAttrs(op->getDiscardableAttrDictionary());
5613 
5614  // Replace op.
5615  Value oldResult = op.getResult();
5616  Value newResult = newOp.getResult();
5617  Value replacement =
5618  (newResult.getType() != oldResult.getType())
5619  ? tensor::CastOp::create(rewriter, op->getLoc(),
5620  oldResult.getType(), newResult)
5621  : newResult;
5622 
5623  rewriter.replaceOp(op, {replacement});
5624 
5625  return success();
5626  }
5627 };

5638 SmallVector<AffineMap>
5639 BatchReduceMatmulOp::getDefaultIndexingMaps(MLIRContext *context) {
5640  AffineExpr d0, d1, d2, d3;
5641  SmallVector<AffineMap> indexingMaps;
5642  bindDims(context, d0, d1, d2, d3);
5643  indexingMaps.push_back(AffineMap::get(4, 0, {d0, d1, d3}, context));
5644  indexingMaps.push_back(AffineMap::get(4, 0, {d0, d3, d2}, context));
5645  indexingMaps.push_back(AffineMap::get(4, 0, {d1, d2}, context));
5646  return indexingMaps;
5647 }

5655 /// Check if the op has broadcast and/or transpose semantic. Returns true if
5656 /// the user defined indexing maps are not equal to default map.
5657 bool BatchReduceMatmulOp::hasUserDefinedMaps() {
5658  SmallVector<AffineMap, 3> defaultMaps =
5659  getDefaultIndexingMaps(this->getContext());
5660  SmallVector<AffineMap, 3> explicitMaps = getIndexingMapsArray();
5661  return defaultMaps != explicitMaps;
5662 }
5663 
5664 /// Returns true if the given bcastMap map is a valid broadcast map. A valid
5665 /// broadcast map must include K dimension.
5666 /// TODO: Strict inclusion of K dimension in the broadcast map is not
5667 /// necessary for both input matrices simultaneously. We can relax this
5668 /// condition to have K dimension for one input matrix map and infer the K
5669 /// dimension for other input matrix map from the one already having K
5670 /// dimension.
5671 bool BatchReduceMatmulOp::isValidLhsRhsBroadcastMap(AffineMap bcastMap,
5672  bool isLHS) {
5673  assert(bcastMap.getNumResults() < 3 &&
5674  "Expected less than 3 result dim expr.");
5675  bool isValid = false;
5676  enum Indices { batchPos, mPos, nPos, kPos };
5677  if (bcastMap.getNumResults() == 1) {
5678  AffineExpr expr = bcastMap.getResult(0);
5679  isValid = expr.isFunctionOfDim(kPos);
5680  } else if (bcastMap.getNumResults() == 2) {
5681  AffineExpr expr0 = bcastMap.getResult(0);
5682  AffineExpr expr1 = bcastMap.getResult(1);
5683  isValid =
5684  isLHS ? ((expr0.isFunctionOfDim(batchPos) ||
5685  expr0.isFunctionOfDim(mPos)) &&
5686  expr1.isFunctionOfDim(kPos))
5687  : ((expr0.isFunctionOfDim(batchPos) &&
5688  expr1.isFunctionOfDim(kPos)) ||
5689  (expr0.isFunctionOfDim(kPos) && expr1.isFunctionOfDim(nPos)));
5690  }
5691  return isValid;
5692 }
5693 
5694 void BatchReduceMatmulOp::regionBuilder(
5695  ImplicitLocOpBuilder &b, Block &block, ArrayRef<NamedAttribute> attrs,
5696  function_ref<InFlightDiagnostic()> emitError) {
5697  if (emitError && block.getNumArguments() != 3) {
5698  emitError() << "BatchReduceMatmulOp regionBuilder expects 3 args, got "
5699  << block.getNumArguments();
5700  return;
5701  }
5702  assert(block.getNumArguments() == 3 &&
5703  "BatchReduceMatmulOp regionBuilder expects 3 args");
5704  RegionBuilderHelper helper(b, block);
5705  SmallVector<Value> yields;
5706 
5707  auto toType = block.getArgument(2).getType();
5708  Value castValA =
5709  helper.buildTypeFn(TypeFn::cast_signed, toType, block.getArgument(0));
5710  Value castValB =
5711  helper.buildTypeFn(TypeFn::cast_signed, toType, block.getArgument(1));
5712  Value mulVal = helper.buildBinaryFn(BinaryFn::mul, castValA, castValB);
5713  Value addVal =
5714  helper.buildBinaryFn(BinaryFn::add, block.getArgument(2), mulVal);
5715  yields.push_back(addVal);
5716  helper.yieldOutputs(yields);
5717 }
5718 
5719 ParseResult BatchReduceMatmulOp::parse(OpAsmParser &parser,
5720  OperationState &result) {
5721  SmallVector<Attribute, 3> indexingMapsAttr;
5722  Attribute mapAttr;
5723  if (succeeded(parser.parseOptionalKeyword("indexing_maps"))) {
5724  if (parser.parseEqual())
5725  return failure();
5726  if (parser.parseLSquare())
5727  return failure();
5728 
5729  do {
5730  if (parser.parseAttribute(mapAttr))
5731  return failure();
5732  if (!isa<AffineMapAttr>(mapAttr)) {
5733  return parser.emitError(parser.getCurrentLocation(),
5734  "expected affine map attribute");
5735  }
5736  indexingMapsAttr.push_back(mapAttr);
5737 
5738  if (parser.parseOptionalComma())
5739  break;
5740  } while (true);
5741 
5742  if (parser.parseRSquare())
5743  return failure();
5744  }
5745  // Initialize indexingMaps, if not supplied explicitly.
5746  if (indexingMapsAttr.empty()) {
5747  indexingMapsAttr = llvm::map_to_vector(
5748  BatchReduceMatmulOp::getDefaultIndexingMaps(parser.getContext()),
5749  [](AffineMap map) -> Attribute { return AffineMapAttr::get(map); });
5750  }
5751  result.addAttribute("indexing_maps",
5752  parser.getBuilder().getArrayAttr(indexingMapsAttr));
5753  return ::parseNamedStructuredOp(parser, result,
5754  BatchReduceMatmulOp::getNumRegionArgs(),
5755  BatchReduceMatmulOp::getRegionBuilder());
5756 }
5757 
5758 void BatchReduceMatmulOp::print(OpAsmPrinter &p) {
5759  SmallVector<Attribute, 3> indexingMaps = llvm::map_to_vector(
5760  BatchReduceMatmulOp::getDefaultIndexingMaps(getContext()),
5761  [](AffineMap map) -> Attribute { return AffineMapAttr::get(map); });
5762 
5763  if (!llvm::equal(getIndexingMaps(), indexingMaps)) {
5764  p << " indexing_maps = [";
5765  llvm::interleaveComma(getIndexingMaps(), p,
5766  [&](Attribute attr) { p.printAttribute(attr); });
5767  p << "]";
5768  }
5769 
5770  SmallVector<StringRef, 3> elidedAttrs = {
5771  "operandSegmentSizes", "linalg.memoized_indexing_maps", "indexing_maps"};
5772  ::printNamedStructuredOp(p, getOperation(), getInputs(), getOutputs(),
5773  elidedAttrs);
5774 }

5776 /// Verify the user defined indexing maps.
5777 LogicalResult BatchReduceMatmulOp::verify() {
5778  // Verification of pure batch_reduce_matmul is handled by
5779  // verifyStructuredOpInterface().
5780  if (!hasUserDefinedMaps())
5781  return success();
5782 
5783  for (unsigned opIndex = 0; opIndex < 3; opIndex++) {
5784  if (failed(verifyExtendedBatchVariantMatmulSemantic(*this, opIndex)))
5785  return failure();
5786  }
5787  return success();
5788 }
